127 //---------------------------------------------------------
128 // lastChordTicks
129 //---------------------------------------------------------
130 
131 // find the duration of the chord starting at or after s in track and ending at tick
132 
133 static Fraction lastChordTicks(const Segment* s, const int track, const Fraction& tick)
134  {
135  while (s && s->tick() < tick) {
136  Element* el = s->element(track);
137  if (el && el->isChordRest()) {
138  ChordRest* cr = static_cast<ChordRest*>(el);
139  if (cr->tick() + cr->actualTicks() == tick)
140  return cr->actualTicks();
141  }
142  s = s->nextCR(track, true);
143  }
144  return Fraction(0,1);
145  }
146 
147 //---------------------------------------------------------
148 // setExtend
149 //---------------------------------------------------------
150 
151 // set extend for lyric no in track to end at tick
152 // called when lyric (with or without "extend") or note with "extend type=stop" is found
153 // note that no == -1 means all lyrics in this track
154 
155 void MusicXmlLyricsExtend::setExtend(const int no, const int track, const Fraction& tick)
156  {
157  QList<Lyrics*> list;
158  foreach(Lyrics* l, _lyrics) {
159  Element* const el = l->parent();
160  if (el->type() == ElementType::CHORD) { // TODO: rest also possible ?
161  ChordRest* const par = static_cast<ChordRest*>(el);
162  if (par->track() == track && (no == -1 || l->no() == no)) {
163  Fraction lct = lastChordTicks(l->segment(), track, tick);
164  if (lct > Fraction(0,1)) {
165  // set lyric tick to the total length from the lyric note
166  // plus all notes covered by the melisma minus the last note length
167  l->setTicks(tick - par->tick() - lct);
168  }
169  list.append(l);
170  }
171  }
172  }
173  // cleanup
174  foreach(Lyrics* l, list) {
175  _lyrics.remove(l);
176  }
177  }

179 //---------------------------------------------------------
180 // MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch
181 //---------------------------------------------------------
182 
183 /**
184  Convert MusicXML \a step (0=C, 1=D, etc.) / \a alter / \a octave to midi pitch.
185  Note: same code is in pass 1 and in pass 2.
186  TODO: combine
187  */
188 
189 static int MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch(int step, int alter, int octave)
190  {
191  // c d e f g a b
192  static int table[7] = { 0, 2, 4, 5, 7, 9, 11 };
193  if (step < 0 || step > 6) {
194  qDebug("MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch: illegal step %d", step);
195  return -1;
196  }
197  int pitch = table[step] + alter + (octave+1) * 12;
198 
199  if (pitch < 0)
200  pitch = -1;
201  if (pitch > 127)
202  pitch = -1;
203 
204  return pitch;
205  }
206 
207 //---------------------------------------------------------
208 // xmlSetPitch
209 //---------------------------------------------------------
210 
211 /**
212  Convert MusicXML \a step / \a alter / \a octave to midi pitch,
213  set pitch and tpc.
214  Note that n's staff and track have not been set yet
215  */
216 
217 static void xmlSetPitch(Note* n, int step, int alter, int octave, const int octaveShift, const Instrument* const instr)
218  {
219  //qDebug("xmlSetPitch(n=%p, step=%d, alter=%d, octave=%d, octaveShift=%d)",
220  // n, step, alter, octave, octaveShift);
221 
222  //const Staff* staff = n->score()->staff(track / VOICES);
223  //const Instrument* instr = staff->part()->instr();
224 
225  const Interval intval = instr->transpose();
226 
227  //qDebug(" staff=%p instr=%p dia=%d chro=%d",
228  // staff, instr, static_cast<int>(intval.diatonic), static_cast<int>(intval.chromatic));
229 
230  int pitch = MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch(step, alter, octave);
231  pitch += intval.chromatic; // assume not in concert pitch
232  pitch += 12 * octaveShift; // correct for octave shift
233  // ensure sane values
234  pitch = limit(pitch, 0, 127);
235 
236  int tpc2 = step2tpc(step, AccidentalVal(alter));
237  int tpc1 = Ms::transposeTpc(tpc2, intval, true);
238  n->setPitch(pitch, tpc1, tpc2);
239  //qDebug(" pitch=%d tpc1=%d tpc2=%d", n->pitch(), n->tpc1(), n->tpc2());
240  }
241 
242 //---------------------------------------------------------
243 // fillGap
244 //---------------------------------------------------------
245 
246 /**
247  Fill one gap (tstart - tend) in this track in this measure with rest(s).
248  */
249 
250 static void fillGap(Measure* measure, int track, const Fraction& tstart, const Fraction& tend)
251  {
252  Fraction ctick = tstart;
253  Fraction restLen = tend - tstart;
254  // qDebug("\nfillGIFV fillGap(measure %p track %d tstart %d tend %d) restLen %d len",
255  // measure, track, tstart, tend, restLen);
256  // note: as MScore::division (#ticks in a quarter note) equals 480
257  // MScore::division / 64 (#ticks in a 256th note) uequals 7.5 but is rounded down to 7
258  while (restLen > Fraction(1,256)) {
259  Fraction len = restLen;
260  TDuration d(TDuration::DurationType::V_INVALID);
261  if (measure->ticks() == restLen)
262  d.setType(TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE);
263  else
264  d.setVal(len.ticks());
265  Rest* rest = new Rest(measure->score(), d);
266  rest->setTicks(len);
267  rest->setTrack(track);
268  rest->setVisible(false);
269  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, tstart);
270  s->add(rest);
271  len = rest->globalTicks();
272  // qDebug(" %d", len);
273  ctick += len;
274  restLen -= len;
275  }
276  }
277 
278 //---------------------------------------------------------
279 // fillGapsInFirstVoices
280 //---------------------------------------------------------
281 
282 /**
283  Fill gaps in first voice of every staff in this measure for this part with rest(s).
284  */
285 
286 static void fillGapsInFirstVoices(Measure* measure, Part* part)
287  {
288  Q_ASSERT(measure);
289  Q_ASSERT(part);
290 
291  Fraction measTick = measure->tick();
292  Fraction measLen = measure->ticks();
293  Fraction nextMeasTick = measTick + measLen;
294  int staffIdx = part->score()->staffIdx(part);
295  /*
296  qDebug("fillGIFV measure %p part %p idx %d nstaves %d tick %d - %d (len %d)",
297  measure, part, staffIdx, part->nstaves(),
298  measTick, nextMeasTick, measLen);
299  */
300  for (int st = 0; st < part->nstaves(); ++st) {
301  int track = (staffIdx + st) * VOICES;
302  Fraction endOfLastCR = measTick;
303  for (Segment* s = measure->first(); s; s = s->next()) {
304  // qDebug("fillGIFV segment %p tp %s", s, s->subTypeName());
305  Element* el = s->element(track);
306  if (el) {
307  // qDebug(" el[%d] %p", track, el);
308  if (s->isChordRestType()) {
309  ChordRest* cr = static_cast<ChordRest*>(el);
310  Fraction crTick = cr->tick();
311  Fraction crLen = cr->globalTicks();
312  Fraction nextCrTick = crTick + crLen;
313  /*
314  qDebug(" chord/rest tick %d - %d (len %d)",
315  crTick, nextCrTick, crLen);
316  */
317  if (crTick > endOfLastCR) {
318  /*
319  qDebug(" GAP: track %d tick %d - %d",
320  track, endOfLastCR, crTick);
321  */
322  fillGap(measure, track, endOfLastCR, crTick);
323  }
324  endOfLastCR = nextCrTick;
325  }
326  }
327  }
328  if (nextMeasTick > endOfLastCR) {
329  /*
330  qDebug("fillGIFV measure end GAP: track %d tick %d - %d",
331  track, endOfLastCR, nextMeasTick);
332  */
333  fillGap(measure, track, endOfLastCR, nextMeasTick);
334  }
335  }
336  }

338 //---------------------------------------------------------
339 // hasDrumset
340 //---------------------------------------------------------
341 
342 /**
343  Determine if \a instruments contains a valid drumset.
344  This is the case if any instrument has a midi-unpitched element.
345  */
346 
347 static bool hasDrumset(const MusicXMLInstruments& instruments)
348  {
349  bool res = false;
350  MusicXMLInstrumentsIterator ii(instruments);
351  while (ii.hasNext()) {
352  ii.next();
353  // debug: dump the instruments
354  //qDebug("instrument: %s %s", qPrintable(ii.key()), qPrintable(ii.value().toString()));
355  // find valid unpitched values
356  int unpitched = ii.value().unpitched;
357  if (0 <= unpitched && unpitched <= 127) {
358  res = true;
359  }
360  }
361 
362  /*
363  for (const auto& instr : instruments) {
364  // MusicXML elements instrument-name, midi-program, instrument-sound, virtual-library, virtual-name
365  // in a shell script use "mscore ... 2>&1 | grep GREP_ME | cut -d' ' -f3-" to extract
366  qDebug("GREP_ME '%s',%d,'%s','%s','%s'",
367  qPrintable(instr.name),
368  instr.midiProgram + 1,
369  qPrintable(instr.sound),
370  qPrintable(instr.virtLib),
371  qPrintable(instr.virtName)
372  );
373  }
374  */
375 
376  return res;
377  }
378 
379 //---------------------------------------------------------
380 // initDrumset
381 //---------------------------------------------------------
382 
383 /**
384  Initialize drumset \a drumset.
385  */
386 
387 // first determine if the part contains a drumset
388 // (this is assummed if any instrument has a valid midi-unpitched element,
389 // which stored in the MusicXMLInstrument pitch field)
390 // then if the part contains a drumset, Drumset drumset is initialized
391 
392 static void initDrumset(Drumset* drumset, const MusicXMLInstruments& instruments)
393  {
394  drumset->clear();
395  MusicXMLInstrumentsIterator ii(instruments);
396  while (ii.hasNext()) {
397  ii.next();
398  // debug: also dump the drumset for this part
399  //qDebug("initDrumset: instrument: %s %s", qPrintable(ii.key()), qPrintable(ii.value().toString()));
400  int unpitched = ii.value().unpitched;
401  if (0 <= unpitched && unpitched <= 127) {
402  drumset->drum(ii.value().unpitched)
403  = DrumInstrument(ii.value().name.toLatin1().constData(),
404  ii.value().notehead, ii.value().line, ii.value().stemDirection);
405  }
406  }
407  }

409 //---------------------------------------------------------
410 // setStaffTypePercussion
411 //---------------------------------------------------------
412 
413 /**
414  Set staff type to percussion
415  */
416 
417 static void setStaffTypePercussion(Part* part, Drumset* drumset)
418  {
419  for (int j = 0; j < part->nstaves(); ++j)
420  if (part->staff(j)->lines(Fraction(0,1)) == 5 && !part->staff(j)->isDrumStaff(Fraction(0,1)))
421  part->staff(j)->setStaffType(Fraction(0,1), *StaffType::preset(StaffTypes::PERC_DEFAULT));
422  // set drumset for instrument
423  part->instrument()->setDrumset(drumset);
424  part->instrument()->channel(0)->setBank(128);
425  }
426 
427 //---------------------------------------------------------
428 // createInstrument
429 //---------------------------------------------------------
430 
431 /**
432  Create an Instrument based on the information in \a mxmlInstr.
433  */
434 
435 static Instrument createInstrument(const MusicXMLInstrument& mxmlInstr, const Interval interval)
436  {
437  Instrument instr;
438 
439  InstrumentTemplate* it = nullptr;
440  if (!mxmlInstr.sound.isEmpty()) {
441  it = Ms::searchTemplateForMusicXmlId(mxmlInstr.sound);
442  }
443 
444  if (!it) {
445  it = Ms::searchTemplateForInstrNameList({mxmlInstr.name});
446  }
447 
448  if (!it) {
449  it = Ms::searchTemplateForMidiProgram(mxmlInstr.midiProgram);
450  }
451 
452  if (it) {
453  // initialize from template with matching MusicXmlId
454  instr = Instrument::fromTemplate(it);
455  // reset transpose, as it is determined later from MusicXML data
456  instr.setTranspose(Interval());
457  }
458  else {
459  // set articulations to default (global articulations)
460  instr.setArticulation(articulation);
461  // set default program
462  instr.channel(0)->setProgram(mxmlInstr.midiProgram >= 0 ? mxmlInstr.midiProgram : 0);
463  }
464 
465  // add / overrule with values read from MusicXML
466  instr.channel(0)->setPan(mxmlInstr.midiPan);
467  instr.channel(0)->setVolume(mxmlInstr.midiVolume);
468  instr.setTrackName(mxmlInstr.name);
469  instr.setTranspose(interval);
470 
471  return instr;
472  }
473 
474 //---------------------------------------------------------
475 // updatePartWithInstrument
476 //---------------------------------------------------------
477 
478 static void updatePartWithInstrument(Part* const part, const MusicXMLInstrument& mxmlInstr, const Interval interval, const bool hasDrumset = false)
479  {
480  Instrument instr = createInstrument(mxmlInstr, interval);
481  if (hasDrumset)
482  instr.channel(0)->setBank(128);
483  part->setInstrument(instr);
484  if (mxmlInstr.midiChannel >= 0)
485  part->setMidiChannel(mxmlInstr.midiChannel, mxmlInstr.midiPort);
486  // note: setMidiProgram() does more than simply setting the MIDI program
487  if (mxmlInstr.midiProgram >= 0)
488  part->setMidiProgram(mxmlInstr.midiProgram);
489  }
490 
491 //---------------------------------------------------------
492 // createInstrumentChange
493 //---------------------------------------------------------
494 
495 /**
496  Create an InstrumentChange based on the information in \a mxmlInstr.
497  */
498 
499 static InstrumentChange* createInstrumentChange(Score* score, const MusicXMLInstrument& mxmlInstr, const Interval interval, const int track)
500  {
501  const Instrument instr = createInstrument(mxmlInstr, interval);
502  InstrumentChange* instrChange = new InstrumentChange(instr, score);
503  instrChange->setTrack(track);
504 
505  // for text use instrument name (if known) else use "Instrument change"
506  const QString text = mxmlInstr.name;
507  instrChange->setXmlText(text.isEmpty() ? "Instrument change" : text);
508  instrChange->setVisible(false);
509 
510  return instrChange;
511  }
512 
513 //---------------------------------------------------------
514 // updatePartWithInstrumentChange
515 //---------------------------------------------------------
516 
517 static void updatePartWithInstrumentChange(Part* const part, const MusicXMLInstrument& mxmlInstr, const Interval interval, Segment* const segment, const int track, const Fraction tick)
518  {
519  const auto ic = createInstrumentChange(part->score(), mxmlInstr, interval, track);
520  segment->add(ic); // note: includes part::setInstrument(instr);
521 
522  // setMidiChannel() depends on setInstrument() already been done
523  if (mxmlInstr.midiChannel >= 0) part->setMidiChannel(mxmlInstr.midiChannel, mxmlInstr.midiPort, tick);
524  }
525 
526 //---------------------------------------------------------
527 // setPartInstruments
528 //---------------------------------------------------------
529 
530 /**
531  Set instruments for Part \a part
532  Note:
533  - MusicXmlInstrList: which instrument plays when
534  - MusicXMLInstruments: instrument details from score-part and part
535  */
536 
537 static void setPartInstruments(MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader,
538  Part* part, const QString& partId,
539  Score* score,
540  const MusicXmlInstrList& instrList,
541  const MusicXmlIntervalList& intervList,
542  const MusicXMLInstruments& instruments)
543  {
544  if (instruments.empty()) {
545  // no instrument details found, create a default instrument
546  //qDebug("no instrument details");
547  updatePartWithInstrument(part, {}, intervList.interval({ 0, 1 }));
548  return;
549  }
550 
551  if (hasDrumset(instruments)) {
552  // do not create multiple instruments for a drum part
553  //qDebug("hasDrumset");
554  MusicXMLInstrument mxmlInstr = instruments.first();
555  updatePartWithInstrument(part, mxmlInstr, {}, true);
556  return;
557  }
558 
559  if (instrList.empty()) {
560  // instrument details found, but no instrument ids found
561  // -> only a single instrument is playing in the part
562  //qDebug("single instrument");
563  MusicXMLInstrument mxmlInstr = instruments.first();
564  updatePartWithInstrument(part, mxmlInstr, intervList.interval({ 0, 1 }));
565  return;
566  }
567 
568  // either a single instrument is playing, or forwards / rests resulted in gaps in the instrument map
569  // (and thus multiple entries)
570  //qDebug("possibly multiple instruments");
571  QString prevInstrId;
572  for (auto it = instrList.cbegin(); it != instrList.cend(); ++it) {
573  Fraction tick = (*it).first;
574  if (it == instrList.cbegin()) {
575  prevInstrId = (*it).second; // first instrument id
576  MusicXMLInstrument mxmlInstr = instruments.value(prevInstrId);
577  updatePartWithInstrument(part, mxmlInstr, intervList.interval(tick));
578  }
579  else {
580  auto instrId = (*it).second;
581  bool mustInsert = instrId != prevInstrId;
582  /*
583  qDebug("tick %s previd %s id %s mustInsert %d",
584  qPrintable(tick.print()),
585  qPrintable(prevInstrId),
586  qPrintable(instrId),
587  mustInsert);
588  */
589  if (mustInsert) {
590  const int staff = score->staffIdx(part);
591  const int track = staff * VOICES;
592  //qDebug("instrument change: tick %s (%d) track %d instr '%s'",
593  // qPrintable(tick.print()), tick.ticks(), track, qPrintable(instrId));
594 
595  Measure* const m = score->tick2measure(tick);
596  Segment* const segment = m->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, tick);
597 
598  if (!segment)
599  logger->logError(QString("segment for instrument change at tick %1 not found")
600  .arg(tick.ticks()), xmlreader);
601  else if (!instruments.contains(instrId))
602  logger->logError(QString("changed instrument '%1' at tick %2 not found in part '%3'")
603  .arg(instrId).arg(tick.ticks()).arg(partId), xmlreader);
604  else {
605  MusicXMLInstrument mxmlInstr = instruments.value(instrId);
606  updatePartWithInstrumentChange(part, mxmlInstr, intervList.interval(tick), segment, track, tick);
607  }
608  }
609  prevInstrId = instrId;
610  }
611  }
612  }
613 
614 //---------------------------------------------------------
615 // text2syms
616 //---------------------------------------------------------
617 
618 /**
619  Convert SMuFL code points to MuseScore <sym>...</sym>
620  */
621 
622 static QString text2syms(const QString& t)
623  {
624  //QTime time;
625  //time.start();
626 
627  // first create a map from symbol (Unicode) text to symId
628  // note that this takes about 1 msec on a Core i5,
629  // caching does not gain much
630 
631  ScoreFont* sf = ScoreFont::fallbackFont();
632  QMap<QString, SymId> map;
633  int maxStringSize = 0; // maximum string size found
634 
635  for (int i = int(SymId::noSym); i < int(SymId::lastSym); ++i) {
636  SymId id((SymId(i)));
637  QString string(sf->toString(id));
638  // insert all syms except space to prevent matching all regular spaces
639  if (id != SymId::space)
640  map.insert(string, id);
641  if (string.size() > maxStringSize)
642  maxStringSize = string.size();
643  }
644  //qDebug("text2syms map count %d maxsz %d filling time elapsed: %d ms",
645  // map.size(), maxStringSize, time.elapsed());
646 
647  // then look for matches
648  QString in = t;
649  QString res;
650 
651  while (in != "") {
652  // try to find the largest match possible
653  int maxMatch = qMin(in.size(), maxStringSize);
654  QString sym;
655  while (maxMatch > 0) {
656  QString toBeMatched = in.left(maxMatch);
657  if (map.contains(toBeMatched)) {
658  sym = Sym::id2name(map.value(toBeMatched));
659  break;
660  }
661  maxMatch--;
662  }
663  if (maxMatch > 0) {
664  // found a match, add sym to res and remove match from string in
665  res += "<sym>";
666  res += sym;
667  res += "</sym>";
668  in.remove(0, maxMatch);
669  }
670  else {
671  // not found, move one char from res to in
672  res += in.leftRef(1);
673  in.remove(0, 1);
674  }
675  }
676 
677  //qDebug("text2syms total time elapsed: %d ms, res '%s'", time.elapsed(), qPrintable(res));
678  return res;
679  }
680 
681 //---------------------------------------------------------
682 // decodeEntities
683 //---------------------------------------------------------
684 
685 /**
686  Decode &#...; in string \a src into UNICODE (utf8) character.
687  */
688 
689 static QString decodeEntities( const QString& src )
690  {
691  QString ret(src);
692  QRegExp re("&#([0-9]+);");
693  re.setMinimal(true);
694 
695  int pos = 0;
696  while ( (pos = re.indexIn(src, pos)) != -1 ) {
697  ret = ret.replace(re.cap(0), QChar(re.cap(1).toInt(0,10)));
698  pos += re.matchedLength();
699  }
700  return ret;
701  }
702 
703 //---------------------------------------------------------
704 // nextPartOfFormattedString
705 //---------------------------------------------------------
706 
707 // TODO: probably should be shared between pass 1 and 2
708 
709 /**
710  Read the next part of a MusicXML formatted string and convert to MuseScore internal encoding.
711  */
712 
713 static QString nextPartOfFormattedString(QXmlStreamReader& e)
714  {
715  //QString lang = e.attribute(QString("xml:lang"), "it");
716  QString fontWeight = e.attributes().value("font-weight").toString();
717  QString fontSize = e.attributes().value("font-size").toString();
718  QString fontStyle = e.attributes().value("font-style").toString();
719  QString underline = e.attributes().value("underline").toString();
720  QString fontFamily = e.attributes().value("font-family").toString();
721  // TODO: color, enclosure, yoffset in only part of the text, ...
722 
723  QString txt = e.readElementText();
724  // replace HTML entities
725  txt = decodeEntities(txt);
726  QString syms = text2syms(txt);
727 
728  QString importedtext;
729 
730  if (!fontSize.isEmpty()) {
731  bool ok = true;
732  float size = fontSize.toFloat(&ok);
733  if (ok)
734  importedtext += QString("<font size=\"%1\"/>").arg(size);
735  }
736 
737  bool needUseDefaultFont = preferences.getBool(PREF_MIGRATION_APPLY_EDWIN_FOR_XML_FILES);
738 
739  if (!fontFamily.isEmpty() && txt == syms && !needUseDefaultFont) {
740  // add font family only if no <sym> replacement made
741  importedtext += QString("<font face=\"%1\"/>").arg(fontFamily);
742  }
743  if (fontWeight == "bold")
744  importedtext += "<b>";
745  if (fontStyle == "italic")
746  importedtext += "<i>";
747  if (!underline.isEmpty()) {
748  bool ok = true;
749  int lines = underline.toInt(&ok);
750  if (ok && (lines > 0)) // 1,2, or 3 underlines are imported as single underline
751  importedtext += "<u>";
752  else
753  underline = "";
754  }
755  if (txt == syms) {
756  txt.replace(QString("\r"), QString("")); // convert Windows line break \r\n -> \n
757  importedtext += txt.toHtmlEscaped();
758  }
759  else {
760  // <sym> replacement made, should be no need for line break or other conversions
761  importedtext += syms;
762  }
763  if (underline != "")
764  importedtext += "</u>";
765  if (fontStyle == "italic")
766  importedtext += "</i>";
767  if (fontWeight == "bold")
768  importedtext += "</b>";
769  //qDebug("importedtext '%s'", qPrintable(importedtext));
770  return importedtext;
771  }
772 
773 //---------------------------------------------------------
774 // addLyric
775 //---------------------------------------------------------
776 
777 /**
778  Add a single lyric to the score or delete it (if number too high)
779  */
780 
781 static void addLyric(MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader,
782  ChordRest* cr, Lyrics* l, int lyricNo, MusicXmlLyricsExtend& extendedLyrics)
783  {
784  if (lyricNo > MAX_LYRICS) {
785  logger->logError(QString("too much lyrics (>%1)")
786  .arg(MAX_LYRICS), xmlreader);
787  delete l;
788  }
789  else {
790  l->setNo(lyricNo);
791  cr->add(l);
792  extendedLyrics.setExtend(lyricNo, cr->track(), cr->tick());
793  }
794  }
795 
796 //---------------------------------------------------------
797 // addLyrics
798 //---------------------------------------------------------
799 
800 /**
801  Add a notes lyrics to the score
802  */
803 
804 static void addLyrics(MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader,
805  ChordRest* cr,
806  const QMap<int, Lyrics*>& numbrdLyrics,
807  const QSet<Lyrics*>& extLyrics,
808  MusicXmlLyricsExtend& extendedLyrics)
809  {
810  for (const auto lyricNo : numbrdLyrics.keys()) {
811  const auto lyric = numbrdLyrics.value(lyricNo);
812  addLyric(logger, xmlreader, cr, lyric, lyricNo, extendedLyrics);
813  if (extLyrics.contains(lyric))
814  extendedLyrics.addLyric(lyric);
815  }
816  }

818 //---------------------------------------------------------
819 // addElemOffset
820 //---------------------------------------------------------
821 
822 static void addElemOffset(Element* el, int track, const QString& placement, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
823  {
824  /*
825  qDebug("addElem el %p track %d placement %s tick %d",
826  el, track, qPrintable(placement), tick);
827  */
828 
829 #if 0 // ws: use placement for symbols
830  // move to correct position
831  // TODO: handle rx, ry
832  if (el->isSymbol()) {
833  qreal y = 0;
834  // calc y offset assuming five line staff and default style
835  // note that required y offset is element type dependent
836  const qreal stafflines = 5; // assume five line staff, but works OK-ish for other sizes too
837  qreal offsAbove = 0;
838  qreal offsBelow = 0;
839  offsAbove = -2;
840  offsBelow = 4 + (stafflines - 1);
841  if (placement == "above")
842  y += offsAbove;
843  if (placement == "below")
844  y += offsBelow;
845  //qDebug(" y = %g", y);
846  y *= el->score()->spatium();
847  el->setUserOff(QPoint(0, y));
848  }
849  else {
850  el->setPlacement(placement == "above" ? Placement::ABOVE : Placement::BELOW);
851  }
852 #endif
853  el->setPlacement(placement == "above" ? Placement::ABOVE : Placement::BELOW);
854  el->setPropertyFlags(Pid::PLACEMENT, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
855 
856  el->setTrack(el->isTempoText() ? 0 : track); // TempoText must be in track 0
857  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, tick);
858  s->add(el);
859  }

861 //---------------------------------------------------------
862 // calculateTupletDuration
863 //---------------------------------------------------------
864 
865 /**
866  Calculate the duration of all notes in the tuplet combined
867  */
868 
869 static Fraction calculateTupletDuration(const Tuplet* const t)
870  {
871  Fraction res;
872 
873  foreach (DurationElement* de, t->elements()) {
874  if (de->type() == ElementType::CHORD || de->type() == ElementType::REST) {
875  const auto cr = static_cast<ChordRest*>(de);
876  const auto fraction = cr->ticks(); // TODO : take care of nested tuplets
877  if (fraction.isValid()) {
878  res += fraction;
879  }
880  }
881  }
882  res /= t->ratio();
883 
884  return res;
885  }
886 
887 //---------------------------------------------------------
888 // determineTupletBaseLen
889 //---------------------------------------------------------
890 
891 /**
892  Determine tuplet baseLen as determined by the tuplet ratio
893  and duration.
894  */
895 
896 static TDuration determineTupletBaseLen(const Tuplet* const t)
897  {
898  Fraction tupletFraction;
899  Fraction tupletFullDuration;
900  determineTupletFractionAndFullDuration(calculateTupletDuration(t), tupletFraction, tupletFullDuration);
901 
902  auto baseLen = tupletFullDuration * Fraction(1, t->ratio().denominator());
903  /*
904  qDebug("tupletFraction %s tupletFullDuration %s ratio %s baseLen %s",
905  qPrintable(tupletFraction.toString()),
906  qPrintable(tupletFullDuration.toString()),
907  qPrintable(t->ratio().toString()),
908  qPrintable(baseLen.toString())
909  );
910  */
911 
912  return TDuration(baseLen);
913  }
914 
915 //---------------------------------------------------------
916 // handleTupletStart
917 //---------------------------------------------------------
918 
919 static void handleTupletStart(const ChordRest* const cr, Tuplet*& tuplet,
920  const int actualNotes, const int normalNotes,
921  const MusicXmlTupletDesc& tupletDesc)
922  {
923  tuplet = new Tuplet(cr->score());
924  tuplet->setTrack(cr->track());
925  tuplet->setRatio(Fraction(actualNotes, normalNotes));
926  tuplet->setTick(cr->tick());
927  tuplet->setBracketType(tupletDesc.bracket);
928  tuplet->setNumberType(tupletDesc.shownumber);
929  // TODO type, placement, bracket
930  tuplet->setParent(cr->measure());
931  }
932 
933 //---------------------------------------------------------
934 // handleTupletStop
935 //---------------------------------------------------------
936 
937 static void handleTupletStop(Tuplet*& tuplet, const int normalNotes)
938  {
939  // allow handleTupletStop to be called w/o error of no tuplet active
940  if (!tuplet) return;
941 
942  // set baselen
943  TDuration td = determineTupletBaseLen(tuplet);
944  tuplet->setBaseLen(td);
945  Fraction f(normalNotes, td.fraction().denominator());
946  f.reduce();
947  tuplet->setTicks(f);
948  // TODO determine usefulness of following check
949  int totalDuration = 0;
950  foreach (DurationElement* de, tuplet->elements()) {
951  if (de->type() == ElementType::CHORD || de->type() == ElementType::REST) {
952  totalDuration+=de->globalTicks().ticks();
953  }
954  }
955  if (!(totalDuration && normalNotes)) {
956  qDebug("MusicXML::import: tuplet stop but bad duration"); // TODO
957  }
958  tuplet = 0;
959  }

961 //---------------------------------------------------------
962 // setElementPropertyFlags
963 //---------------------------------------------------------
964 
965 static void setElementPropertyFlags(ScoreElement* element, const Pid propertyId,
966  const QString value1, const QString value2 = QString())
967  {
968  if (value1.isEmpty()) // Set as an implicit value
969  element->setPropertyFlags(propertyId, PropertyFlags::STYLED);
970  else if (!value1.isNull() || !value2.isNull()) // Set as an explicit value
971  element->setPropertyFlags(propertyId, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
972  }

974 //---------------------------------------------------------
975 // addArticulationToChord
976 //---------------------------------------------------------
977 
978 static void addArticulationToChord(const Notation& notation, ChordRest* cr)
979  {
980  const SymId articSym = notation.symId();
981  const QString dir = notation.attribute("type");
982  const QString place = notation.attribute("placement");
983  Articulation* na = new Articulation(articSym, cr->score());
984 
985  if (!dir.isNull()) // Only for case where XML attribute is present (isEmpty wouldn't work)
986  na->setUp(dir.isEmpty() || dir == "up");
987  setElementPropertyFlags(na, Pid::DIRECTION, dir);
988 
989  if (place == "above" || dir.isEmpty() || dir == "up")
990  na->setAnchor(ArticulationAnchor::TOP_STAFF);
991  else if (place == "below" || dir == "down")
992  na->setAnchor(ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_STAFF);
993  setElementPropertyFlags(na, Pid::DIRECTION, dir, place);
994 
995  cr->add(na);
996  }

998 //---------------------------------------------------------
999 // addFermataToChord
1000 //---------------------------------------------------------
1001 
1002 /**
1003  Add a MusicXML fermata.
1004  Note: MusicXML common.mod: "The fermata type is upright if not specified."
1005  */
1006 
1007 static void addFermataToChord(const Notation& notation, ChordRest* cr)
1008  {
1009  const SymId articSym = notation.symId();
1010  const QString direction = notation.attribute("type");
1011  Fermata* na = new Fermata(articSym, cr->score());
1012  na->setTrack(cr->track());
1013  if (!direction.isNull()) // Only for case where XML attribute is present (isEmpty wouldn't work)
1014  na->setPlacement(direction == "inverted" ? Placement::BELOW : Placement::ABOVE);
1015  setElementPropertyFlags(na, Pid::PLACEMENT, direction);
1016  if (cr->segment() == nullptr && cr->isGrace())
1017  cr->el().push_back(na); // store for later move to segment
1018  else
1019  cr->segment()->add(na);
1020  }

1022 //---------------------------------------------------------
1023 // addMordentToChord
1024 //---------------------------------------------------------
1025 
1026 /**
1027  Add Mordent to Chord.
1028  */
1029 
1030 static void addMordentToChord(const Notation& notation, ChordRest* cr)
1031  {
1032  const QString name = notation.name();
1033  const QString attrLong = notation.attribute("long");
1034  const QString attrAppr = notation.attribute("approach");
1035  const QString attrDep = notation.attribute("departure");
1036  SymId articSym = SymId::noSym; // legal but impossible ArticulationType value here indicating "not found"
1037  if (name == "inverted-mordent") {
1038  if ((attrLong == "" || attrLong == "no") && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "")
1039  articSym = SymId::ornamentShortTrill;
1040  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "")
1041  articSym = SymId::ornamentTremblement;
1042  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "below" && attrDep == "")
1043  articSym = SymId::ornamentUpPrall;
1044  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "above" && attrDep == "")
1045  articSym = SymId::ornamentPrecompMordentUpperPrefix;
1046  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "below")
1047  articSym = SymId::ornamentPrallDown;
1048  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "above")
1049  articSym = SymId::ornamentPrallUp;
1050  }
1051  else if (name == "mordent") {
1052  if ((attrLong == "" || attrLong == "no") && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "")
1053  articSym = SymId::ornamentMordent;
1054  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "" && attrDep == "")
1055  articSym = SymId::ornamentPrallMordent;
1056  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "below" && attrDep == "")
1057  articSym = SymId::ornamentUpMordent;
1058  else if (attrLong == "yes" && attrAppr == "above" && attrDep == "")
1059  articSym = SymId::ornamentDownMordent;
1060  }
1061  if (articSym != SymId::noSym) {
1062  Articulation* na = new Articulation(cr->score());
1063  na->setSymId(articSym);
1064  cr->add(na);
1065  }
1066  else
1067  qDebug("unknown ornament: name '%s' long '%s' approach '%s' departure '%s'",
1068  qPrintable(name), qPrintable(attrLong), qPrintable(attrAppr), qPrintable(attrDep)); // TODO
1069  }
1070 
1071 //---------------------------------------------------------
1072 // convertArticulationToSymId
1073 //---------------------------------------------------------
1074 
1075 /**
1076  Convert a MusicXML articulation to a chord as a "simple" MuseScore articulation.
1077  These are the articulations that can be
1078  - represented by an enum class SymId
1079  - added to a ChordRest
1080  Return true (articulation recognized and converted)
1081  or false (articulation not recognized).
1082  Note simple implementation: MusicXML syntax is not strictly
1083  checked, the articulations parent element does not matter.
1084  */
1085 
1086 static bool convertArticulationToSymId(const QString& mxmlName, SymId& id)
1087  {
1088  QMap<QString, SymId> map; // map MusicXML articulation name to MuseScore symbol
1089  map["accent"] = SymId::articAccentAbove;
1090  map["staccatissimo"] = SymId::articStaccatissimoAbove;
1091  map["staccato"] = SymId::articStaccatoAbove;
1092  map["tenuto"] = SymId::articTenutoAbove;
1093  map["strong-accent"] = SymId::articMarcatoAbove;
1094  map["delayed-turn"] = SymId::ornamentTurn;
1095  map["turn"] = SymId::ornamentTurn;
1096  map["inverted-turn"] = SymId::ornamentTurnInverted;
1097  map["stopped"] = SymId::brassMuteClosed;
1098  map["up-bow"] = SymId::stringsUpBow;
1099  map["down-bow"] = SymId::stringsDownBow;
1100  map["detached-legato"] = SymId::articTenutoStaccatoAbove;
1101  map["spiccato"] = SymId::articStaccatissimoAbove;
1102  map["snap-pizzicato"] = SymId::pluckedSnapPizzicatoAbove;
1103  map["schleifer"] = SymId::ornamentPrecompSlide;
1104  map["open-string"] = SymId::brassMuteOpen;
1105  map["thumb-position"] = SymId::stringsThumbPosition;
1106  map["soft-accent"] = SymId::articSoftAccentAbove;
1107  map["stress"] = SymId::articStressAbove;
1108  map["unstress"] = SymId::articUnstressAbove;
1109 
1110  if (map.contains(mxmlName)) {
1111  id = map.value(mxmlName);
1112  return true;
1113  }
1114  else {
1115  id = SymId::noSym;
1116  return false;
1117  }
1118  }
1119 
1120 //---------------------------------------------------------
1121 // convertNotehead
1122 //---------------------------------------------------------
1123 
1124 /**
1125  Convert a MusicXML notehead name to a MuseScore headgroup.
1126  */
1127 
1128 static NoteHead::Group convertNotehead(QString mxmlName)
1129  {
1130  QMap<QString, int> map; // map MusicXML notehead name to a MuseScore headgroup
1131  map["slash"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_SLASH);
1132  map["triangle"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_TRIANGLE_UP);
1133  map["diamond"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_DIAMOND);
1134  map["cross"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_PLUS);
1135  map["x"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_CROSS);
1136  map["circle-x"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_XCIRCLE);
1137  map["inverted triangle"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_TRIANGLE_DOWN);
1138  map["slashed"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_SLASHED1);
1139  map["back slashed"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_SLASHED2);
1140  map["normal"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_NORMAL);
1141  map["do"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_DO);
1142  map["re"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_RE);
1143  map["mi"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_MI);
1144  map["fa"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_FA);
1145  map["fa up"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_FA);
1146  map["so"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_SOL);
1147  map["la"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_LA);
1148  map["ti"] = int(NoteHead::Group::HEAD_TI);
1149 
1150  if (map.contains(mxmlName))
1151  return NoteHead::Group(map.value(mxmlName));
1152  else
1153  qDebug("unknown notehead %s", qPrintable(mxmlName)); // TODO
1154  // default: return 0
1155  return NoteHead::Group::HEAD_NORMAL;
1156  }

1158 //---------------------------------------------------------
1159 // addTextToNote
1160 //---------------------------------------------------------
1161 
1162 /**
1163  Add Text to Note.
1164  */
1165 
1166 static void addTextToNote(int l, int c, QString txt, QString placement, QString fontWeight,
1167  qreal fontSize, QString fontStyle, QString fontFamily, Tid subType, Score* score, Note* note)
1168  {
1169  if (note) {
1170  if (!txt.isEmpty()) {
1171  TextBase* t = new Fingering(score, subType);
1172  t->setPlainText(txt);
1173 
1174  bool needUseDefaultFont = preferences.getBool(PREF_MIGRATION_APPLY_EDWIN_FOR_XML_FILES);
1175 
1176  if (!fontFamily.isEmpty() && !needUseDefaultFont) {
1177  t->setFamily(fontFamily);
1178  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::FONT_FACE, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1179  }
1180  if (std::isnormal(fontSize) && fontSize > 0.0) {
1181  t->setSize(fontSize);
1182  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::FONT_SIZE, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1183  }
1184  if (!fontWeight.isEmpty()) {
1185  t->setBold(fontWeight == "bold");
1186  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::FONT_STYLE, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1187  }
1188  if (!fontStyle.isEmpty()) {
1189  t->setItalic(fontStyle == "italic");
1190  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::FONT_STYLE, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1191  }
1192  if (!placement.isEmpty()) {
1193  t->setPlacement(placement == "below" ? Placement::BELOW : Placement::ABOVE);
1194  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::PLACEMENT, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1195  }
1196  note->add(t);
1197  }
1198  }
1199  else
1200  qDebug("%s", qPrintable(QString("Error at line %1 col %2: no note for text").arg(l).arg(c))); // TODO
1201  }

1207 /**
1208  Helper for direction().
1209  SLine placement is modified by changing the first segments user offset
1210  As the SLine has just been created, it does not have any segment yet

1212 
1213 static void setSLinePlacement(SLine* sli, const QString placement)

1224  if (placement == "above") {
1225  const qreal stafflines = 5; // assume five line staff, but works OK-ish for other sizes too
1226  qreal offsAbove = -6 - (stafflines - 1);

1237  }
1238  else {

1240  }
1241 #endif

1244  }

1248 //---------------------------------------------------------
1249 
1250 // note that in case of overlapping spanners, handleSpannerStart is called for every spanner
1251 // as spanners QMap allows only one value per key, this does not hurt at all
1252 
1253 static void handleSpannerStart(SLine* new_sp, int track, QString& placement, const Fraction& tick, MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners)
1254  {
1255  //qDebug("handleSpannerStart(sp %p, track %d, tick %s (%d))", new_sp, track, qPrintable(tick.print()), tick.ticks());
1256  new_sp->setTrack(track);
1257  setSLinePlacement(new_sp, placement);
1258  spanners[new_sp] = QPair<int, int>(tick.ticks(), -1);
1259  }

1263 //---------------------------------------------------------
1264 
1265 static void handleSpannerStop(SLine* cur_sp, int track2, const Fraction& tick, MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners)

1268  if (!cur_sp)
1269  return;

1272  spanners[cur_sp].second = tick.ticks();

1279 //---------------------------------------------------------
1280 // MusicXMLParserPass2
1281 //---------------------------------------------------------
1282 
1283 MusicXMLParserPass2::MusicXMLParserPass2(Score* score, MusicXMLParserPass1& pass1, MxmlLogger* logger)
1284  : _divs(0), _score(score), _pass1(pass1), _logger(logger)
1285  {
1286  // nothing
1287  }

1289 //---------------------------------------------------------
1290 // setChordRestDuration
1291 //---------------------------------------------------------
1292 
1293 /**
1294  * Set \a cr duration
1295  */
1296 
1297 static void setChordRestDuration(ChordRest* cr, TDuration duration, const Fraction dura)
1298  {
1299  if (duration.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE) {
1300  cr->setDurationType(duration);
1301  cr->setTicks(dura);
1302  }
1303  else {
1304  cr->setDurationType(duration);
1305  cr->setTicks(cr->durationType().fraction());
1306  }
1307  }
1308 
1309 //---------------------------------------------------------
1310 // addRest
1311 //---------------------------------------------------------
1312 
1313 /**
1314  * Add a rest to the score
1315  * TODO: beam handling
1316  * TODO: display step handling
1317  * TODO: visible handling
1318  * TODO: whole measure rest handling
1319  */
1320 
1321 static Rest* addRest(Score* score, Measure* m,
1322  const Fraction& tick, const int track, const int move,
1323  const TDuration duration, const Fraction dura)
1324  {
1325  Segment* s = m->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, tick);
1326  // Sibelius might export two rests at the same place, ignore the 2nd one
1327  // <?DoletSibelius Two NoteRests in same voice at same position may be an error?>
1328  // Same issue may result from trying to import incomplete tuplets
1329  if (s->element(track)) {
1330  qDebug("cannot add rest at tick %s (%d) track %d: element already present", qPrintable(tick.print()), tick.ticks(), track); // TODO
1331  return nullptr;
1332  }
1333 
1334  Rest* cr = new Rest(score);
1335  setChordRestDuration(cr, duration, dura);
1336  cr->setTrack(track);
1337  cr->setStaffMove(move);
1338  s->add(cr);
1339  return cr;
1340  }
1341 
1342 //---------------------------------------------------------
1343 // resetTuplets
1344 //---------------------------------------------------------
1345 
1346 static void resetTuplets(Tuplets& tuplets)
1347  {
1348  for (auto& pair : tuplets) {
1349  auto tuplet = pair.second;
1350  if (tuplet) {
1351  const auto actualDuration = tuplet->elementsDuration() / tuplet->ratio();
1352  const auto missingDuration = missingTupletDuration(actualDuration);
1353  qDebug("tuplet %p not stopped at end of measure, tick %s duration %s missing %s",
1354  tuplet,
1355  qPrintable(tuplet->tick().print()),
1356  qPrintable(actualDuration.print()), qPrintable(missingDuration.print()));
1357  if (actualDuration > Fraction(0, 1) && missingDuration > Fraction(0, 1)) {
1358  qDebug("add missing %s to previous tuplet", qPrintable(missingDuration.print()));
1359  const auto& firstElement = tuplet->elements().at(0);
1360  // appended the rest to the current end of the tuplet (firstElement->tick() + actualDuration)
1361  const auto extraRest = addRest(firstElement->score(), firstElement->measure(), firstElement->tick() + actualDuration, firstElement->track(), 0,
1362  TDuration { missingDuration* tuplet->ratio() }, missingDuration);
1363  if (extraRest) {
1364  extraRest->setTuplet(tuplet);
1365  tuplet->add(extraRest);
1366  }
1367  }
1368  const auto normalNotes = tuplet->ratio().denominator();
1369  handleTupletStop(tuplet, normalNotes);
1370  }
1371  }
1372  }
1373 
1374 //---------------------------------------------------------
1375 // initPartState
1376 //---------------------------------------------------------
1377 
1378 /**
1379  Initialize members as required for reading the MusicXML part element.
1380  TODO: factor out part reading into a separate class
1381  TODO: preferably use automatically initialized variables
1382  Note that Qt automatically initializes new elements in QVector (tuplets).
1383  */
1384 
1385 void MusicXMLParserPass2::initPartState(const QString& partId)
1386  {
1387  Q_UNUSED(partId);
1388  _timeSigDura = Fraction(0, 0); // invalid
1389  _tie = 0;
1390  _lastVolta = 0;
1391  _hasDrumset = false;
1392  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL; ++i)
1393  _slurs[i] = SlurDesc();
1394  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL; ++i)
1395  _trills[i] = 0;
1396  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL; ++i)
1397  _glissandi[i][0] = _glissandi[i][1] = 0;
1398  _pedalContinue = 0;
1399  _harmony = 0;
1400  _tremStart = 0;
1401  _figBass = 0;
1402  _multiMeasureRestCount = -1;
1403  _measureStyleSlash = MusicXmlSlash::NONE;

1405  }

1407 //---------------------------------------------------------
1408 // findIncompleteSpannersInStack
1409 //---------------------------------------------------------
1410 
1411 static void findIncompleteSpannersInStack(const QString& spannerType, SpannerStack& stack, SpannerSet& res)
1412  {
1413  for (auto& desc : stack) {
1414  if (desc._sp) {
1415  qDebug("%s not terminated at end of part", qPrintable(spannerType));
1416  res.insert(desc._sp);
1417  desc = {};
1418  }
1419  }
1420  }

1422 //---------------------------------------------------------
1423 // findIncompleteSpannersAtPartEnd
1424 //---------------------------------------------------------
1425 
1426 SpannerSet MusicXMLParserPass2::findIncompleteSpannersAtPartEnd()
1427  {
1428  SpannerSet res;
1429  findIncompleteSpannersInStack("bracket", _brackets, res);
1430  findIncompleteSpannersInStack("wedge", _hairpins, res);
1431  findIncompleteSpannersInStack("octave-shift", _ottavas, res);
1432  if (_pedal._sp) {
1433  qDebug("pedal not terminated at end of part");
1434  res.insert(_pedal._sp);
1435  _pedal = {};
1436  }
1437  return res;
1438  }

1440 //---------------------------------------------------------
1441 // multi-measure rest state handling
1442 //---------------------------------------------------------
1443 
1444 // If any multi-measure rest is found, the "create multi-measure rest" style setting is enabled.
1445 // First measure in a multi-measure rest gets setBreakMultiMeasureRest(true), then count down
1446 // the remaining number of measures.
1447 // The first measure after a multi-measure rest gets setBreakMultiMeasureRest(true).
1448 // For all other measures breakMultiMeasureRest is unchanged (stays default (false)).
1449 
1450 //---------------------------------------------------------
1451 // setMultiMeasureRestCount
1452 //---------------------------------------------------------
1453 
1454 /**
1455  Set the multi-measure rest counter.
1456  */
1457 
1458 
1459 void MusicXMLParserPass2::setMultiMeasureRestCount(int count)
1460  {
1461  _multiMeasureRestCount = count;
1462  }
1463 
1464 //---------------------------------------------------------
1465 // getAndDecMultiMeasureRestCount
1466 //---------------------------------------------------------
1467 
1468 /**
1469  Return current multi-measure rest counter.
1470  Decrement counter if possible (not beyond -1).
1471  */
1472 
1473 int MusicXMLParserPass2::getAndDecMultiMeasureRestCount()
1474  {
1475  int res = _multiMeasureRestCount;
1476  if (_multiMeasureRestCount >= 0)
1477  _multiMeasureRestCount--;
1478  return res;
1479  }

1526 //---------------------------------------------------------
1527 // parse
1528 //---------------------------------------------------------
1529 
1530 /**
1531  Start the parsing process, after verifying the top-level node is score-partwise
1532  */
1533 
1534 Score::FileError MusicXMLParserPass2::parse()
1535  {
1536  bool found = false;
1537  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
1538  if (_e.name() == "score-partwise") {
1539  found = true;
1540  scorePartwise();
1541  }
1542  else {
1543  _logger->logError("this is not a MusicXML score-partwise file", &_e);
1544  _e.skipCurrentElement();
1545  return Score::FileError::FILE_BAD_FORMAT;
1546  }
1547  }
1548 
1549  if (!found) {
1550  _logger->logError("this is not a MusicXML score-partwise file", &_e);
1551  return Score::FileError::FILE_BAD_FORMAT;
1552  }
1553 
1554  return Score::FileError::FILE_NO_ERROR;
1555  }
1556 
1557 //---------------------------------------------------------
1558 // scorePartwise
1559 //---------------------------------------------------------
1560 
1561 /**
1562  Parse the MusicXML top-level (XPath /score-partwise) node.
1563  */
1564 
1565 void MusicXMLParserPass2::scorePartwise()
1566  {
1567  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "score-partwise");
1568 
1569  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
1570  if (_e.name() == "part") {
1571  part();
1572  }
1573  else if (_e.name() == "part-list")
1574  partList();
1575  else
1576  skipLogCurrElem();
1577  }
1578  // set last measure barline to normal or MuseScore will generate light-heavy EndBarline
1579  // TODO, handle other tracks?
1580  if (_score->lastMeasure()->endBarLineType() == BarLineType::NORMAL)
1581  _score->lastMeasure()->setEndBarLineType(BarLineType::NORMAL, 0);
1582  }
1583 
1584 //---------------------------------------------------------
1585 // partList
1586 //---------------------------------------------------------
1587 
1588 /**
1589  Parse the /score-partwise/part-list node.
1590  */
1591 
1592 void MusicXMLParserPass2::partList()
1593  {
1594  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "part-list");
1595 
1596  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
1597  if (_e.name() == "score-part")
1598  scorePart();
1599  else
1600  skipLogCurrElem();
1601  }
1602  }
1603 
1604 //---------------------------------------------------------
1605 // scorePart
1606 //---------------------------------------------------------
1607 
1608 // Parse the /score-partwise/part-list/score-part node.
1609 // TODO: nothing required for pass 2 ?
1610 
1611 void MusicXMLParserPass2::scorePart()
1612  {
1613  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "score-part");
1614 
1615  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
1616  if (_e.name() == "midi-instrument")
1617  _e.skipCurrentElement(); // skip but don't log
1618  else if (_e.name() == "score-instrument")
1619  _e.skipCurrentElement(); // skip but don't log
1620  else if (_e.name() == "part-name")
1621  _e.skipCurrentElement(); // skip but don't log
1622  else
1623  skipLogCurrElem();
1624  }
1625  }
1626 
1627 //---------------------------------------------------------
1628 // part
1629 //---------------------------------------------------------
1630 
1631 /**
1632  Parse the /score-partwise/part node.
1633  */
1634 
1635 void MusicXMLParserPass2::part()
1636  {
1637  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "part");
1638  const QString id = _e.attributes().value("id").toString();
1639 
1640  if (!_pass1.hasPart(id)) {
1641  _logger->logError(QString("MusicXMLParserPass2::part cannot find part '%1'").arg(id), &_e);
1642  skipLogCurrElem();
1643  }
1644 
1645  initPartState(id);
1646 
1647  const auto& instruments = _pass1.getInstruments(id);
1648  _hasDrumset = hasDrumset(instruments);
1649 
1650  // set the parts first instrument
1651  setPartInstruments(_logger, &_e, _pass1.getPart(id), id, _score, _pass1.getInstrList(id), _pass1.getIntervals(id), instruments);
1652 
1653  // set the part name
1654  auto mxmlPart = _pass1.getMusicXmlPart(id);
1655  _pass1.getPart(id)->setPartName(mxmlPart.getName());
1656  if (mxmlPart.getPrintName())
1657  _pass1.getPart(id)->setLongName(mxmlPart.getName());
1658  if (mxmlPart.getPrintAbbr())
1659  _pass1.getPart(id)->setPlainShortName(mxmlPart.getAbbr());
1660  // try to prevent an empty track name
1661  if (_pass1.getPart(id)->partName() == "") {
1662  QString instrId = _pass1.getInstrList(id).instrument(Fraction(0, 1));
1663  _pass1.getPart(id)->setPartName(instruments[instrId].name);
1664  }
1665 
1666 #ifdef DEBUG_VOICE_MAPPER
1667  VoiceList voicelist = _pass1.getVoiceList(id);
1668  // debug: print voice mapper contents
1669  qDebug("voiceMapperStats: part '%s'", qPrintable(id));
1670  for (QMap<QString, Ms::VoiceDesc>::const_iterator i = voicelist.constBegin(); i != voicelist.constEnd(); ++i) {
1671  qDebug("voiceMapperStats: voice %s staff data %s",
1672  qPrintable(i.key()), qPrintable(i.value().toString()));
1673  }
1674 #endif
1675 
1676  // read the measures
1677  int nr = 0; // current measure sequence number
1678  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
1679  if (_e.name() == "measure") {
1680  Fraction t = _pass1.getMeasureStart(nr);
1681  if (t.isValid())
1682  measure(id, t);
1683  else {
1684  _logger->logError(QString("no valid start time for measure %1").arg(nr + 1), &_e);
1685  _e.skipCurrentElement();
1686  }
1687  ++nr;
1688  }
1689  else
1690  skipLogCurrElem();
1691  }
1692 
1693  // stop all remaining extends for this part
1694  Measure* lm = _pass1.getPart(id)->score()->lastMeasure();
1695  if (lm) {
1696  int strack = _pass1.trackForPart(id);
1697  int etrack = strack + _pass1.getPart(id)->nstaves() * VOICES;
1698  Fraction lastTick = lm->endTick();
1699  for (int trk = strack; trk < etrack; trk++)
1700  _extendedLyrics.setExtend(-1, trk, lastTick);
1701  }
1702 
1703  const auto incompleteSpanners = findIncompleteSpannersAtPartEnd();
1704  //qDebug("spanner list:");
1705  auto i = _spanners.constBegin();
1706  while (i != _spanners.constEnd()) {
1707  auto sp = i.key();
1708  Fraction tick1 = Fraction::fromTicks(i.value().first);
1709  Fraction tick2 = Fraction::fromTicks(i.value().second);
1710  //qDebug("spanner %p tp %d tick1 %s tick2 %s track1 %d track2 %d",
1711  // sp, sp->type(), qPrintable(tick1.print()), qPrintable(tick2.print()), sp->track(), sp->track2());
1712  if (incompleteSpanners.find(sp) == incompleteSpanners.end()) {
1713  // complete spanner -> add to score
1714  sp->setTick(tick1);
1715  sp->setTick2(tick2);
1716  sp->score()->addElement(sp);
1717  }
1718  else {
1719  // incomplete spanner -> cleanup
1720  delete sp;
1721  }
1722  ++i;
1723  }
1724  _spanners.clear();
1725 
1726  if (_hasDrumset) {
1727  Drumset* drumset = new Drumset;
1728  const auto& instrumentsAfterPass2 = _pass1.getInstruments(id);
1729  initDrumset(drumset, instrumentsAfterPass2);
1730  // set staff type to percussion if incorrectly imported as pitched staff
1731  // Note: part has been read, staff type already set based on clef type and staff-details
1732  // but may be incorrect for a percussion staff that does not use a percussion clef
1733  setStaffTypePercussion(_pass1.getPart(id), drumset);
1734  }
1735  }
1736 
1737 //---------------------------------------------------------
1738 // findMeasure
1739 //---------------------------------------------------------
1740 
1741 /**
1742  In Score \a score find the measure starting at \a tick.
1743  */
1744 
1745 static Measure* findMeasure(Score* score, const Fraction& tick)
1746  {
1747  for (Measure* m = score->firstMeasure(); m; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
1748  if (m->tick() == tick)
1749  return m;
1750  }
1751  return 0;
1752  }
1753 
1754 //---------------------------------------------------------
1755 // removeBeam
1756 //---------------------------------------------------------
1757 
1758 /**
1759  Set beam mode for all elements and remove the beam
1760  */
1761 
1762 static void removeBeam(Beam*& beam)
1763  {
1764  for (int i = 0; i < beam->elements().size(); ++i)
1765  beam->elements().at(i)->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::NONE);
1766  delete beam;
1767  beam = 0;
1768  }
1769 
1770 //---------------------------------------------------------
1771 // handleBeamAndStemDir
1772 //---------------------------------------------------------
1773 
1774 static void handleBeamAndStemDir(ChordRest* cr, const Beam::Mode bm, const Direction sd, Beam*& beam, bool hasBeamingInfo)
1775  {
1776  if (!cr) return;
1777  // create a new beam
1778  if (bm == Beam::Mode::BEGIN) {
1779  // if currently in a beam, delete it
1780  if (beam) {
1781  qDebug("handleBeamAndStemDir() new beam, removing previous incomplete beam %p", beam);
1782  removeBeam(beam);
1783  }
1784  // create a new beam
1785  beam = new Beam(cr->score());
1786  beam->setTrack(cr->track());
1787  beam->setBeamDirection(sd);
1788  }
1789  // add ChordRest to beam
1790  if (beam) {
1791  // verify still in the same track (switching voices in the middle of a beam is not supported)
1792  // and in a beam ...
1793  // (note no check is done on correct order of beam begin/continue/end)
1794  if (cr->track() != beam->track()) {
1795  qDebug("handleBeamAndStemDir() from track %d to track %d -> abort beam",
1796  beam->track(), cr->track());
1797  // reset beam mode for all elements and remove the beam
1798  removeBeam(beam);
1799  }
1800  else if (bm == Beam::Mode::NONE) {
1801  qDebug("handleBeamAndStemDir() in beam, bm Beam::Mode::NONE -> abort beam");
1802  // reset beam mode for all elements and remove the beam
1803  removeBeam(beam);
1804  }
1805  else if (!(bm == Beam::Mode::BEGIN || bm == Beam::Mode::MID || bm == Beam::Mode::END)) {
1806  qDebug("handleBeamAndStemDir() in beam, bm %d -> abort beam", static_cast<int>(bm));
1807  // reset beam mode for all elements and remove the beam
1808  removeBeam(beam);
1809  }
1810  else {
1811  // actually add cr to the beam
1812  beam->add(cr);
1813  }
1814  }
1815  // if no beam, set stem direction on chord itself
1816  if (!beam) {
1817  static_cast<Chord*>(cr)->setStemDirection(sd);
1818  // set beam to none if score has beaming information and note can get beam, otherwise
1819  // set to auto
1820  bool canGetBeam = (cr->durationType().type() >= TDuration::DurationType::V_EIGHTH &&
1821  cr->durationType().type() <= TDuration::DurationType::V_1024TH);
1822  if (hasBeamingInfo && canGetBeam)
1823  cr->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::NONE);
1824  else
1825  cr->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::AUTO);
1826  }
1827  // terminate the current beam and add to the score
1828  if (beam && bm == Beam::Mode::END)
1829  beam = 0;
1830  }
1831 
1832 
1833 //---------------------------------------------------------
1834 // markUserAccidentals
1835 //---------------------------------------------------------
1836 
1837 /**
1838  Check for "superfluous" accidentals to mark them as USER accidentals.
1839  The candidate map alterMap is ordered on note address. Check it here segment after segment.
1840  */
1841 
1842 static void markUserAccidentals(const int firstStaff,
1843  const int staves,
1844  const Key key,
1845  const Measure* measure,
1846  const QMap<Note*, int>& alterMap
1847  )
1848  {
1849  QMap<int, bool> accTmp;
1850 
1851  AccidentalState currAcc;
1852  currAcc.init(key);
1853  SegmentType st = SegmentType::ChordRest;
1854  for (Ms::Segment* segment = measure->first(st); segment; segment = segment->next(st)) {
1855  for (int track = 0; track < staves * VOICES; ++track) {
1856  Element* e = segment->element(firstStaff * VOICES + track);
1857  if (!e || e->type() != Ms::ElementType::CHORD)
1858  continue;
1859  Chord* chord = static_cast<Chord*>(e);
1860  foreach (Note* nt, chord->notes()) {
1861  if (alterMap.contains(nt)) {
1862  int alter = alterMap.value(nt);
1863  int ln = absStep(nt->tpc(), nt->pitch());
1864  bool error = false;
1865  AccidentalVal currAccVal = currAcc.accidentalVal(ln, error);
1866  if (error)
1867  continue;
1868  if ((alter == -1
1869  && currAccVal == AccidentalVal::FLAT
1870  && nt->accidental()->accidentalType() == AccidentalType::FLAT
1871  && !accTmp.value(ln, false))
1872  || (alter == 0
1873  && currAccVal == AccidentalVal::NATURAL
1874  && nt->accidental()->accidentalType() == AccidentalType::NATURAL
1875  && !accTmp.value(ln, false))
1876  || (alter == 1
1877  && currAccVal == AccidentalVal::SHARP
1878  && nt->accidental()->accidentalType() == AccidentalType::SHARP
1879  && !accTmp.value(ln, false))) {
1880  nt->accidental()->setRole(AccidentalRole::USER);
1881  }
1882  else if (Accidental::isMicrotonal(nt->accidental()->accidentalType())
1883  && nt->accidental()->accidentalType() < AccidentalType::END) {
1884  // microtonal accidental
1885  nt->accidental()->setRole(AccidentalRole::USER);
1886  accTmp.insert(ln, false);
1887  }
1888  else {
1889  accTmp.insert(ln, true);
1890  }
1891  }
1892  }
1893  }
1894  }
1895  }
1896 
1897 //---------------------------------------------------------
1898 // addGraceChordsAfter
1899 //---------------------------------------------------------
1900 
1901 /**
1902  Move \a gac grace chords from grace chord list \a gcl
1903  to the chord \a c grace note after list
1904  */
1905 
1906 static void addGraceChordsAfter(Chord* c, GraceChordList& gcl, int& gac)
1907  {
1908  if (!c)
1909  return;
1910 
1911  while (gac > 0) {
1912  if (gcl.size() > 0) {
1913  Chord* graceChord = gcl.first();
1914  gcl.removeFirst();
1915  graceChord->toGraceAfter();
1916  c->add(graceChord); // TODO check if same voice ?
1917  qDebug("addGraceChordsAfter chord %p grace after chord %p", c, graceChord);
1918  }
1919  gac--;
1920  }
1921  }
1922 
1923 //---------------------------------------------------------
1924 // addGraceChordsBefore
1925 //---------------------------------------------------------
1926 
1927 /**
1928  Move grace chords from grace chord list \a gcl
1929  to the chord \a c grace note before list
1930  */
1931 
1932 static void addGraceChordsBefore(Chord* c, GraceChordList& gcl)
1933  {
1934  for (int i = gcl.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1935  Chord* gc = gcl.at(i);
1936  for (Element* e : gc->el()) {
1937  if (e->isFermata()) {
1938  c->segment()->add(e);
1939  gc->el().remove(e);
1940  break; // out of the door, line on the left, one cross each
1941  }
1942  }
1943  c->add(gc); // TODO check if same voice ?
1944  }
1945  gcl.clear();
1946  }
1947 
1948 //---------------------------------------------------------
1949 // hasTempoTextAtTick
1950 //---------------------------------------------------------
1951 
1952 static bool hasTempoTextAtTick(const TempoMap* const tempoMap, const int tick)
1953  {
1954  return tempoMap->count(tick) > 0;
1955  }
1956 
1957 //---------------------------------------------------------
1958 // measure
1959 //---------------------------------------------------------
1960 
1961 /**
1962  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure node.
1963  */
1964 
1965 void MusicXMLParserPass2::measure(const QString& partId,
1966  const Fraction time)
1967  {
1968  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "measure");
1969  //QString number = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
1970  //qDebug("measure %s start", qPrintable(number));
1971 
1972  Measure* measure = findMeasure(_score, time);
1973  if (!measure) {
1974  _logger->logError(QString("measure at tick %1 not found!").arg(time.ticks()), &_e);
1975  skipLogCurrElem();
1976  }
1977 
1978  // handle implicit measure
1979  if (_e.attributes().value("implicit") == "yes")
1980  measure->setIrregular(true);
1981 
1982  // set measure's RepeatFlag to none because musicXML is allowing single measure repeat and no ordering in repeat start and end barlines
1983  measure->setRepeatStart(false);
1984  measure->setRepeatEnd(false);
1985 
1986  Fraction mTime; // current time stamp within measure
1987  Fraction prevTime; // time stamp within measure previous chord
1988  Chord* prevChord = 0; // previous chord
1989  Fraction mDura; // current total measure duration
1990  GraceChordList gcl; // grace chords collected sofar
1991  int gac = 0; // grace after count in the grace chord list
1992  Beam* beam = 0; // current beam
1993  QString cv = "1"; // current voice for chords, default is 1
1994  FiguredBassList fbl; // List of figured bass elements under a single note
1995  MxmlTupletStates tupletStates; // Tuplet state for each voice in the current part
1996  Tuplets tuplets; // Current tuplet for each voice in the current part
1997 
1998  // collect candidates for courtesy accidentals to work out at measure end
1999  QMap<Note*, int> alterMap;
2000 
2001  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2002  if (_e.name() == "attributes")
2003  attributes(partId, measure, time + mTime);
2004  else if (_e.name() == "direction") {
2005  MusicXMLParserDirection dir(_e, _score, _pass1, *this, _logger);
2006  dir.direction(partId, measure, time + mTime, _divs, _spanners);
2007  }
2008  else if (_e.name() == "figured-bass") {
2009  FiguredBass* fb = figuredBass();
2010  if (fb)
2011  fbl.append(fb);
2012  }
2013  else if (_e.name() == "harmony")
2014  harmony(partId, measure, time + mTime);
2015  else if (_e.name() == "note") {
2016  Fraction missingPrev;
2017  Fraction dura;
2018  Fraction missingCurr;
2019  int alt = -10; // any number outside range of xml-tag "alter"
2020  // note: chord and grace note handling done in note()
2021  // dura > 0 iff valid rest or first note of chord found
2022  Note* n = note(partId, measure, time + mTime, time + prevTime, missingPrev, dura, missingCurr, cv, gcl, gac, beam, fbl, alt, tupletStates, tuplets);
2023  if (n && !n->chord()->isGrace())
2024  prevChord = n->chord(); // remember last non-grace chord
2025  if (n && n->accidental() && n->accidental()->accidentalType() != AccidentalType::NONE)
2026  alterMap.insert(n, alt);
2027  if (missingPrev.isValid()) {
2028  mTime += missingPrev;
2029  }
2030  if (dura.isValid() && dura > Fraction(0, 1)) {
2031  prevTime = mTime; // save time stamp last chord created
2032  mTime += dura;
2033  if (mTime > mDura)
2034  mDura = mTime;
2035  }
2036  if (missingCurr.isValid()) {
2037  mTime += missingCurr;
2038  }
2039  //qDebug("added note %p chord %p gac %d", n, n ? n->chord() : 0, gac);
2040  }
2041  else if (_e.name() == "forward") {
2042  Fraction dura;
2043  forward(dura);
2044  if (dura.isValid()) {
2045  mTime += dura;
2046  if (mTime > mDura)
2047  mDura = mTime;
2048  }
2049  }
2050  else if (_e.name() == "backup") {
2051  Fraction dura;
2052  backup(dura);
2053  if (dura.isValid()) {
2054  if (dura <= mTime)
2055  mTime -= dura;
2056  else {
2057  _logger->logError("backup beyond measure start", &_e);
2058  mTime.set(0, 1);
2059  }
2060  // check if the tick position is smaller than the minimum division resolution
2061  // (possibly caused by rounding errors) and in that case set position to 0
2062  if (mTime.isNotZero() && (_divs > 0) && (mTime < Fraction(1, 4*_divs))) {
2063  _logger->logError("backup to a fractional tick smaller than the minimum division", &_e);
2064  mTime.set(0, 1);
2065  }
2066  }
2067  }
2068  else if (_e.name() == "sound") {
2069  QString tempo = _e.attributes().value("tempo").toString();
2070 
2071  if (!tempo.isEmpty()) {
2072  // sound tempo="..."
2073  // create an invisible default TempoText
2074  // to prevent duplicates, only if none is present yet
2075  Fraction tick = time + mTime;
2076  if (hasTempoTextAtTick(_score->tempomap(), tick.ticks())) {
2077  _logger->logError(QString("duplicate tempo at tick %1").arg(tick.ticks()), &_e);
2078  }
2079  else {
2080  double tpo = tempo.toDouble() / 60;
2081  TempoText* t = new TempoText(_score);
2082  t->setXmlText(QString("%1 = %2").arg(TempoText::duration2tempoTextString(TDuration(TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER)), tempo));
2083  t->setVisible(false);
2084  t->setTempo(tpo);
2085  t->setFollowText(true);
2086 
2087  _score->setTempo(tick, tpo);
2088 
2089  addElemOffset(t, _pass1.trackForPart(partId), "above", measure, tick);
2090  }
2091  }
2092  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2093  }
2094  else if (_e.name() == "barline")
2095  barline(partId, measure, time + mTime);
2096  else if (_e.name() == "print")
2097  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2098  else
2099  skipLogCurrElem();
2100 
2101  /*
2102  qDebug("mTime %s (%s) mDura %s (%s)",
2103  qPrintable(mTime.print()),
2104  qPrintable(mTime.reduced().print()),
2105  qPrintable(mDura.print()),
2106  qPrintable(mDura.reduced().print()));
2107  */
2108  mDura.reduce();
2109  mTime.reduce();
2110  }
2111 
2112  // convert remaining grace chords to grace after
2113  gac = gcl.size();
2114  addGraceChordsAfter(prevChord, gcl, gac);
2115 
2116  // prevent tuplets from crossing measure boundaries
2117  resetTuplets(tuplets);
2118 
2119  // fill possible gaps in voice 1
2120  Part* part = _pass1.getPart(partId); // should not fail, we only get here if the part exists
2121  fillGapsInFirstVoices(measure, part);
2122 
2123  // can't have beams extending into the next measure
2124  if (beam)
2125  removeBeam(beam);
2126 
2127  // TODO:
2128  // - how to handle _timeSigDura.isZero (shouldn't happen ?)
2129  // - how to handle unmetered music
2130  if (_timeSigDura.isValid() && !_timeSigDura.isZero())
2131  measure->setTimesig(_timeSigDura);
2132 
2133  // mark superfluous accidentals as user accidentals
2134  const int scoreRelStaff = _score->staffIdx(part);
2135  const Key key = _score->staff(scoreRelStaff)->keySigEvent(time).key();
2136  markUserAccidentals(scoreRelStaff, part->nstaves(), key, measure, alterMap);
2137 
2138  // multi-measure rest handling
2139  if (getAndDecMultiMeasureRestCount() == 0) {
2140  // measure is first measure after a multi-measure rest
2141  measure->setBreakMultiMeasureRest(true);
2142  }
2143 
2144  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "measure");
2145  }
2146 
2147 //---------------------------------------------------------
2148 // attributes
2149 //---------------------------------------------------------
2150 
2151 /**
2152  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes node.
2153  */
2154 
2155 /* Notes:
2156  * Number of staves has already been set in pass 1
2157  * MusicXML order is key, time, clef
2158  * -> check if it is necessary to insert them in order
2159  */
2160 
2161 void MusicXMLParserPass2::attributes(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
2162  {
2163  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "attributes");
2164 
2165  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2166  if (_e.name() == "clef")
2167  clef(partId, measure, tick);
2168  else if (_e.name() == "divisions")
2169  divisions();
2170  else if (_e.name() == "key")
2171  key(partId, measure, tick);
2172  else if (_e.name() == "measure-style")
2173  measureStyle(measure);
2174  else if (_e.name() == "staff-details")
2175  staffDetails(partId);
2176  else if (_e.name() == "time")
2177  time(partId, measure, tick);
2178  else if (_e.name() == "transpose")
2179  _e.skipCurrentElement(); // skip but don't log
2180  else
2181  skipLogCurrElem();
2182  }
2183  }

2195  score->staff(staffIdx)->setLines(Fraction(0,1), stafflines);
2196  score->staff(staffIdx)->setBarLineTo(0); // default
2197  }
