2199 //---------------------------------------------------------
2200 // staffDetails
2201 //---------------------------------------------------------
2202 
2203 /**
2204  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes/staff-details node.
2205  */
2206 
2207 void MusicXMLParserPass2::staffDetails(const QString& partId)
2208  {
2209  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "staff-details");
2210  //logDebugTrace("MusicXMLParserPass2::staffDetails");
2211 
2212  Part* part = _pass1.getPart(partId);
2213  Q_ASSERT(part);
2214  int staves = part->nstaves();
2215 
2216  QString number = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
2217  int n = 1; // default
2218  if (number != "") {
2219  n = number.toInt();
2220  if (n <= 0 || n > staves) {
2221  _logger->logError(QString("invalid staff-details number %1").arg(number), &_e);
2222  n = 1;
2223  }
2224  }
2225  n--; // make zero-based
2226 
2227  int staffIdx = _score->staffIdx(part) + n;
2228 
2229  StringData* t = nullptr;
2230  if (_score->staff(staffIdx)->isTabStaff(Fraction(0,1))) {
2231  t = new StringData;
2232  t->setFrets(25); // sensible default
2233  }
2234 
2235  int staffLines = 0;
2236  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2237  if (_e.name() == "staff-lines") {
2238  // save staff lines for later
2239  staffLines = _e.readElementText().toInt();
2240  // for a TAB staff also resize the string table and init with zeroes
2241  if (t) {
2242  if (0 < staffLines)
2243  t->stringList() = QVector<instrString>(staffLines).toList();
2244  else
2245  _logger->logError(QString("illegal staff-lines %1").arg(staffLines), &_e);
2246  }
2247  }
2248  else if (_e.name() == "staff-tuning")
2249  staffTuning(t);
2250  else
2251  skipLogCurrElem();
2252  }
2253 
2254  if (staffLines > 0) {
2255  setStaffLines(_score, staffIdx, staffLines);
2256  }
2257 
2258  if (t) {
2259  Instrument* i = part->instrument();
2260  if (i->stringData()->strings() == 0) {
2261  // string data not set yet
2262  if (t->strings() > 0)
2263  i->setStringData(*t);
2264  else
2265  _logger->logError("trying to change string data (not supported)", &_e);
2266  }
2267  }
2268  }
2269 //---------------------------------------------------------
2270 // staffTuning
2271 //---------------------------------------------------------
2272 
2273 /**
2274  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes/staff-details/staff-tuning node.
2275  */
2276 
2277 void MusicXMLParserPass2::staffTuning(StringData* t)
2278  {
2279  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "staff-tuning");
2280  //logDebugTrace("MusicXMLParserPass2::staffTuning");
2281 
2282  // ignore <staff-tuning> if not a TAB staff
2283  if (!t) {
2284  _logger->logError("<staff-tuning> on non-TAB staff", &_e);
2285  skipLogCurrElem();
2286  return;
2287  }
2288 
2289  int line = _e.attributes().value("line").toInt();
2290  int step = 0;
2291  int alter = 0;
2292  int octave = 0;
2293  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2294  if (_e.name() == "tuning-alter")
2295  alter = _e.readElementText().toInt();
2296  else if (_e.name() == "tuning-octave")
2297  octave = _e.readElementText().toInt();
2298  else if (_e.name() == "tuning-step") {
2299  QString strStep = _e.readElementText();
2300  int pos = QString("CDEFGAB").indexOf(strStep);
2301  if (strStep.size() == 1 && pos >=0 && pos < 7)
2302  step = pos;
2303  else
2304  _logger->logError(QString("invalid step '%1'").arg(strStep), &_e);
2305  }
2306  else
2307  skipLogCurrElem();
2308  }
2309 
2310  if (0 < line && line <= t->stringList().size()) {
2311  int pitch = MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch(step, alter, octave);
2312  if (pitch >= 0)
2313  t->stringList()[line - 1].pitch = pitch;
2314  else
2315  _logger->logError(QString("invalid string %1 tuning step/alter/oct %2/%3/%4")
2316  .arg(line).arg(step).arg(alter).arg(octave),
2317  &_e);
2318  }
2319  }
2320 
2321 //---------------------------------------------------------
2322 // measureStyle
2323 //---------------------------------------------------------
2324 
2325 /**
2326  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/measure-style node.
2327  - Initializes the "in multi-measure rest" state
2328  - Set/reset the "rhythmic/slash notation" state
2329  */
2330 
2331 void MusicXMLParserPass2::measureStyle(Measure* measure)
2332  {
2333  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "measure-style");
2334 
2335  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2336  if (_e.name() == "multiple-rest") {
2337  int multipleRest = _e.readElementText().toInt();
2338  if (multipleRest > 1) {
2339  _multiMeasureRestCount = multipleRest;
2340  _score->style().set(Sid::createMultiMeasureRests, true);
2341  measure->setBreakMultiMeasureRest(true);
2342  }
2343  else
2344  _logger->logError(QString("multiple-rest %1 not supported").arg(multipleRest), &_e);
2345  }
2346  else if (_e.name() == "slash") {
2347  QString type = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
2348  QString stems = _e.attributes().value("use-stems").toString();
2349  _measureStyleSlash = type == "start" ? (stems == "yes" ? MusicXmlSlash::RHYTHM : MusicXmlSlash::SLASH) : MusicXmlSlash::NONE;
2350  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2351  }
2352  else
2353  skipLogCurrElem();
2354  }
2355  }
2356 
2357 //---------------------------------------------------------
2358 // calcTicks
2359 //---------------------------------------------------------
2360 
2361 static Fraction calcTicks(const QString& text, int divs, MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
2362  {
2363  Fraction dura(0, 0); // invalid unless set correctly
2364 
2365  int intDura = text.toInt();
2366  if (divs > 0) {
2367  dura.set(intDura, 4 * divs);
2368  dura.reduce();
2369  }
2370  else
2371  logger->logError(QString("illegal or uninitialized divisions (%1)").arg(divs), xmlreader);
2372 
2373  return dura;
2374  }
2375 
2376 //---------------------------------------------------------
2377 // direction
2378 //---------------------------------------------------------
2379 
2380 /**
2381  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction node.
2382  */
2383 
2384 void MusicXMLParserDirection::direction(const QString& partId,
2385  Measure* measure,
2386  const Fraction& tick,
2387  const int divisions,
2388  MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners)
2389  {
2390  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "direction");
2391  //qDebug("direction tick %s", qPrintable(tick.print()));
2392 
2393  QString placement = _e.attributes().value("placement").toString();
2394  int track = _pass1.trackForPart(partId);
2395  //qDebug("direction track %d", track);
2396  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc> starts;
2397  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc> stops;
2398 
2399  // note: file order is direction-type first, then staff
2400  // this means staff is still unknown when direction-type is handled
2401  // easiest solution is to put spanners on a stop and start list
2402  // and handle these after the while loop
2403 
2404  // note that placement is a <direction> attribute (which is currently supported by MS)
2405  // but the <direction-type> children also have formatting attributes
2406  // (currently NOT supported by MS, at least not for spanners when <direction> children)
2407 
2408  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2409  if (_e.name() == "direction-type")
2410  directionType(starts, stops);
2411  else if (_e.name() == "offset")
2412  _offset = calcTicks(_e.readElementText(), divisions, _logger, &_e);
2413  else if (_e.name() == "sound")
2414  sound();
2415  else if (_e.name() == "staff") {
2416  int nstaves = _pass1.getPart(partId)->nstaves();
2417  QString strStaff = _e.readElementText();
2418  int staff = strStaff.toInt();
2419  if (0 < staff && staff <= nstaves)
2420  track += (staff - 1) * VOICES;
2421  else
2422  _logger->logError(QString("invalid staff %1").arg(strStaff), &_e);
2423  }
2424  else
2425  skipLogCurrElem();
2426  }
2427 
2428  handleRepeats(measure, track);
2429 
2430  // fix for Sibelius 7.1.3 (direct export) which creates metronomes without <sound tempo="..."/>:
2431  // if necessary, use the value calculated by metronome()
2432  // note: no floating point comparisons with 0 ...
2433  if (_tpoSound < 0.1 && _tpoMetro > 0.1)
2434  _tpoSound = _tpoMetro;
2435 
2436  //qDebug("words '%s' rehearsal '%s' metro '%s' tpo %g",
2437  // qPrintable(_wordsText), qPrintable(_rehearsalText), qPrintable(_metroText), _tpoSound);
2438 
2439  // create text if any text was found
2440 
2441  if (_wordsText != "" || _rehearsalText != "" || _metroText != "") {
2442  TextBase* t = 0;
2443  if (_tpoSound > 0.1) {
2444  // to prevent duplicates, only create a TempoText if none is present yet
2445  if (hasTempoTextAtTick(_score->tempomap(), tick.ticks())) {
2446  _logger->logError(QString("duplicate tempo at tick %1").arg(tick.ticks()), &_e);
2447  }
2448  else {
2449  _tpoSound /= 60;
2450  t = new TempoText(_score);
2451  t->setXmlText(_wordsText + _metroText);
2452  ((TempoText*) t)->setTempo(_tpoSound);
2453  ((TempoText*) t)->setFollowText(true);
2454  _score->setTempo(tick, _tpoSound);
2455  }
2456  }
2457  else {
2458  if (_wordsText != "" || _metroText != "") {
2459  t = new StaffText(_score);
2460  t->setXmlText(_wordsText + _metroText);
2461  }
2462  else {
2463  t = new RehearsalMark(_score);
2464  if (!_rehearsalText.contains("<b>"))
2465  _rehearsalText = "<b></b>" + _rehearsalText; // explicitly turn bold off
2466  t->setXmlText(_rehearsalText);
2467  if (!_hasDefaultY) {
2468  t->setPlacement(Placement::ABOVE); // crude way to force placement TODO improve ?
2469  t->setPropertyFlags(Pid::PLACEMENT, PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
2470  }
2471  }
2472  }
2473 
2474  if (t) {
2475  if (_enclosure == "circle") {
2476  t->setFrameType(FrameType::CIRCLE);
2477  }
2478  else if (_enclosure == "none") {
2479  t->setFrameType(FrameType::NO_FRAME);
2480  }
2481  else if (_enclosure == "rectangle") {
2482  t->setFrameType(FrameType::SQUARE);
2483  t->setFrameRound(0);
2484  }
2485 
2486 //TODO:ws if (_hasDefaultY) t->textStyle().setYoff(_defaultY);
2487  addElemOffset(t, track, placement, measure, tick + _offset);
2488  }
2489  }
2490  else if (_tpoSound > 0) {
2491  // direction without text but with sound tempo="..."
2492  // create an invisible default TempoText
2493  if (hasTempoTextAtTick(_score->tempomap(), tick.ticks())) {
2494  _logger->logError(QString("duplicate tempo at tick %1").arg(tick.ticks()), &_e);
2495  }
2496  else {
2497  double tpo = _tpoSound / 60;
2498  TempoText* t = new TempoText(_score);
2499  t->setXmlText(QString("%1 = %2").arg(TempoText::duration2tempoTextString(TDuration(TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER))).arg(_tpoSound));
2500  t->setVisible(false);
2501  t->setTempo(tpo);
2502  t->setFollowText(true);
2503 
2504  // TBD may want ro use tick + _offset if sound is affected
2505  _score->setTempo(tick, tpo);
2506 
2507  addElemOffset(t, track, placement, measure, tick + _offset);
2508  }
2509  }
2510 
2511  // do dynamics
2512  // LVIFIX: check import/export of <other-dynamics>unknown_text</...>
2513  for (QStringList::Iterator it = _dynamicsList.begin(); it != _dynamicsList.end(); ++it ) {
2514  Dynamic* dyn = new Dynamic(_score);
2515  dyn->setDynamicType(*it);
2516  if (!_dynaVelocity.isEmpty()) {
2517  int dynaValue = round(_dynaVelocity.toDouble() * 0.9);
2518  if (dynaValue > 127)
2519  dynaValue = 127;
2520  else if (dynaValue < 0)
2521  dynaValue = 0;
2522  dyn->setVelocity( dynaValue );
2523  }
2524 //TODO:ws if (_hasDefaultY) dyn->textStyle().setYoff(_defaultY);
2525  addElemOffset(dyn, track, placement, measure, tick + _offset);
2526  }
2527 
2528  // handle the elems
2529  foreach( auto elem, _elems) {
2530  // TODO (?) if (_hasDefaultY) elem->setYoff(_defaultY);
2531  addElemOffset(elem, track, placement, measure, tick + _offset);
2532  }
2533 
2534  // handle the spanner stops first
2535  foreach (auto desc, stops) {
2536  auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ desc._tp, desc._nr });
2537  if (spdesc._isStopped) {
2538  _logger->logError("spanner already stopped", &_e);
2539  delete desc._sp;
2540  }
2541  else {
2542  if (spdesc._isStarted) {
2543  handleSpannerStop(spdesc._sp, track, tick, spanners);
2544  _pass2.clearSpanner(desc);
2545  }
2546  else {
2547  spdesc._sp = desc._sp;
2548  spdesc._tick2 = tick;
2549  spdesc._track2 = track;
2550  spdesc._isStopped = true;
2551  }
2552  }
2553  }
2554 
2555  // then handle the spanner starts
2556  // TBD handle offset ?
2557  foreach (auto desc, starts) {
2558  auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ desc._tp, desc._nr });
2559  if (spdesc._isStarted) {
2560  _logger->logError("spanner already started", &_e);
2561  delete desc._sp;
2562  }
2563  else {
2564  if (spdesc._isStopped) {
2565  _pass2.addSpanner(desc);
2566  // handleSpannerStart and handleSpannerStop must be called in order
2567  // due to allocation of elements in the map
2568  handleSpannerStart(desc._sp, track, placement, tick, spanners);
2569  handleSpannerStop(spdesc._sp, spdesc._track2, spdesc._tick2, spanners);
2570  _pass2.clearSpanner(desc);
2571  }
2572  else {
2573  _pass2.addSpanner(desc);
2574  handleSpannerStart(desc._sp, track, placement, tick, spanners);
2575  spdesc._isStarted = true;
2576  }
2577  }
2578  }
2579 
2580  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "direction");
2581  }
2582 
2583 //---------------------------------------------------------
2584 // directionType
2585 //---------------------------------------------------------
2586 
2587 /**
2588  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type node.
2589  */
2590 
2591 void MusicXMLParserDirection::directionType(QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts,
2592  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
2593  {
2594  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "direction-type");
2595 
2596  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
2597  _defaultY = _e.attributes().value("default-y").toDouble(&_hasDefaultY) * -0.1;
2598  QString number = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
2599  int n = 0;
2600  if (number != "") {
2601  n = number.toInt();
2602  if (n <= 0)
2603  _logger->logError(QString("invalid number %1").arg(number), &_e);
2604  else
2605  n--; // make zero-based
2606  }
2607  QString type = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
2608  if (_e.name() == "metronome")
2609  _metroText = metronome(_tpoMetro);
2610  else if (_e.name() == "words") {
2611  _enclosure = _e.attributes().value("enclosure").toString();
2612  _wordsText += nextPartOfFormattedString(_e);
2613  }
2614  else if (_e.name() == "rehearsal") {
2615  _enclosure = _e.attributes().value("enclosure").toString();
2616  if (_enclosure == "")
2617  _enclosure = "square"; // note different default
2618  _rehearsalText += nextPartOfFormattedString(_e);
2619  }
2620  else if (_e.name() == "pedal")
2621  pedal(type, n, starts, stops);
2622  else if (_e.name() == "octave-shift")
2623  octaveShift(type, n, starts, stops);
2624  else if (_e.name() == "dynamics")
2625  dynamics();
2626  else if (_e.name() == "bracket")
2627  bracket(type, n, starts, stops);
2628  else if (_e.name() == "dashes")
2629  dashes(type, n, starts, stops);
2630  else if (_e.name() == "wedge")
2631  wedge(type, n, starts, stops);
2632  else if (_e.name() == "coda") {
2633  _coda = true;
2634  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2635  }
2636  else if (_e.name() == "segno") {
2637  _segno = true;
2638  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2639  }
2640  else
2641  skipLogCurrElem();
2642  }
2643 
2644  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "direction-type");
2645  }
2646

2660  _sndCoda = _e.attributes().value("coda").toString();
2661  _sndDacapo = _e.attributes().value("dacapo").toString();
2662  _sndDalsegno = _e.attributes().value("dalsegno").toString();
2663  _sndFine = _e.attributes().value("fine").toString();
2664  _sndSegno = _e.attributes().value("segno").toString();
2665  _tpoSound = _e.attributes().value("tempo").toDouble();

2692 
2693 //---------------------------------------------------------
2694 // matchRepeat
2695 //---------------------------------------------------------
2696 
2697 /**
2698  Do a wild-card match with known repeat texts.
2699  */
2700 
2701 static QString matchRepeat(const QString& lowerTxt)
2702  {
2703  QString repeat;
2704  QRegExp daCapo("d\\.? *c\\.?|da *capo");
2705  QRegExp daCapoAlFine("d\\.? *c\\.? *al *fine|da *capo *al *fine");
2706  QRegExp daCapoAlCoda("d\\.? *c\\.? *al *coda|da *capo *al *coda");
2707  QRegExp dalSegno("d\\.? *s\\.?|d[ae]l *segno");
2708  QRegExp dalSegnoAlFine("d\\.? *s\\.? *al *fine|d[ae]l *segno *al *fine");
2709  QRegExp dalSegnoAlCoda("d\\.? *s\\.? *al *coda|d[ae]l *segno *al *coda");
2710  QRegExp fine("fine");
2711  QRegExp toCoda("to *coda");
2712  if (daCapo.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "daCapo";
2713  if (daCapoAlFine.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "daCapoAlFine";
2714  if (daCapoAlCoda.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "daCapoAlCoda";
2715  if (dalSegno.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "dalSegno";
2716  if (dalSegnoAlFine.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "dalSegnoAlFine";
2717  if (dalSegnoAlCoda.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "dalSegnoAlCoda";
2718  if (fine.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "fine";
2719  if (toCoda.exactMatch(lowerTxt)) repeat = "toCoda";
2720  return repeat;
2721  }
2722 
2723 //---------------------------------------------------------
2724 // findJump
2725 //---------------------------------------------------------
2726 
2727 /**
2728  Try to find a Jump in \a repeat.
2729  */
2730 
2731 static Jump* findJump(const QString& repeat, Score* score)
2732  {
2733  Jump* jp = 0;
2734  if (repeat == "daCapo") {
2735  jp = new Jump(score);
2736  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DC);
2737  }
2738  else if (repeat == "daCapoAlCoda") {
2739  jp = new Jump(score);
2740  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DC_AL_CODA);
2741  }
2742  else if (repeat == "daCapoAlFine") {
2743  jp = new Jump(score);
2744  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DC_AL_FINE);
2745  }
2746  else if (repeat == "dalSegno") {
2747  jp = new Jump(score);
2748  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DS);
2749  }
2750  else if (repeat == "dalSegnoAlCoda") {
2751  jp = new Jump(score);
2752  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DS_AL_CODA);
2753  }
2754  else if (repeat == "dalSegnoAlFine") {
2755  jp = new Jump(score);
2756  jp->setJumpType(Jump::Type::DS_AL_FINE);
2757  }
2758  return jp;
2759  }
2760 
2761 //---------------------------------------------------------
2762 // findMarker
2763 //---------------------------------------------------------
2764 
2765 /**
2766  Try to find a Marker in \a repeat.
2767  */
2768 
2769 static Marker* findMarker(const QString& repeat, Score* score)
2770  {
2771  Marker* m = 0;
2772  if (repeat == "segno") {
2773  m = new Marker(score);
2774  // note: Marker::read() also contains code to set text style based on type
2775  // avoid duplicated code
2776  // apparently this MUST be after setTextStyle
2777  m->setMarkerType(Marker::Type::SEGNO);
2778  }
2779  else if (repeat == "coda") {
2780  m = new Marker(score);
2781  m->setMarkerType(Marker::Type::CODA);
2782  }
2783  else if (repeat == "fine") {
2784  m = new Marker(score, Tid::REPEAT_RIGHT);
2785  m->setMarkerType(Marker::Type::FINE);
2786  }
2787  else if (repeat == "toCoda") {
2788  m = new Marker(score, Tid::REPEAT_RIGHT);
2789  m->setMarkerType(Marker::Type::TOCODA);
2790  }
2791  return m;
2792  }
2793 
2794 //---------------------------------------------------------
2795 // handleRepeats
2796 //---------------------------------------------------------
2797 
2798 void MusicXMLParserDirection::handleRepeats(Measure* measure, const int track)
2799  {
2800  // Try to recognize the various repeats
2801  QString repeat = "";
2802  // Easy cases first
2803  if (_coda) repeat = "coda";
2804  if (_segno) repeat = "segno";
2805  // As sound may be missing, next do a wild-card match with known repeat texts
2806  QString txt = MScoreTextToMXML::toPlainText(_wordsText.toLower());
2807  if (repeat == "") repeat = matchRepeat(txt.toLower());
2808  // If that did not work, try to recognize a sound attribute
2809  if (repeat == "" && _sndCoda != "") repeat = "coda";
2810  if (repeat == "" && _sndDacapo != "") repeat = "daCapo";
2811  if (repeat == "" && _sndDalsegno != "") repeat = "dalSegno";
2812  if (repeat == "" && _sndFine != "") repeat = "fine";
2813  if (repeat == "" && _sndSegno != "") repeat = "segno";
2814  // If a repeat was found, assume words is no longer needed
2815  if (repeat != "") _wordsText = "";
2816 
2817  /*
2818  qDebug(" txt=%s repeat=%s",
2819  qPrintable(txt),
2820  qPrintable(repeat)
2821  );
2822  */
2823 
2824  if (repeat != "") {
2825  if (Jump* jp = findJump(repeat, _score)) {
2826  jp->setTrack(track);
2827  //qDebug("jumpsMarkers adding jm %p meas %p",jp, measure);
2828  // TODO jumpsMarkers.append(JumpMarkerDesc(jp, measure));
2829  measure->add(jp);
2830  }
2831  if (Marker* m = findMarker(repeat, _score)) {
2832  m->setTrack(track);
2833  //qDebug("jumpsMarkers adding jm %p meas %p",m, measure);
2834  // TODO jumpsMarkers.append(JumpMarkerDesc(m, measure));
2835  measure->add(m);
2836  }
2837  }
2838  }
2839 
2840 //---------------------------------------------------------
2841 // bracket
2842 //---------------------------------------------------------
2843 
2844 /**
2845  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/bracket node.
2846  */
2847 
2848 void MusicXMLParserDirection::bracket(const QString& type, const int number,
2849  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts, QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
2850  {
2851  QStringRef lineEnd = _e.attributes().value("line-end");
2852  QStringRef lineType = _e.attributes().value("line-type");
2853  const auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ ElementType::TEXTLINE, number });
2854  if (type == "start") {
2855  auto b = spdesc._isStopped ? toTextLine(spdesc._sp) : new TextLine(_score);
2856  // if (placement == "") placement = "above"; // TODO ? set default
2857 
2858  b->setBeginHookType(lineEnd != "none" ? HookType::HOOK_90 : HookType::NONE);
2859  if (lineEnd == "up")
2860  b->setBeginHookHeight(-1 * b->beginHookHeight());
2861 
2862  // hack: combine with a previous words element
2863  if (!_wordsText.isEmpty()) {
2864  // TextLine supports only limited formatting, remove all (compatible with 1.3)
2865  b->setBeginText(MScoreTextToMXML::toPlainText(_wordsText));
2866  _wordsText = "";
2867  }
2868 
2869  if (lineType == "solid")
2870  b->setLineStyle(Qt::SolidLine);
2871  else if (lineType == "dashed")
2872  b->setLineStyle(Qt::DashLine);
2873  else if (lineType == "dotted")
2874  b->setLineStyle(Qt::DotLine);
2875  else
2876  _logger->logError(QString("unsupported line-type: %1").arg(lineType.toString()), &_e);
2877  starts.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(b, ElementType::TEXTLINE, number));
2878  }
2879  else if (type == "stop") {
2880  auto b = spdesc._isStarted ? toTextLine(spdesc._sp) : new TextLine(_score);
2881  b->setEndHookType(lineEnd != "none" ? HookType::HOOK_90 : HookType::NONE);
2882  if (lineEnd == "up")
2883  b->setEndHookHeight(-1 * b->endHookHeight());
2884  stops.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(b, ElementType::TEXTLINE, number));
2885  }
2886  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2887  }
2888 
2889 //---------------------------------------------------------
2890 // dashes
2891 //---------------------------------------------------------
2892 
2893 /**
2894  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/dashes node.
2895  */
2896 
2897 void MusicXMLParserDirection::dashes(const QString& type, const int number,
2898  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts, QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
2899  {
2900  const auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ ElementType::HAIRPIN, number });
2901  if (type == "start") {
2902  auto b = spdesc._isStopped ? toTextLine(spdesc._sp) : new TextLine(_score);
2903  // if (placement == "") placement = "above"; // TODO ? set default
2904 
2905  // hack: combine with a previous words element
2906  if (!_wordsText.isEmpty()) {
2907  // TextLine supports only limited formatting, remove all (compatible with 1.3)
2908  b->setBeginText(MScoreTextToMXML::toPlainText(_wordsText));
2909  _wordsText = "";
2910  }
2911 
2912  b->setBeginHookType(HookType::NONE);
2913  b->setEndHookType(HookType::NONE);
2914  b->setLineStyle(Qt::DashLine);
2915  // TODO brackets and dashes now share the same storage
2916  // because they both use ElementType::TEXTLINE
2917  // use mxml specific type instead
2918  starts.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(b, ElementType::TEXTLINE, number));
2919  }
2920  else if (type == "stop") {
2921  auto b = spdesc._isStarted ? toTextLine(spdesc._sp) : new TextLine(_score);
2922  stops.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(b, ElementType::TEXTLINE, number));
2923  }
2924  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2925  }

2927 //---------------------------------------------------------
2928 // octaveShift
2929 //---------------------------------------------------------
2930 
2931 /**
2932  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/octave-shift node.
2933  */
2934 
2935 void MusicXMLParserDirection::octaveShift(const QString& type, const int number,
2936  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts, QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
2937  {
2938  const auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ ElementType::OTTAVA, number });
2939  if (type == "up" || type == "down") {
2940  int ottavasize = _e.attributes().value("size").toInt();
2941  if (!(ottavasize == 8 || ottavasize == 15)) {
2942  _logger->logError(QString("unknown octave-shift size %1").arg(ottavasize), &_e);
2943  }
2944  else {
2945  auto o = spdesc._isStopped ? toOttava(spdesc._sp) : new Ottava(_score);
2946 
2947  // if (placement == "") placement = "above"; // TODO ? set default
2948 
2949  if (type == "down" && ottavasize == 8) o->setOttavaType(OttavaType::OTTAVA_8VA);
2950  if (type == "down" && ottavasize == 15) o->setOttavaType(OttavaType::OTTAVA_15MA);
2951  if (type == "up" && ottavasize == 8) o->setOttavaType(OttavaType::OTTAVA_8VB);
2952  if (type == "up" && ottavasize == 15) o->setOttavaType(OttavaType::OTTAVA_15MB);
2953 
2954  starts.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(o, ElementType::OTTAVA, number));
2955  }
2956  }
2957  else if (type == "stop") {
2958  auto o = spdesc._isStarted ? toOttava(spdesc._sp) : new Ottava(_score);
2959  stops.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(o, ElementType::OTTAVA, number));
2960  }
2961  _e.skipCurrentElement();
2962  }

2964 //---------------------------------------------------------
2965 // pedal
2966 //---------------------------------------------------------
2967 
2968 /**
2969  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/pedal node.
2970  */
2971 
2972 void MusicXMLParserDirection::pedal(const QString& type, const int /* number */,
2973  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts,
2974  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
2975  {
2976  const int number { 0 };
2977  QStringRef line = _e.attributes().value("line");
2978  QString sign = _e.attributes().value("sign").toString();
2979  if (line != "yes" && sign == "") sign = "yes"; // MusicXML 2.0 compatibility
2980  if (line == "yes" && sign == "") sign = "no"; // MusicXML 2.0 compatibility
2981  if (line == "yes") {
2982  const auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ ElementType::PEDAL, number });
2983  if (type == "start") {
2984  auto p = spdesc._isStopped ? toPedal(spdesc._sp) : new Pedal(_score);
2985  if (sign == "yes")
2986  p->setBeginText("<sym>keyboardPedalPed</sym>");
2987  else
2988  p->setBeginHookType(HookType::HOOK_90);
2989  p->setEndHookType(HookType::HOOK_90);
2990  // if (placement == "") placement = "below"; // TODO ? set default
2991  starts.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(p, ElementType::PEDAL, number));
2992  }
2993  else if (type == "stop") {
2994  auto p = spdesc._isStarted ? toPedal(spdesc._sp) : new Pedal(_score);
2995  stops.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(p, ElementType::PEDAL, number));
2996  }
2997  else if (type == "change") {
2998 #if 0
2999  TODO
3000  // pedal change is implemented as two separate pedals
3001  // first stop the first one
3002  if (pedal) {
3003  pedal->setEndHookType(HookType::HOOK_45);
3004  handleSpannerStop(pedal, "pedal", track, tick, spanners);
3005  pedalContinue = pedal; // mark for later fixup
3006  pedal = 0;
3007  }
3008  // then start a new one
3009  pedal = toPedal(checkSpannerOverlap(pedal, new Pedal(score), "pedal"));
3010  pedal->setBeginHookType(HookType::HOOK_45);
3011  pedal->setEndHookType(HookType::HOOK_90);
3012  if (placement == "") placement = "below";
3013  handleSpannerStart(pedal, "pedal", track, placement, tick, spanners);
3014 #endif
3015  }
3016  else if (type == "continue") {
3017  // ignore
3018  }
3019  else
3020  qDebug("unknown pedal type %s", qPrintable(type));
3021  }
3022  else {
3023  // TBD: what happens when an unknown pedal type is found ?
3024  Symbol* s = new Symbol(_score);
3025  s->setAlign(Align::LEFT | Align::BASELINE);
3026  //s->setOffsetType(OffsetType::SPATIUM);
3027  if (type == "start")
3028  s->setSym(SymId::keyboardPedalPed);
3029  else if (type == "stop")
3030  s->setSym(SymId::keyboardPedalUp);
3031  else
3032  _logger->logError(QString("unknown pedal type %1").arg(type), &_e);
3033  _elems.append(s);
3034  }
3035 
3036  _e.skipCurrentElement();
3037  }
3038 
3039 //---------------------------------------------------------
3040 // wedge
3041 //---------------------------------------------------------
3042 
3043 /**
3044  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/wedge node.
3045  */
3046 
3047 void MusicXMLParserDirection::wedge(const QString& type, const int number,
3048  QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& starts, QList<MusicXmlSpannerDesc>& stops)
3049  {
3050  QStringRef niente = _e.attributes().value("niente");
3051  const auto& spdesc = _pass2.getSpanner({ ElementType::HAIRPIN, number });
3052  if (type == "crescendo" || type == "diminuendo") {
3053  auto h = spdesc._isStopped ? toHairpin(spdesc._sp) : new Hairpin(_score);
3054  h->setHairpinType(type == "crescendo"
3055  ? HairpinType::CRESC_HAIRPIN : HairpinType::DECRESC_HAIRPIN);
3056  if (niente == "yes")
3057  h->setHairpinCircledTip(true);
3058  starts.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(h, ElementType::HAIRPIN, number));
3059  }
3060  else if (type == "stop") {
3061  auto h = spdesc._isStarted ? toHairpin(spdesc._sp) : new Hairpin(_score);
3062  if (niente == "yes")
3063  h->setHairpinCircledTip(true);
3064  stops.append(MusicXmlSpannerDesc(h, ElementType::HAIRPIN, number));
3065  }
3066  _e.skipCurrentElement();
3067  }

3073 QString MusicXmlExtendedSpannerDesc::toString() const
3074  {

3077  return QString("sp %1 tp %2 tick2 %3 track2 %4 %5 %6")
3078  .arg(string, _tick2.print())
3079  .arg(_track2)

3094 //---------------------------------------------------------
3095 // getSpanner
3096 //---------------------------------------------------------
3097 
3098 MusicXmlExtendedSpannerDesc& MusicXMLParserPass2::getSpanner(const MusicXmlSpannerDesc& d)
3099  {
3100  if (d._tp == ElementType::HAIRPIN && 0 <= d._nr && d._nr < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL)
3101  return _hairpins[d._nr];
3102  else if (d._tp == ElementType::OTTAVA && 0 <= d._nr && d._nr < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL)
3103  return _ottavas[d._nr];
3104  else if (d._tp == ElementType::PEDAL && 0 == d._nr)
3105  return _pedal;
3106  else if (d._tp == ElementType::TEXTLINE && 0 <= d._nr && d._nr < MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL)
3107  return _brackets[d._nr];
3108  _logger->logError(QString("invalid number %1").arg(d._nr + 1), &_e);
3109  return _dummyNewMusicXmlSpannerDesc;
3110  }

3120  }

3122 //---------------------------------------------------------
3123 // metronome
3124 //---------------------------------------------------------
3125 
3126 /**
3127  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/direction/direction-type/metronome node.
3128  Convert to text and set r to calculated tempo.
3129  */
3130 
3131 QString MusicXMLParserDirection::metronome(double& r)
3132  {
3133  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "metronome");
3134 
3135  r = 0;
3136  QString tempoText;
3137  QString perMinute;
3138  bool parenth = _e.attributes().value("parentheses") == "yes";
3139 
3140  if (parenth)
3141  tempoText += "(";
3142 
3143  TDuration dur1;
3144  TDuration dur2;
3145 
3146  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
3147  if (_e.name() == "metronome-note" || _e.name() == "metronome-relation") {
3148  skipLogCurrElem();
3149  continue;
3150  }
3151  QString txt = _e.readElementText();
3152  if (_e.name() == "beat-unit") {
3153  // set first dur that is still invalid
3154  if (!dur1.isValid()) dur1.setType(txt);
3155  else if (!dur2.isValid()) dur2.setType(txt);
3156  }
3157  else if (_e.name() == "beat-unit-dot") {
3158  if (dur2.isValid()) dur2.setDots(1);
3159  else if (dur1.isValid()) dur1.setDots(1);
3160  }
3161  else if (_e.name() == "per-minute")
3162  perMinute = txt;
3163  else
3164  skipLogCurrElem();
3165  }
3166 
3167  if (dur1.isValid())
3168  tempoText += TempoText::duration2tempoTextString(dur1);
3169  if (dur2.isValid()) {
3170  tempoText += " = ";
3171  tempoText += TempoText::duration2tempoTextString(dur2);
3172  }
3173  else if (perMinute != "") {
3174  tempoText += " = ";
3175  tempoText += perMinute;
3176  }
3177  if (dur1.isValid() && !dur2.isValid() && perMinute != "") {
3178  bool ok;
3179  double d = perMinute.toDouble(&ok);
3180  if (ok) {
3181  // convert fraction to beats per minute
3182  r = 4 * dur1.fraction().numerator() * d / dur1.fraction().denominator();
3183  }
3184  }
3185 
3186  if (parenth)
3187  tempoText += ")";
3188 
3189  return tempoText;
3190  }

3192 //---------------------------------------------------------
3193 // determineBarLineType
3194 //---------------------------------------------------------
3195 
3196 static bool determineBarLineType(const QString& barStyle, const QString& repeat,
3197  BarLineType& type, bool& visible)
3198  {
3199  // set defaults
3200  type = BarLineType::NORMAL;
3201  visible = true;
3202 
3203  if (barStyle == "light-heavy" && repeat == "backward")
3204  type = BarLineType::END_REPEAT;
3205  else if (barStyle == "heavy-light" && repeat == "forward")
3206  type = BarLineType::START_REPEAT;
3207  else if (barStyle == "light-heavy" && repeat.isEmpty())
3208  type = BarLineType::END;
3209  else if (barStyle == "heavy-light" && repeat.isEmpty())
3210  type = BarLineType::REVERSE_END;
3211  else if (barStyle == "regular")
3212  type = BarLineType::NORMAL;
3213  else if (barStyle == "dashed")
3214  type = BarLineType::BROKEN;
3215  else if (barStyle == "dotted")
3216  type = BarLineType::DOTTED;
3217  else if (barStyle == "light-light")
3218  type = BarLineType::DOUBLE;
3219  /*
3220  else if (barStyle == "heavy-light")
3221  ;
3222  */
3223  else if (barStyle == "heavy-heavy")
3224  type = BarLineType::DOUBLE_HEAVY;
3225  else if (barStyle == "heavy")
3226  type = BarLineType::HEAVY;
3227  else if (barStyle == "none")
3228  visible = false;
3229  else if (barStyle == "") {
3230  if (repeat == "backward")
3231  type = BarLineType::END_REPEAT;
3232  else if (repeat == "forward")
3233  type = BarLineType::START_REPEAT;
3234  else {
3235  qDebug("empty bar type"); // TODO
3236  return false;
3237  }
3238  }
3239  else if ((barStyle == "tick") || (barStyle == "short")) {
3240  // handled later (as normal barline with different parameters)
3241  }
3242  else {
3243  qDebug("unsupported bar type <%s>", qPrintable(barStyle)); // TODO
3244  return false;
3245  }
3246 
3247  return true;
3248  }

3254 /*
3255  * Create a barline of the specified type.
3256  */
3257 
3258 static std::unique_ptr<BarLine> createBarline(Score* score, const int track, const BarLineType type, const bool visible, const QString& barStyle)
3259  {
3260  std::unique_ptr<BarLine> barline(new BarLine(score));
3261  barline->setTrack(track);
3262  barline->setBarLineType(type);
3263  barline->setSpanStaff(0);
3264  barline->setVisible(visible);
3265  if (barStyle == "tick") {
3266  barline->setSpanFrom(BARLINE_SPAN_TICK1_FROM);
3267  barline->setSpanTo(BARLINE_SPAN_TICK1_TO);
3268  }
3269  else if (barStyle == "short") {
3270  barline->setSpanFrom(BARLINE_SPAN_SHORT1_FROM);
3271  barline->setSpanTo(BARLINE_SPAN_SHORT1_TO);
3272  }
3273  return barline;
3274  }

3278 //---------------------------------------------------------
3279 
3280 /*
3281  * Add barline to the measure at tick.
3282  */
3283 
3284 static void addBarlineToMeasure(Measure* measure, const Fraction tick, std::unique_ptr<BarLine> barline)
3285  {
3286  auto st = SegmentType::BarLine;
3287  if (tick == measure->endTick())
3288  st = SegmentType::EndBarLine;
3289  else if (tick == measure->tick())
3290  st = SegmentType::BeginBarLine;
3291  const auto segment = measure->getSegment(st, tick);
3292  barline->layout();
3293  segment->add(barline.release());
3294  }

3296 //---------------------------------------------------------
3297 // barline
3298 //---------------------------------------------------------
3299 
3300 /**
3301  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/barline node.
3302  */
3303 
3304 /*
3305  Following barline types are automatically generated by MuseScore in an EndBarLine segment at the end of a measure:
3306  - normal (excluding tick and short)
3307  - start repeat
3308  - end-start repeat
3309  - end repeat
3310  - final (at the end of the score only)
3311  The other barline types can also be in an EndBarLine segment at the end of a measure, but are NOT generated
3312  Mid-measure barlines are in a BarLine segment and are NOT generated
3313  Following barline types can only be at the end of a measure:
3314  - start repeat
3315  - end-start repeat
3316  - end repeat
3317  - final
3318  */
3319 
3320 void MusicXMLParserPass2::barline(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
3321  {
3322  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "barline");
3323 
3324  QString loc = _e.attributes().value("location").toString();
3325  if (loc == "")
3326  loc = "right";
3327  QString barStyle;
3328  QString endingNumber;
3329  QString endingType;
3330  QString endingText;
3331  QString repeat;
3332  QString count;
3333 
3334  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
3335  if (_e.name() == "bar-style")
3336  barStyle = _e.readElementText();
3337  else if (_e.name() == "ending") {
3338  endingNumber = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
3339  endingType = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
3340  endingText = _e.readElementText();
3341  }
3342  else if (_e.name() == "repeat") {
3343  repeat = _e.attributes().value("direction").toString();
3344  count = _e.attributes().value("times").toString();
3345  if (count.isEmpty()) {
3346  count = "2";
3347  }
3348  measure->setRepeatCount(count.toInt());
3349  _e.skipCurrentElement();
3350  }
3351  else
3352  skipLogCurrElem();
3353  }
3354 
3355  BarLineType type = BarLineType::NORMAL;
3356  bool visible = true;
3357  if (determineBarLineType(barStyle, repeat, type, visible)) {
3358  const auto track = _pass1.trackForPart(partId);
3359  if (type == BarLineType::START_REPEAT) {
3360  // combine start_repeat flag with current state initialized during measure parsing
3361  measure->setRepeatStart(true);
3362  }
3363  else if (type == BarLineType::END_REPEAT) {
3364  // combine end_repeat flag with current state initialized during measure parsing
3365  measure->setRepeatEnd(true);
3366  }
3367  else if (type == BarLineType::END) {
3368  measure->setEndBarLineType(type, track, visible);
3369  }
3370  else {
3371  if (barStyle == "tick"
3372  || barStyle == "short"
3373  || barStyle == "none"
3374  || barStyle == "dashed"
3375  || barStyle == "dotted"
3376  || barStyle == "light-light"
3377  || barStyle == "regular") {
3378  auto b = createBarline(measure->score(), track, type, visible, barStyle);
3379  addBarlineToMeasure(measure, tick, std::move(b));
3380  }
3381  }
3382  }
3383 
3384  doEnding(partId, measure, endingNumber, endingType, endingText);
3385  }

3387 //---------------------------------------------------------
3388 // doEnding
3389 //---------------------------------------------------------
3390 
3391 void MusicXMLParserPass2::doEnding(const QString& partId, Measure* measure,
3392  const QString& number, const QString& type, const QString& text)
3393  {
3394  if (!(number.isEmpty() && type.isEmpty())) {
3395  if (number.isEmpty())
3396  _logger->logError("empty ending number", &_e);
3397  else if (type.isEmpty())
3398  _logger->logError("empty ending type", &_e);
3399  else {
3400  QStringList sl = number.split(",", QString::SkipEmptyParts);
3401  QList<int> iEndingNumbers;
3402  bool unsupported = false;
3403  foreach(const QString &s, sl) {
3404  int iEndingNumber = s.toInt();
3405  if (iEndingNumber <= 0) {
3406  unsupported = true;
3407  break;
3408  }
3409  iEndingNumbers.append(iEndingNumber);
3410  }
3411 
3412  if (unsupported)
3413  _logger->logError(QString("unsupported ending number '%1'").arg(number), &_e);
3414  else {
3415  if (type == "start") {
3416  Volta* volta = new Volta(_score);
3417  volta->setTrack(_pass1.trackForPart(partId));
3418  volta->setText(text.isEmpty() ? number : text);
3419  // LVIFIX TODO also support endings "1 - 3"
3420  volta->endings().clear();
3421  volta->endings().append(iEndingNumbers);
3422  volta->setTick(measure->tick());
3423  _score->addElement(volta);
3424  _lastVolta = volta;
3425  }
3426  else if (type == "stop") {
3427  if (_lastVolta) {
3428  _lastVolta->setVoltaType(Volta::Type::CLOSED);
3429  _lastVolta->setTick2(measure->tick() + measure->ticks());
3430  _lastVolta = 0;
3431  }
3432  else
3433  _logger->logError("ending stop without start", &_e);
3434  }
3435  else if (type == "discontinue") {
3436  if (_lastVolta) {
3437  _lastVolta->setVoltaType(Volta::Type::OPEN);
3438  _lastVolta->setTick2(measure->tick() + measure->ticks());
3439  _lastVolta = 0;
3440  }
3441  else
3442  _logger->logError("ending discontinue without start", &_e);
3443  }
3444  else
3445  _logger->logError(QString("unsupported ending type '%1'").arg(type), &_e);
3446  }
3447  }
3448  }
3449  }

3451 //---------------------------------------------------------
3452 // addSymToSig
3453 //---------------------------------------------------------
3454 
3455 /**
3456  Add a symbol defined as key-step \a step , -alter \a alter and -accidental \a accid to \a sig.
3457  */
3458 
3459 static void addSymToSig(KeySigEvent& sig, const QString& step, const QString& alter, const QString& accid)
3460  {
3461  //qDebug("addSymToSig(step '%s' alt '%s' acc '%s')",
3462  // qPrintable(step), qPrintable(alter), qPrintable(accid));
3463 
3464  SymId id = mxmlString2accSymId(accid);
3465  if (id == SymId::noSym) {
3466  bool ok;
3467  double d;
3468  d = alter.toDouble(&ok);
3469  AccidentalType accTpAlter = ok ? microtonalGuess(d) : AccidentalType::NONE;
3470  id = mxmlString2accSymId(accidentalType2MxmlString(accTpAlter));
3471  }
3472 
3473  if (step.size() == 1 && id != SymId::noSym) {
3474  const QString table = "FEDCBAG";
3475  const int line = table.indexOf(step);
3476  // no auto layout for custom keysig, calculate xpos
3477  // TODO: use symbol width ?
3478  const qreal spread = 1.4; // assumed glyph width in space
3479  const qreal x = sig.keySymbols().size() * spread;
3480  if (line >= 0) {
3481  KeySym ks;
3482  ks.sym = id;
3483  ks.spos = QPointF(x, qreal(line) * 0.5);
3484  sig.keySymbols().append(ks);
3485  sig.setCustom(true);
3486  }
3487  }
3488  }

3494 /**
3495  Add a KeySigEvent to the score.
3496  */
3497 
3498 static void addKey(const KeySigEvent key, const bool printObj, Score* score, Measure* measure, const int staffIdx, const Fraction& tick)
3499  {
3500  Key oldkey = score->staff(staffIdx)->key(tick);
3501  // TODO only if different custom key ?
3502  if (oldkey != key.key() || key.custom() || key.isAtonal()) {
3503  // new key differs from key in effect at this tick
3504  KeySig* keysig = new KeySig(score);
3505  keysig->setTrack((staffIdx) * VOICES);
3506  keysig->setKeySigEvent(key);
3507  keysig->setVisible(printObj);
3508  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::KeySig, tick);
3509  s->add(keysig);
3510  //currKeySig->setKeySigEvent(key);
3511  }
3512  }

3514 //---------------------------------------------------------
3515 // flushAlteredTone
3516 //---------------------------------------------------------
3517 
3518 /**
3519  If a valid key-step, -alter, -accidental combination has been read,
3520  convert it to a key symbol and add to the key.
3521  Clear key-step, -alter, -accidental.
3522  */
3523 
3524 static void flushAlteredTone(KeySigEvent& kse, QString& step, QString& alt, QString& acc)
3525  {
3526  //qDebug("flushAlteredTone(step '%s' alt '%s' acc '%s')",
3527  // qPrintable(step), qPrintable(alt), qPrintable(acc));
3528 
3529  if (step == "" && alt == "" && acc == "")
3530  return; // nothing to do
3531 
3532  // step and alt are required, but also accept step and acc
3533  if (step != "" && (alt != "" || acc != "")) {
3534  addSymToSig(kse, step, alt, acc);
3535  }
3536  else {
3537  qDebug("flushAlteredTone invalid combination of step '%s' alt '%s' acc '%s')",
3538  qPrintable(step), qPrintable(alt), qPrintable(acc)); // TODO
3539  }
3540 
3541  // clean up
3542  step = "";
3543  alt = "";
3544  acc = "";
3545  }

3547 //---------------------------------------------------------
3548 // key
3549 //---------------------------------------------------------
3550 
3551 /**
3552  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes/key node.
3553  */
3554 
3555 // TODO: check currKeySig handling
3556 
3557 void MusicXMLParserPass2::key(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
3558  {
3559  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "key");
3560 
3561  QString strKeyno = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
3562  int keyno = -1; // assume no number (see below)
3563  if (strKeyno != "") {
3564  keyno = strKeyno.toInt();
3565  if (keyno == 0) {
3566  // conversion error (0), assume staff 1
3567  _logger->logError(QString("invalid key number '%1'").arg(strKeyno), &_e);
3568  keyno = 1;
3569  }
3570  // convert to 0-based
3571  keyno--;
3572  }
3573  bool printObject = _e.attributes().value("print-object") != "no";
3574 
3575  // for custom keys, a single altered tone is described by
3576  // key-step (required), key-alter (required) and key-accidental (optional)
3577  // none, one or more altered tone may be present
3578  // a simple state machine is required to detect them
3579  KeySigEvent key;
3580  QString keyStep;
3581  QString keyAlter;
3582  QString keyAccidental;
3583 
3584  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
3585  if (_e.name() == "fifths")
3586  key.setKey(Key(_e.readElementText().toInt()));
3587  else if (_e.name() == "mode") {
3588  QString m = _e.readElementText();
3589  if (m == "none") {
3590  key.setCustom(true);
3591  key.setMode(KeyMode::NONE);
3592  }
3593  else if (m == "major")
3594  key.setMode(KeyMode::MAJOR);
3595  else if (m == "minor")
3596  key.setMode(KeyMode::MINOR);
3597  else if (m == "dorian")
3598  key.setMode(KeyMode::DORIAN);
3599  else if (m == "phrygian")
3600  key.setMode(KeyMode::PHRYGIAN);
3601  else if (m == "lydian")
3602  key.setMode(KeyMode::LYDIAN);
3603  else if (m == "mixolydian")
3604  key.setMode(KeyMode::MIXOLYDIAN);
3605  else if (m == "aeolian")
3606  key.setMode(KeyMode::AEOLIAN);
3607  else if (m == "ionian")
3608  key.setMode(KeyMode::IONIAN);
3609  else if (m == "locrian")
3610  key.setMode(KeyMode::LOCRIAN);
3611  else
3612  _logger->logError(QString("Unsupported mode '%1'").arg(m), &_e);
3613  }
3614  else if (_e.name() == "cancel")
3615  skipLogCurrElem(); // TODO ??
3616  else if (_e.name() == "key-step") {
3617  flushAlteredTone(key, keyStep, keyAlter, keyAccidental);
3618  keyStep = _e.readElementText();
3619  }
3620  else if (_e.name() == "key-alter")
3621  keyAlter = _e.readElementText();
3622  else if (_e.name() == "key-accidental")
3623  keyAccidental = _e.readElementText();
3624  else
3625  skipLogCurrElem();
3626  }
3627  flushAlteredTone(key, keyStep, keyAlter, keyAccidental);
3628 
3629  int nstaves = _pass1.getPart(partId)->nstaves();
3630  int staffIdx = _pass1.trackForPart(partId) / VOICES;
3631  if (keyno == -1) {
3632  // apply key to all staves in the part
3633  for (int i = 0; i < nstaves; ++i) {
3634  addKey(key, printObject, _score, measure, staffIdx + i, tick);
3635  }
3636  }
3637  else if (keyno < nstaves)
3638  addKey(key, printObject, _score, measure, staffIdx + keyno, tick);
3639  }
3640 
3641 //---------------------------------------------------------
3642 // clef
3643 //---------------------------------------------------------
3644 
3645 /**
3646  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes/clef node.
3647  */
3648 
3649 void MusicXMLParserPass2::clef(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
3650  {
3651  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "clef");
3652 
3653  Part* part = _pass1.getPart(partId);
3654  Q_ASSERT(part);
3655 
3656  // TODO: check error handling for
3657  // - single staff
3658  // - multi-staff with same clef
3659  QString strClefno = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
3660  const bool afterBarline = _e.attributes().value("after-barline") == "yes";
3661  int clefno = 1; // default
3662  if (strClefno != "")
3663  clefno = strClefno.toInt();
3664  if (clefno <= 0 || clefno > part->nstaves()) {
3665  // conversion error (0) or other issue, assume staff 1
3666  // Also for Cubase 6.5.5 which generates clef number="2" in a single staff part
3667  // Same fix is required in pass 1 and pass 2
3668  _logger->logError(QString("invalid clef number '%1'").arg(strClefno), &_e);
3669  clefno = 1;
3670  }
3671  // convert to 0-based
3672  clefno--;
3673 
3674  ClefType clef = ClefType::G;
3675  StaffTypes st = StaffTypes::STANDARD;
3676 
3677  QString c;
3678  int i = 0;
3679  int line = -1;
3680 
3681  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
3682  if (_e.name() == "sign")
3683  c = _e.readElementText();
3684  else if (_e.name() == "line")
3685  line = _e.readElementText().toInt();
3686  else if (_e.name() == "clef-octave-change") {
3687  i = _e.readElementText().toInt();
3688  if (i && !(c == "F" || c == "G"))
3689  qDebug("clef-octave-change only implemented for F and G key"); // TODO
3690  }
3691  else
3692  skipLogCurrElem();
3693  }
3694 
3695  //some software (Primus) don't include line and assume some default
3696  // it's permitted by MusicXML 2.0 XSD
3697  if (line == -1) {
3698  if (c == "G")
3699  line = 2;
3700  else if (c == "F")
3701  line = 4;
3702  else if (c == "C")
3703  line = 3;
3704  }
3705 
3706  if (c == "G" && i == 0 && line == 2)
3707  clef = ClefType::G;
3708  else if (c == "G" && i == 1 && line == 2)
3709  clef = ClefType::G8_VA;
3710  else if (c == "G" && i == 2 && line == 2)
3711  clef = ClefType::G15_MA;
3712  else if (c == "G" && i == -1 && line == 2)
3713  clef = ClefType::G8_VB;
3714  else if (c == "G" && i == 0 && line == 1)
3715  clef = ClefType::G_1;
3716  else if (c == "F" && i == 0 && line == 3)
3717  clef = ClefType::F_B;
3718  else if (c == "F" && i == 0 && line == 4)
3719  clef = ClefType::F;
3720  else if (c == "F" && i == 1 && line == 4)
3721  clef = ClefType::F_8VA;
3722  else if (c == "F" && i == 2 && line == 4)
3723  clef = ClefType::F_15MA;
3724  else if (c == "F" && i == -1 && line == 4)
3725  clef = ClefType::F8_VB;
3726  else if (c == "F" && i == -2 && line == 4)
3727  clef = ClefType::F15_MB;
3728  else if (c == "F" && i == 0 && line == 5)
3729  clef = ClefType::F_C;
3730  else if (c == "C") {
3731  if (line == 5)
3732  clef = ClefType::C5;
3733  else if (line == 4)
3734  clef = ClefType::C4;
3735  else if (line == 3)
3736  clef = ClefType::C3;
3737  else if (line == 2)
3738  clef = ClefType::C2;
3739  else if (line == 1)
3740  clef = ClefType::C1;
3741  }
3742  else if (c == "percussion") {
3743  clef = ClefType::PERC;
3744  if (_hasDrumset) {
3745  st = StaffTypes::PERC_DEFAULT;
3746  }
3747  }
3748  else if (c == "TAB") {
3749  clef = ClefType::TAB;
3750  st= StaffTypes::TAB_DEFAULT;
3751  }
3752  else
3753  qDebug("clef: unknown clef <sign=%s line=%d oct ch=%d>", qPrintable(c), line, i); // TODO
3754 
3755  Clef* clefs = new Clef(_score);
3756  clefs->setClefType(clef);
3757  int track = _pass1.trackForPart(partId) + clefno * VOICES;
3758  clefs->setTrack(track);
3759  Segment* s;
3760  // check if the clef change needs to be in the previous measure
3761  if (!afterBarline && (tick == measure->tick()) && measure->prevMeasure())
3762  s = measure->prevMeasure()->getSegment(SegmentType::Clef, tick);
3763  else
3764  s = measure->getSegment(tick.isNotZero() ? SegmentType::Clef : SegmentType::HeaderClef, tick);
3765  s->add(clefs);
3766 
3767  // set the correct staff type
3768  // note that clef handling should probably done in pass1
3769  int staffIdx = _score->staffIdx(part) + clefno;
3770  int lines = _score->staff(staffIdx)->lines(Fraction(0,1));
3771  if (tick.isZero()) { // changing staff type not supported (yet ?)
3772  _score->staff(staffIdx)->setStaffType(tick, *StaffType::preset(st));
3773  _score->staff(staffIdx)->setLines(tick, lines); // preserve previously set staff lines
3774  _score->staff(staffIdx)->setBarLineTo(0); // default
3775  }
3776  }
3777 
3778 //---------------------------------------------------------
3779 // determineTimeSig
3780 //---------------------------------------------------------
3781 
3782 /**
3783  Determine the time signature based on \a beats, \a beatType and \a timeSymbol.
3784  Sets return parameters \a st, \a bts, \a btp.
3785  Return true if OK, false on error.
3786  */
3787 
3788 // TODO: share between pass 1 and pass 2
3789 
3790 static bool determineTimeSig(const QString beats, const QString beatType, const QString timeSymbol,
3791  TimeSigType& st, int& bts, int& btp)
3792  {
3793  // initialize
3794  st = TimeSigType::NORMAL;
3795  bts = 0; // the beats (max 4 separated by "+") as integer
3796  btp = 0; // beat-type as integer
3797  // determine if timesig is valid
3798  if (beats == "2" && beatType == "2" && timeSymbol == "cut") {
3799  st = TimeSigType::ALLA_BREVE;
3800  bts = 2;
3801  btp = 2;
3802  return true;
3803  }
3804  else if (beats == "4" && beatType == "4" && timeSymbol == "common") {
3805  st = TimeSigType::FOUR_FOUR;
3806  bts = 4;
3807  btp = 4;
3808  return true;
3809  }
3810  else if (beats == "2" && beatType == "2" && timeSymbol == "cut2") {
3811  st = TimeSigType::CUT_BACH;
3812  bts = 2;
3813  btp = 2;
3814  return true;
3815  }
3816  else if (beats == "9" && beatType == "8" && timeSymbol == "cut3") {
3817  st = TimeSigType::CUT_TRIPLE;
3818  bts = 9;
3819  btp = 8;
3820  return true;
3821  }
3822  else {
3823  if (!timeSymbol.isEmpty() && timeSymbol != "normal") {
3824  qDebug("determineTimeSig: time symbol <%s> not recognized with beats=%s and beat-type=%s",
3825  qPrintable(timeSymbol), qPrintable(beats), qPrintable(beatType)); // TODO
3826  return false;
3827  }
3828 
3829  btp = beatType.toInt();
3830  QStringList list = beats.split("+");
3831  for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++)
3832  bts += list.at(i).toInt();
3833  }
3834 
3835  // determine if bts and btp are valid
3836  if (bts <= 0 || btp <=0) {
3837  qDebug("determineTimeSig: beats=%s and/or beat-type=%s not recognized",
3838  qPrintable(beats), qPrintable(beatType)); // TODO
3839  return false;
3840  }
3841 
3842  return true;
3843  }
3844 
3845 //---------------------------------------------------------
3846 // time
3847 //---------------------------------------------------------
3848 
3849 /**
3850  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/attributes/time node.
3851  */
3852 
3853 void MusicXMLParserPass2::time(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction& tick)
3854  {
3855  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "time");
3856 
3857  QString beats;
3858  QString beatType;
3859  QString timeSymbol = _e.attributes().value("symbol").toString();
3860  bool printObject = _e.attributes().value("print-object") != "no";
3861 
3862  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
3863  if (_e.name() == "beats")
3864  beats = _e.readElementText();
3865  else if (_e.name() == "beat-type")
3866  beatType = _e.readElementText();
3867  else
3868  skipLogCurrElem();
3869  }
3870 
3871  if (beats != "" && beatType != "") {
3872  // determine if timesig is valid
3873  TimeSigType st = TimeSigType::NORMAL;
3874  int bts = 0; // total beats as integer (beats may contain multiple numbers, separated by "+")
3875  int btp = 0; // beat-type as integer
3876  if (determineTimeSig(beats, beatType, timeSymbol, st, bts, btp)) {
3877  _timeSigDura = Fraction(bts, btp);
3878  Fraction fractionTSig = Fraction(bts, btp);
3879  for (int i = 0; i < _pass1.getPart(partId)->nstaves(); ++i) {
3880  TimeSig* timesig = new TimeSig(_score);
3881  timesig->setVisible(printObject);
3882  int track = _pass1.trackForPart(partId) + i * VOICES;
3883  timesig->setTrack(track);
3884  timesig->setSig(fractionTSig, st);
3885  // handle simple compound time signature
3886  if (beats.contains(QChar('+'))) {
3887  timesig->setNumeratorString(beats);
3888  timesig->setDenominatorString(beatType);
3889  }
3890  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, tick);
3891  s->add(timesig);
3892  }
3893  }
3894  }
3895  }

3914 //---------------------------------------------------------
3915 // isWholeMeasureRest
3916 //---------------------------------------------------------
3917 
3918 /**
3919  * Determine whole measure rest.
3920  */
3921 
3922 // By convention, whole measure rests do not have a "type" element
3923 // As of MusicXML 3.0, this can be indicated by an attribute "measure",
3924 // but for backwards compatibility the "old" convention still has to be supported.
3925 // Also verify the rest fits exactly in the measure, as some programs
3926 // (e.g. Cakewalk SONAR X2 Studio [Version: 19.0.0.306]) leave out
3927 // the type for all rests.
3928 // Sibelius calls all whole-measure rests "whole", even if the duration != 4/4
3929 
3930 static bool isWholeMeasureRest(const bool rest, const QString& type, const Fraction dura, const Fraction mDura)
3931  {
3932  if (!rest)
3933  return false;
3934 
3935  if (!dura.isValid())
3936  return false;
3937 
3938  if (!mDura.isValid())
3939  return false;
3940 
3941  return ((type == "" && dura == mDura)
3942  || (type == "whole" && dura == mDura && dura != Fraction(1, 1)));
3943  }
3944 
3945 //---------------------------------------------------------
3946 // determineDuration
3947 //---------------------------------------------------------
3948 
3949 /**
3950  * Determine duration for a note or rest.
3951  * This includes whole measure rest detection.
3952  */
3953 
3954 static TDuration determineDuration(const bool rest, const QString& type, const int dots, const Fraction dura, const Fraction mDura)
3955  {
3956  //qDebug("determineDuration rest %d type '%s' dots %d dura %s mDura %s",
3957  // rest, qPrintable(type), dots, qPrintable(dura.print()), qPrintable(mDura.print()));
3958 
3959  TDuration res;
3960  if (rest) {
3961  if (isWholeMeasureRest(rest, type, dura, mDura))
3962  res.setType(TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE);
3963  else if (type == "") {
3964  // If no type, set duration type based on duration.
3965  // Note that sometimes unusual duration (e.g. 261/256) are found.
3966  res.setVal(dura.ticks());
3967  }
3968  else {
3969  res.setType(type);
3970  res.setDots(dots);
3971  }
3972  }
3973  else {
3974  res.setType(type);
3975  res.setDots(dots);
3976  if (res.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_INVALID)
3977  res.setType(TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER); // default, TODO: use dura ?
3978  }
3979 
3980  //qDebug("-> dur %hhd (%s) dots %d ticks %s",
3981  // res.type(), qPrintable(res.name()), res.dots(), qPrintable(dura.print()));
3982 
3983  return res;
3984  }

3986 //---------------------------------------------------------
3987 // findOrCreateChord
3988 //---------------------------------------------------------
3989 
3990 /**
3991  * Find (or create if not found) the chord at \a tick and \a track.
3992  * Note: staff move is a note property in MusicXML, but chord property in MuseScore
3993  * This is simply ignored here, effectively using the last chords value.
3994  */
3995 
3996 static Chord* findOrCreateChord(Score* score, Measure* m,
3997  const Fraction& tick, const int track, const int move,
3998  const TDuration duration, const Fraction dura,
3999  Beam::Mode bm)
4000  {
4001  //qDebug("findOrCreateChord tick %d track %d dur ticks %d ticks %s bm %hhd",
4002  // tick, track, duration.ticks(), qPrintable(dura.print()), bm);
4003  Chord* c = m->findChord(tick, track);
4004  if (c == 0) {
4005  c = new Chord(score);
4006  if (bm == Beam::Mode::END)
4007  // The beam palette does not support beam END, use MID instead which means "beam
4008  // current note together with previous note".
4009  c->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::MID);
4010  else
4011  c->setBeamMode(bm);
4012  c->setTrack(track);
4013 
4014  setChordRestDuration(c, duration, dura);
4015  Segment* s = m->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, tick);
4016  s->add(c);
4017  }
4018  c->setStaffMove(move);
4019  return c;
4020  }

4022 //---------------------------------------------------------
4023 // graceNoteType
4024 //---------------------------------------------------------
4025 
4026 /**
4027  * convert duration and slash to grace note type
4028  */
4029 
4030 NoteType graceNoteType(const TDuration duration, const bool slash)
4031  {
4032  NoteType nt = NoteType::APPOGGIATURA;
4033  if (slash)
4034  nt = NoteType::ACCIACCATURA;
4035  if (duration.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER) {
4036  nt = NoteType::GRACE4;
4037  }
4038  else if (duration.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_16TH) {
4039  nt = NoteType::GRACE16;
4040  }
4041  else if (duration.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_32ND) {
4042  nt = NoteType::GRACE32;
4043  }
4044  return nt;
4045  }

4066 //---------------------------------------------------------
4067 // handleDisplayStep
4068 //---------------------------------------------------------
4069 
4070 /**
4071  * convert display-step and display-octave to staff line
4072  */
4073 
4074 static void handleDisplayStep(ChordRest* cr, int step, int octave, const Fraction& tick, qreal spatium)
4075  {
4076  if (0 <= step && step <= 6 && 0 <= octave && octave <= 9) {
4077  //qDebug("rest step=%d oct=%d", step, octave);
4078  ClefType clef = cr->staff()->clef(tick);
4079  int po = ClefInfo::pitchOffset(clef);
4080  //qDebug(" clef=%hhd po=%d step=%d", clef, po, step);
4081  int dp = 7 * (octave + 2) + step;
4082  //qDebug(" dp=%d po-dp=%d", dp, po-dp);
4083  cr->ryoffset() = (po - dp + 3) * spatium / 2;
4084  }
4085  }

4095 static void setNoteHead(Note* note, const QColor noteheadColor, const bool noteheadParentheses, const QString& noteheadFilled)
4096  {

4098 
4099  if (noteheadColor != QColor::Invalid)
4100  note->setColor(noteheadColor);
4101  if (noteheadParentheses) {
4102  auto s = new Symbol(score);
4103  s->setSym(SymId::noteheadParenthesisLeft);
4104  s->setParent(note);
4105  score->addElement(s);
4106  s = new Symbol(score);
4107  s->setSym(SymId::noteheadParenthesisRight);
4108  s->setParent(note);
4109  score->addElement(s);
4110  }
4111 
4112  if (noteheadFilled == "no")
4113  note->setHeadType(NoteHead::Type::HEAD_HALF);
4114  else if (noteheadFilled == "yes")
4115  note->setHeadType(NoteHead::Type::HEAD_QUARTER);
4116  }

4119 // addFiguredBassElemens
4120 //---------------------------------------------------------
4121 
4122 /**
4123  Add the figured bass elements.
4124  */
4125 
4126 static void addFiguredBassElemens(FiguredBassList& fbl, const Fraction noteStartTime, const int msTrack,
4127  const Fraction dura, Measure* measure)
4128  {
4129  if (!fbl.isEmpty()) {
4130  auto sTick = noteStartTime; // starting tick
4131  foreach (FiguredBass* fb, fbl) {
4132  fb->setTrack(msTrack);
4133  // No duration tag defaults ticks() to 0; set to note value
4134  if (fb->ticks().isZero())
4135  fb->setTicks(dura);
4136  // TODO: set correct onNote value
4137  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, sTick);
4138  s->add(fb);
4139  sTick += fb->ticks();
4140  }
4141  fbl.clear();
4142  }
4143  }

4145 //---------------------------------------------------------
4146 // addTremolo
4147 //---------------------------------------------------------
4148 
4149 static void addTremolo(ChordRest* cr,
4150  const int tremoloNr, const QString& tremoloType,
4151  Chord*& tremStart,
4152  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader,
4153  Fraction& timeMod)
4154  {
4155  if (!cr->isChord())
4156  return;
4157  if (tremoloNr) {
4158  //qDebug("tremolo %d type '%s' ticks %d tremStart %p", tremoloNr, qPrintable(tremoloType), ticks, _tremStart);
4159  if (tremoloNr == 1 || tremoloNr == 2 || tremoloNr == 3 || tremoloNr == 4) {
4160  if (tremoloType == "" || tremoloType == "single") {
4161  const auto tremolo = new Tremolo(cr->score());
4162  switch (tremoloNr) {
4163  case 1: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::R8); break;
4164  case 2: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::R16); break;
4165  case 3: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::R32); break;
4166  case 4: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::R64); break;
4167  }
4168  cr->add(tremolo);
4169  }
4170  else if (tremoloType == "start") {
4171  if (tremStart) logger->logError("MusicXML::import: double tremolo start", xmlreader);
4172  tremStart = static_cast<Chord*>(cr);
4173  // timeMod takes into account also the factor 2 of a two-note tremolo
4174  if (timeMod.isValid() && ((timeMod.denominator() % 2) == 0)) {
4175  timeMod.setDenominator(timeMod.denominator() / 2);
4176  }
4177  }
4178  else if (tremoloType == "stop") {
4179  if (tremStart) {
4180  const auto tremolo = new Tremolo(cr->score());
4181  switch (tremoloNr) {
4182  case 1: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::C8); break;
4183  case 2: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::C16); break;
4184  case 3: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::C32); break;
4185  case 4: tremolo->setTremoloType(TremoloType::C64); break;
4186  }
4187  tremolo->setChords(tremStart, static_cast<Chord*>(cr));
4188  // fixup chord duration and type
4189  const Fraction tremDur = cr->ticks() * Fraction(1,2);
4190  tremolo->chord1()->setDurationType(tremDur);
4191  tremolo->chord1()->setTicks(tremDur);
4192  tremolo->chord2()->setDurationType(tremDur);
4193  tremolo->chord2()->setTicks(tremDur);
4194  // add tremolo to first chord (only)
4195  tremStart->add(tremolo);
4196  // timeMod takes into account also the factor 2 of a two-note tremolo
4197  if (timeMod.isValid() && ((timeMod.denominator() % 2) == 0)) {
4198  timeMod.setDenominator(timeMod.denominator() / 2);
4199  }
4200  }
4201  else logger->logError("MusicXML::import: double tremolo stop w/o start", xmlreader);
4202  tremStart = nullptr;
4203  }
4204  }
4205  else
4206  logger->logError(QString("unknown tremolo type %1").arg(tremoloNr), xmlreader);
4207  }
4208  }

4211 // setPitch
4212 //---------------------------------------------------------
4213 
4214 // TODO: refactor: optimize parameters
4215 
4216 static void setPitch(Note* note, MusicXMLParserPass1& pass1, const QString& partId, const QString& instrumentId, const mxmlNotePitch& mnp, const int octaveShift, const Instrument* const instrument)
4217  {
4218  const auto& instruments = pass1.getInstruments(partId);
4219  if (mnp.unpitched()) {
4220  if (hasDrumset(instruments)
4221  && instruments.contains(instrumentId)) {
4222  // step and oct are display-step and ...-oct
4223  // get pitch from instrument definition in drumset instead
4224  int unpitched = instruments[instrumentId].unpitched;
4225  note->setPitch(limit(unpitched, 0, 127));
4226  // TODO - does this need to be key-aware?
4227  note->setTpc(pitch2tpc(unpitched, Key::C, Prefer::NEAREST)); // TODO: necessary ?
4228  }
4229  else {
4230  //qDebug("disp step %d oct %d", displayStep, displayOctave);
4231  xmlSetPitch(note, mnp.displayStep(), 0, mnp.displayOctave(), 0, instrument);
4232  }
4233  }
4234  else {
4235  xmlSetPitch(note, mnp.step(), mnp.alter(), mnp.octave(), octaveShift, instrument);
4236  }
4237  }
4238 
4239 //---------------------------------------------------------
4240 // setDrumset
4241 //---------------------------------------------------------
4242 
4243 // set drumset information
4244 // note that in MuseScore, the drumset contains defaults for notehead,
4245 // line and stem direction, while a MusicXML file contains actuals.
4246 // the MusicXML values for each note are simply copied to the defaults
4247 
4248 static void setDrumset(Chord* c, MusicXMLParserPass1& pass1, const QString& partId, const QString& instrumentId,
4249  const Fraction noteStartTime, const mxmlNotePitch& mnp, const Direction stemDir, const NoteHead::Group headGroup)
4250  {
4251  // determine staff line based on display-step / -octave and clef type
4252  const auto clef = c->staff()->clef(noteStartTime);
4253  const auto po = ClefInfo::pitchOffset(clef);
4254  const auto pitch = MusicXMLStepAltOct2Pitch(mnp.displayStep(), 0, mnp.displayOctave());
4255  auto line = po - absStep(pitch);
4256 
4257  // correct for number of staff lines
4258  // see ExportMusicXml::unpitch2xml for explanation
4259  // TODO handle other # staff lines ?
4260  int staffLines = c->staff()->lines(Fraction(0,1));
4261  if (staffLines == 1) line -= 8;
4262  if (staffLines == 3) line -= 2;
4263 
4264  // the drum palette cannot handle stem direction AUTO,
4265  // overrule if necessary
4266  Direction overruledStemDir = stemDir;
4267  if (stemDir == Direction::AUTO) {
4268  if (line > 4)
4269  overruledStemDir = Direction::DOWN;
4270  else
4271  overruledStemDir = Direction::UP;
4272  }
4273  // this should be done in pass 1, would make _pass1 const here
4274  pass1.setDrumsetDefault(partId, instrumentId, headGroup, line, overruledStemDir);
4275  }

4279 //---------------------------------------------------------
4280 
4281 /**
4282  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note node.
4283  */
4284 
4285 Note* MusicXMLParserPass2::note(const QString& partId,
4286  Measure* measure,
4287  const Fraction sTime,
4288  const Fraction prevSTime,
4289  Fraction& missingPrev,
4290  Fraction& dura,
4291  Fraction& missingCurr,
4292  QString& currentVoice,
4293  GraceChordList& gcl,
4294  int& gac,
4295  Beam*& currBeam,
4296  FiguredBassList& fbl,
4297  int& alt,
4298  MxmlTupletStates& tupletStates,
4299  Tuplets& tuplets
4300  )
4301  {
4302  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "note");
4303 
4304  if (_e.attributes().value("print-spacing") == "no") {
4305  notePrintSpacingNo(dura);
4306  return 0;
4307  }
4308 
4309  bool chord = false;
4310  bool cue = false;

4312  bool grace = false;
4313  bool rest = false;
4314  int staff = 1;
4315  QString type;
4316  QString voice;

4318  bool noStem = false;
4319  NoteHead::Group headGroup = NoteHead::Group::HEAD_NORMAL;

4321  noteColor.setNamedColor(_e.attributes().value("color").toString());
4322  QColor noteheadColor = QColor::Invalid;
4323  bool noteheadParentheses = false;

4325  int velocity = round(_e.attributes().value("dynamics").toDouble() * 0.9);
4326  bool graceSlash = false;
