4328  Beam::Mode bm = Beam::Mode::AUTO;
4329  QString instrumentId;
4330  MusicXMLParserLyric lyric { _pass1.getMusicXmlPart(partId).lyricNumberHandler(), _e, _score, _logger };
4331  MusicXMLParserNotations notations { _e, _score, _logger };
4332 
4333  mxmlNoteDuration mnd { _divs, _logger };
4334  mxmlNotePitch mnp { _logger };
4335 
4336  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4337  if (mnp.readProperties(_e, _score)) {
4338  // element handled
4339  }
4340  else if (mnd.readProperties(_e)) {
4341  // element handled
4342  }
4343  else if (_e.name() == "beam")
4344  beam(bm);
4345  else if (_e.name() == "chord") {
4346  chord = true;
4347  _e.readNext();
4348  }
4349  else if (_e.name() == "cue") {
4350  cue = true;
4351  _e.readNext();
4352  }
4353  else if (_e.name() == "grace") {
4354  grace = true;
4355  graceSlash = _e.attributes().value("slash") == "yes";
4356  _e.readNext();
4357  }
4358  else if (_e.name() == "instrument") {
4359  instrumentId = _e.attributes().value("id").toString();
4360  _e.readNext();
4361  }
4362  else if (_e.name() == "lyric") {
4363  // lyrics on grace notes not (yet) supported by MuseScore
4364  if (!grace) {
4365  lyric.parse();
4366  }
4367  else {
4368  _logger->logDebugInfo("ignoring lyrics on grace notes", &_e);
4369  skipLogCurrElem();
4370  }
4371  }
4372  else if (_e.name() == "notations") {
4373  notations.parse();
4374  }
4375  else if (_e.name() == "notehead") {
4376  noteheadColor.setNamedColor(_e.attributes().value("color").toString());
4377  noteheadParentheses = _e.attributes().value("parentheses") == "yes";
4378  noteheadFilled = _e.attributes().value("filled").toString();
4379  headGroup = convertNotehead(_e.readElementText());
4380  }
4381  else if (_e.name() == "rest") {
4382  rest = true;
4383  mnp.displayStepOctave(_e);
4384  }
4385  else if (_e.name() == "staff") {
4386  auto ok = false;
4387  auto strStaff = _e.readElementText();
4388  staff = strStaff.toInt(&ok);
4389  if (!ok) {
4390  // error already reported in pass 1
4391  staff = 1;
4392  }
4393  }
4394  else if (_e.name() == "stem")
4395  stem(stemDir, noStem);
4396  else if (_e.name() == "type") {
4397  small = _e.attributes().value("size") == "cue";
4398  type = _e.readElementText();
4399  }
4400  else if (_e.name() == "voice")
4401  voice = _e.readElementText();
4402  else
4403  skipLogCurrElem();
4404  }
4405 
4406  // convert staff to zero-based (in case of error, staff will be -1)
4407  staff--;
4408 
4409  // Bug fix for Sibelius 7.1.3 which does not write <voice> for notes with <chord>
4410  if (!chord)
4411  // remember voice
4412  currentVoice = voice;
4413  else if (voice == "")
4414  // use voice from last note w/o <chord>
4415  voice = currentVoice;
4416 
4417  // Assume voice 1 if voice is empty (legal in a single voice part)
4418  if (voice == "")
4419  voice = "1";
4420 
4421  // check for timing error(s) and set dura
4422  // keep in this order as checkTiming() might change dura
4423  auto errorStr = mnd.checkTiming(type, rest, grace);
4424  dura = mnd.dura();
4425  if (errorStr != "")
4426  _logger->logError(errorStr, &_e);
4427 
4428  // At this point all checks have been done, the note should be added
4429  // note: in case of error exit from here, the postponed <note> children
4430  // must still be skipped
4431 
4432  int msMove = 0;
4433  int msTrack = 0;
4434  int msVoice = 0;
4435 
4436  if (!_pass1.determineStaffMoveVoice(partId, staff, voice, msMove, msTrack, msVoice)) {
4437  _logger->logDebugInfo(QString("could not map staff %1 voice '%2'").arg(staff + 1).arg(voice), &_e);
4438  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "note");
4439  return 0;
4440  }
4441 
4442  // start time for note:
4443  // - sTime for non-chord / first chord note
4444  // - prevTime for others
4445  auto noteStartTime = chord ? prevSTime : sTime;
4446  auto timeMod = mnd.timeMod();
4447 
4448  // determine tuplet state, used twice (before and after note allocation)
4449  MxmlTupletFlags tupletAction;
4450 
4451  // handle tuplet state for the previous chord or rest
4452  if (!chord && !grace) {
4453  auto& tuplet = tuplets[voice];
4454  auto& tupletState = tupletStates[voice];
4455  tupletAction = tupletState.determineTupletAction(mnd.dura(), timeMod, notations.tupletDesc().type, mnd.normalType(), missingPrev, missingCurr);
4456  if (tupletAction & MxmlTupletFlag::STOP_PREVIOUS) {
4457  // tuplet start while already in tuplet
4458  if (missingPrev.isValid() && missingPrev > Fraction(0, 1)) {
4459  const auto track = msTrack + msVoice;
4460  const auto extraRest = addRest(_score, measure, noteStartTime, track, msMove,
4461  TDuration { missingPrev* tuplet->ratio() }, missingPrev);
4462  if (extraRest) {
4463  extraRest->setTuplet(tuplet);
4464  tuplet->add(extraRest);
4465  noteStartTime += missingPrev;
4466  }
4467  }
4468  // recover by simply stopping the current tuplet first
4469  const auto normalNotes = timeMod.numerator();
4470  handleTupletStop(tuplet, normalNotes);
4471  }
4472  }
4473 
4474  Chord* c { nullptr };
4475  ChordRest* cr { nullptr };
4476  Note* note { nullptr };
4477 
4478  TDuration duration = determineDuration(rest, type, mnd.dots(), dura, measure->ticks());
4479 
4480  // begin allocation
4481  if (rest) {
4482  const auto track = msTrack + msVoice;
4483  cr = addRest(_score, measure, noteStartTime, track, msMove,
4484  duration, dura);
4485  }
4486  else {
4487  if (!grace) {
4488  // regular note
4489  // if there is already a chord just add to it
4490  // else create a new one
4491  // this basically ignores <chord/> errors
4492  c = findOrCreateChord(_score, measure,
4493  noteStartTime,
4494  msTrack + msVoice, msMove,
4495  duration, dura, bm);
4496  }
4497  else {
4498  // grace note
4499  // TODO: check if explicit stem direction should also be set for grace notes
4500  // (the DOM parser does that, but seems to have no effect on the autotester)
4501  if (!chord || gcl.isEmpty()) {
4502  c = createGraceChord(_score, msTrack + msVoice, duration, graceSlash);
4503  // TODO FIX
4504  // the setStaffMove() below results in identical behaviour as 2.0:
4505  // grace note will be at the wrong staff with the wrong pitch,
4506  // seems to use the line value calculated for the right staff
4507  // leaving it places the note at the wrong staff with the right pitch
4508  // this affects only grace notes where staff move differs from
4509  // the main note, e.g. DebuMandSample.xml first grace in part 2
4510  // c->setStaffMove(msMove);
4511  // END TODO
4512  gcl.append(c);
4513  }
4514  else
4515  c = gcl.last();
4516 
4517  }
4518  note = new Note(_score);
4519  const int ottavaStaff = (msTrack - _pass1.trackForPart(partId)) / VOICES;
4520  const int octaveShift = _pass1.octaveShift(partId, ottavaStaff, noteStartTime);
4521  const auto part = _pass1.getPart(partId);
4522  const auto instrument = part->instrument(noteStartTime);
4523  setPitch(note, _pass1, partId, instrumentId, mnp, octaveShift, instrument);
4524  c->add(note);
4525  //c->setStemDirection(stemDir); // already done in handleBeamAndStemDir()
4526  //c->setNoStem(noStem);
4527  cr = c;
4528  }
4529  // end allocation
4530 
4531  if (rest) {
4532  const auto track = msTrack + msVoice;
4533  if (cr) {
4534  if (currBeam) {
4535  if (currBeam->track() == track) {
4536  cr->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::MID);
4537  currBeam->add(cr);
4538  }
4539  else
4540  removeBeam(currBeam);
4541  }
4542  else
4543  cr->setBeamMode(Beam::Mode::NONE);
4544  cr->setSmall(small);
4545  if (noteColor != QColor::Invalid)
4546  cr->setColor(noteColor);
4547  cr->setVisible(printObject);
4548  handleDisplayStep(cr, mnp.displayStep(), mnp.displayOctave(), noteStartTime, _score->spatium());
4549  }
4550  }
4551  else {
4552  if (!grace) {
4553  // regular note
4554  // handle beam
4555  if (!chord)
4556  handleBeamAndStemDir(c, bm, stemDir, currBeam, _pass1.hasBeamingInfo());
4557 
4558  // append any grace chord after chord to the previous chord
4559  const auto prevChord = measure->findChord(prevSTime, msTrack + msVoice);
4560  if (prevChord && prevChord != c)
4561  addGraceChordsAfter(prevChord, gcl, gac);
4562 
4563  // append any grace chord
4564  addGraceChordsBefore(c, gcl);
4565  }
4566 
4567  note->setSmall(cue || small); // cue notes are always small, normal notes only if size=cue
4568  note->setPlay(!cue); // cue notes don't play
4569  note->setHeadGroup(headGroup);
4570  if (noteColor != QColor::Invalid)
4571  note->setColor(noteColor);
4572  setNoteHead(note, noteheadColor, noteheadParentheses, noteheadFilled);
4573  note->setVisible(printObject); // TODO also set the stem to invisible
4574 
4575  if (velocity > 0) {
4576  note->setVeloType(Note::ValueType::USER_VAL);
4577  note->setVeloOffset(velocity);
4578  }
4579 
4580  if (mnp.unpitched()) {
4581  setDrumset(c, _pass1, partId, instrumentId, noteStartTime, mnp, stemDir, headGroup);
4582  }
4583 
4584  // accidental handling
4585  //qDebug("note acc %p type %hhd acctype %hhd",
4586  // acc, acc ? acc->accidentalType() : static_cast<Ms::AccidentalType>(0), accType);
4587  Accidental* acc = mnp.acc();
4588  if (!acc && mnp.accType() != AccidentalType::NONE) {
4589  acc = new Accidental(_score);
4590  acc->setAccidentalType(mnp.accType());
4591  }
4592 
4593  if (acc) {
4594  note->add(acc);
4595  // save alter value for user accidental
4596  if (acc->accidentalType() != AccidentalType::NONE)
4597  alt = mnp.alter();
4598  }
4599 
4600  c->setNoStem(noStem);
4601  }
4602 
4603  // cr can be 0 here (if a rest cannot be added)
4604  // TODO: complete and cleanup handling this case
4605  if (cr)
4606  cr->setVisible(printObject);
4607 
4608  Q_ASSERT(_pass1.getPart(partId));
4609 
4610  // handle notations
4611  if (cr) {
4612  notations.addToScore(cr, note, noteStartTime.ticks(), _slurs, _glissandi, _spanners, _trills, _tie);
4613  }
4614 
4615  // handle grace after state: remember current grace list size
4616  if (grace && notations.mustStopGraceAFter()) {
4617  gac = gcl.size();
4618  }
4619 
4620  // handle tremolo before handling tuplet (two note tremolos modify timeMod)
4621  if (cr) {
4622  addTremolo(cr, notations.tremoloNr(), notations.tremoloType(), _tremStart, _logger, &_e, timeMod);
4623  }
4624 
4625  // handle tuplet state for the current chord or rest
4626  if (cr) {
4627  if (!chord && !grace) {
4628  auto& tuplet = tuplets[voice];
4629  // do tuplet if valid time-modification is not 1/1 and is not 1/2 (tremolo)
4630  // TODO: check interaction tuplet and tremolo handling
4631  if (timeMod.isValid() && timeMod != Fraction(1, 1) && timeMod != Fraction(1, 2)) {
4632  const auto actualNotes = timeMod.denominator();
4633  const auto normalNotes = timeMod.numerator();
4634  if (tupletAction & MxmlTupletFlag::START_NEW) {
4635  // create a new tuplet
4636  handleTupletStart(cr, tuplet, actualNotes, normalNotes, notations.tupletDesc());
4637  }
4638  if (tupletAction & MxmlTupletFlag::ADD_CHORD) {
4639  cr->setTuplet(tuplet);
4640  tuplet->add(cr);
4641  }
4642  if (tupletAction & MxmlTupletFlag::STOP_CURRENT) {
4643  if (missingCurr.isValid() && missingCurr > Fraction(0, 1)) {
4644  qDebug("add missing %s to current tuplet", qPrintable(missingCurr.print()));
4645  const auto track = msTrack + msVoice;
4646  const auto extraRest = addRest(_score, measure, noteStartTime + dura, track, msMove,
4647  TDuration { missingCurr* tuplet->ratio() }, missingCurr);
4648  if (extraRest) {
4649  extraRest->setTuplet(tuplet);
4650  tuplet->add(extraRest);
4651  }
4652  }
4653  handleTupletStop(tuplet, normalNotes);
4654  }
4655  }
4656  else if (tuplet) {
4657  // stop any still incomplete tuplet
4658  handleTupletStop(tuplet, 2);
4659  }
4660  }
4661  }
4662 
4663  // add lyrics found by lyric
4664  if (cr) {
4665  // add lyrics and stop corresponding extends
4666  addLyrics(_logger, &_e, cr, lyric.numberedLyrics(), lyric.extendedLyrics(), _extendedLyrics);
4667  if (rest) {
4668  // stop all extends
4669  _extendedLyrics.setExtend(-1, cr->track(), cr->tick());
4670  }
4671  }
4672 
4673  // add figured bass element
4674  addFiguredBassElemens(fbl, noteStartTime, msTrack, dura, measure);
4675 
4676  // convert to slash or rhythmic notation if needed
4677  // TODO in the case of slash notation, we assume that given notes do in fact correspond to slash beats
4678  if (c && _measureStyleSlash != MusicXmlSlash::NONE) {
4679  c->setSlash(true, _measureStyleSlash == MusicXmlSlash::SLASH);
4680  }
4681 
4682  // don't count chord or grace note duration
4683  // note that this does not check the MusicXML requirement that notes in a chord
4684  // cannot have a duration longer than the first note in the chord
4685  if (chord || grace)
4686  dura.set(0, 1);
4687 
4688  if (!(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "note"))
4689  qDebug("name %s line %lld", qPrintable(_e.name().toString()), _e.lineNumber());
4690  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "note");
4691 
4692  return note;
4693  }
4694 
4695 //---------------------------------------------------------
4696 // notePrintSpacingNo
4697 //---------------------------------------------------------
4698 
4699 /**
4700  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note node for a note with print-spacing="no".
4701  These are handled like a forward: only moving the time forward.
4702  */
4703 
4704 void MusicXMLParserPass2::notePrintSpacingNo(Fraction& dura)
4705  {
4706  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "note");
4707  //_logger->logDebugTrace("MusicXMLParserPass1::notePrintSpacingNo", &_e);
4708 
4709  bool chord = false;
4710  bool grace = false;
4711 
4712  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4713  if (_e.name() == "chord") {
4714  chord = true;
4715  _e.readNext();
4716  }
4717  else if (_e.name() == "duration")
4718  duration(dura);
4719  else if (_e.name() == "grace") {
4720  grace = true;
4721  _e.readNext();
4722  }
4723  else
4724  _e.skipCurrentElement(); // skip but don't log
4725  }
4726 
4727  // don't count chord or grace note duration
4728  // note that this does not check the MusicXML requirement that notes in a chord
4729  // cannot have a duration longer than the first note in the chord
4730  if (chord || grace)
4731  dura.set(0, 1);
4732 
4733  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "note");
4734  }

4739 
4740 /**
4741  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/duration node.
4742  */
4743 
4744 void MusicXMLParserPass2::duration(Fraction& dura)
4745  {
4746  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "duration");
4747 
4748  dura.set(0, 0); // invalid unless set correctly
4749  const auto elementText = _e.readElementText();
4750  if (elementText.toInt() > 0)
4751  dura = calcTicks(elementText, _divs, _logger, &_e);
4752  else
4753  _logger->logError(QString("illegal duration %1").arg(dura.print()), &_e);
4754  //qDebug("duration %s valid %d", qPrintable(dura.print()), dura.isValid());
4755  }

4757 //---------------------------------------------------------
4758 // figure
4759 //---------------------------------------------------------
4760 
4761 /**
4762  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/harmony/figured-bass/figure node.
4763  Return the result as a FiguredBassItem.
4764  */
4765 
4766 FiguredBassItem* MusicXMLParserPass2::figure(const int idx, const bool paren)
4767  {
4768  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "figure");
4769 
4770  FiguredBassItem* fgi = new FiguredBassItem(_score, idx);
4771 
4772  // read the figure
4773  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4774  if (_e.name() == "extend") {
4775  QStringRef type = _e.attributes().value("type");
4776  if (type == "start")
4777  fgi->setContLine(FiguredBassItem::ContLine::EXTENDED);
4778  else if (type == "continue")
4779  fgi->setContLine(FiguredBassItem::ContLine::EXTENDED);
4780  else if (type == "stop")
4781  fgi->setContLine(FiguredBassItem::ContLine::SIMPLE);
4782  _e.skipCurrentElement();
4783  }
4784  else if (_e.name() == "figure-number") {
4785  QString val = _e.readElementText();
4786  int iVal = val.toInt();
4787  // MusicXML spec states figure-number is a number
4788  // MuseScore can only handle single digit
4789  if (1 <= iVal && iVal <= 9)
4790  fgi->setDigit(iVal);
4791  else
4792  _logger->logError(QString("incorrect figure-number '%1'").arg(val), &_e);
4793  }
4794  else if (_e.name() == "prefix")
4795  fgi->setPrefix(fgi->MusicXML2Modifier(_e.readElementText()));
4796  else if (_e.name() == "suffix")
4797  fgi->setSuffix(fgi->MusicXML2Modifier(_e.readElementText()));
4798  else
4799  skipLogCurrElem();
4800  }
4801 
4802  // set parentheses
4803  if (paren) {
4804  // parenthesis open
4805  if (fgi->prefix() != FiguredBassItem::Modifier::NONE)
4806  fgi->setParenth1(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDOPEN); // before prefix
4807  else if (fgi->digit() != FBIDigitNone)
4808  fgi->setParenth2(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDOPEN); // before digit
4809  else if (fgi->suffix() != FiguredBassItem::Modifier::NONE)
4810  fgi->setParenth3(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDOPEN); // before suffix
4811  // parenthesis close
4812  if (fgi->suffix() != FiguredBassItem::Modifier::NONE)
4813  fgi->setParenth4(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDCLOSED); // after suffix
4814  else if (fgi->digit() != FBIDigitNone)
4815  fgi->setParenth3(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDCLOSED); // after digit
4816  else if (fgi->prefix() != FiguredBassItem::Modifier::NONE)
4817  fgi->setParenth2(FiguredBassItem::Parenthesis::ROUNDCLOSED); // after prefix
4818  }
4819 
4820  return fgi;
4821  }
4822 
4823 //---------------------------------------------------------
4824 // figuredBass
4825 //---------------------------------------------------------
4826 
4827 /**
4828  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/harmony/figured-bass node.
4829  TODO check description:
4830  // Set the FiguredBass state based on the MusicXML <figured-bass> node de.
4831  // Note that onNote and ticks must be set by the MusicXML importer,
4832  // as the required context is not present in the items DOM tree.
4833  // Exception: if a <duration> element is present, tick can be set.
4834  Return the result as a FiguredBass if valid, non-empty figure(s) are found.
4835  Return 0 in case of error.
4836  */
4837 
4838 FiguredBass* MusicXMLParserPass2::figuredBass()
4839  {
4840  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "figured-bass");
4841 
4842  FiguredBass* fb = new FiguredBass(_score);
4843 
4844  bool parentheses = _e.attributes().value("parentheses") == "yes";
4845  QString normalizedText;
4846  int idx = 0;
4847  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4848  if (_e.name() == "duration") {
4849  Fraction dura;
4850  duration(dura);
4851  if (dura.isValid() && dura > Fraction(0, 1))
4852  fb->setTicks(dura);
4853  }
4854  else if (_e.name() == "figure") {
4855  FiguredBassItem* pItem = figure(idx++, parentheses);
4856  pItem->setTrack(0 /* TODO fb->track() */);
4857  pItem->setParent(fb);
4858  fb->appendItem(pItem);
4859  // add item normalized text
4860  if (!normalizedText.isEmpty())
4861  normalizedText.append('\n');
4862  normalizedText.append(pItem->normalizedText());
4863  }
4864  else {
4865  skipLogCurrElem();
4866  delete fb;
4867  return 0;
4868  }
4869  }
4870 
4871  fb->setXmlText(normalizedText); // this is the text to show while editing
4872 
4873  if (normalizedText.isEmpty()) {
4874  delete fb;
4875  return 0;
4876  }
4877 
4878  return fb;
4879  }
4880 
4881 //---------------------------------------------------------
4882 // frame
4883 //---------------------------------------------------------
4884 
4885 /**
4886  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/harmony/frame node.
4887  Return the result as a FretDiagram.
4888  */
4889 
4890 FretDiagram* MusicXMLParserPass2::frame()
4891  {
4892  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "frame");
4893 
4894  FretDiagram* fd = new FretDiagram(_score);
4895 
4896  // Format: fret: string
4897  std::map<int, int> bStarts;
4898  std::map<int, int> bEnds;
4899 
4900  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4901  if (_e.name() == "frame-frets") {
4902  int val = _e.readElementText().toInt();
4903  if (val > 0)
4904  fd->setFrets(val);
4905  else
4906  _logger->logError(QString("FretDiagram::readMusicXML: illegal frame-fret %1").arg(val), &_e);
4907  }
4908  else if (_e.name() == "frame-note") {
4909  int fret = -1;
4910  int string = -1;
4911  int actualString = -1;
4912  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
4913  if (_e.name() == "fret")
4914  fret = _e.readElementText().toInt();
4915  else if (_e.name() == "string") {
4916  string = _e.readElementText().toInt();
4917  actualString = fd->strings() - string;
4918  }
4919  else if (_e.name() == "barre") {
4920  // Keep barres to be added later
4921  QString t = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
4922  if (t == "start")
4923  bStarts[fret] = actualString;
4924  else if (t == "stop")
4925  bEnds[fret] = actualString;
4926  else
4927  _logger->logError(QString("FretDiagram::readMusicXML: illegal frame-note barre type %1").arg(t), &_e);
4928  skipLogCurrElem();
4929  }
4930  else
4931  skipLogCurrElem();
4932  }
4933  _logger->logDebugInfo(QString("FretDiagram::readMusicXML string %1 fret %2").arg(string).arg(fret), &_e);
4934 
4935  if (string > 0) {
4936  if (fret == 0)
4937  fd->setMarker(actualString, FretMarkerType::CIRCLE);
4938  else if (fret > 0)
4939  fd->setDot(actualString, fret, true);
4940  }
4941  else
4942  _logger->logError(QString("FretDiagram::readMusicXML: illegal frame-note string %1").arg(string), &_e);
4943  }
4944  else if (_e.name() == "frame-strings") {
4945  int val = _e.readElementText().toInt();
4946  if (val > 0) {
4947  fd->setStrings(val);
4948  for (int i = 0; i < val; ++i) {
4949  // MXML Spec: any string without a dot or other marker has a closed string
4950  // cross marker above it.
4951  fd->setMarker(i, FretMarkerType::CROSS);
4952  }
4953  }
4954  else
4955  _logger->logError(QString("FretDiagram::readMusicXML: illegal frame-strings %1").arg(val), &_e);
4956  }
4957  else
4958  skipLogCurrElem();
4959  }
4960 
4961  // Finally add barres
4962  for (auto const& i : bStarts) {
4963  int fret = i.first;
4964  int startString = i.second;
4965 
4966  if (bEnds.find(fret) == bEnds.end())
4967  continue;
4968 
4969  int endString = bEnds[fret];
4970  fd->setBarre(startString, endString, fret);
4971  }
4972 
4973  return fd;
4974  }
4975 
4976 //---------------------------------------------------------
4977 // harmony
4978 //---------------------------------------------------------
4979 
4980 /**
4981  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/harmony node.
4982  */
4983 
4984 void MusicXMLParserPass2::harmony(const QString& partId, Measure* measure, const Fraction sTime)
4985  {
4986  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "harmony");
4987 
4988  int track = _pass1.trackForPart(partId);
4989 
4990  // placement:
4991  // in order to work correctly, this should probably be adjusted to account for spatium
4992  // but in any case, we don't support import relative-x/y for other elements
4993  // no reason to do so for chord symbols
4994 #if 0 // TODO:ws
4995  double rx = 0.0; // 0.1 * e.attribute("relative-x", "0").toDouble();
4996  double ry = 0.0; // -0.1 * e.attribute("relative-y", "0").toDouble();
4997 
4998  double styleYOff = _score->textStyle(Tid::HARMONY).offset().y();
4999  OffsetType offsetType = _score->textStyle(Tid::HARMONY).offsetType();
5000  if (offsetType == OffsetType::ABS) {
5001  styleYOff = styleYOff * DPMM / _score->spatium();
5002  }
5003 
5004  // TODO: check correct dy handling
5005  // previous code: double dy = -0.1 * e.attribute("default-y", QString::number(styleYOff* -10)).toDouble();
5006  double dy = -0.1 * _e.attributes().value("default-y").toDouble();
5007 #endif
5008  bool printObject = _e.attributes().value("print-object") != "no";
5009  //QString printFrame = _e.attributes().value("print-frame").toString();
5010  //QString printStyle = _e.attributes().value("print-style").toString();
5011 
5012  QString kind, kindText, functionText, symbols, parens;
5013  QList<HDegree> degreeList;
5014 
5015  /* TODO ?
5016  if (harmony) {
5017  qDebug("MusicXML::import: more than one harmony");
5018  return;
5019  }
5020  */
5021 
5022  FretDiagram* fd = 0;
5023  Harmony* ha = new Harmony(_score);
5024 //TODO:ws ha->setUserOff(QPointF(rx, ry + dy - styleYOff));
5025  Fraction offset;
5026  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5027  if (_e.name() == "root") {
5028  QString step;
5029  int alter = 0;
5030  bool invalidRoot = false;
5031  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5032  if (_e.name() == "root-step") {
5033  // attributes: print-style
5034  step = _e.readElementText();
5035  if (_e.attributes().hasAttribute("text")) {
5036  if (_e.attributes().value("text").toString() == "") {
5037  invalidRoot = true;
5038  }
5039  }
5040  }
5041  else if (_e.name() == "root-alter") {
5042  // attributes: print-object, print-style
5043  // location (left-right)
5044  alter = _e.readElementText().toInt();
5045  }
5046  else
5047  skipLogCurrElem();
5048  }
5049  if (invalidRoot)
5050  ha->setRootTpc(Tpc::TPC_INVALID);
5051  else
5052  ha->setRootTpc(step2tpc(step, AccidentalVal(alter)));
5053  }
5054  else if (_e.name() == "function") {
5055  // attributes: print-style
5056  ha->setRootTpc(Tpc::TPC_INVALID);
5057  ha->setBaseTpc(Tpc::TPC_INVALID);
5058  functionText = _e.readElementText();
5059  // TODO: parse to decide between ROMAN and NASHVILLE
5060  ha->setHarmonyType(HarmonyType::ROMAN);
5061  }
5062  else if (_e.name() == "kind") {
5063  // attributes: use-symbols yes-no
5064  // text, stack-degrees, parentheses-degree, bracket-degrees,
5065  // print-style, halign, valign
5066  kindText = _e.attributes().value("text").toString();
5067  symbols = _e.attributes().value("use-symbols").toString();
5068  parens = _e.attributes().value("parentheses-degrees").toString();
5069  kind = _e.readElementText();
5070  if (kind == "none") {
5071  ha->setRootTpc(Tpc::TPC_INVALID);
5072  }
5073  }
5074  else if (_e.name() == "inversion") {
5075  // attributes: print-style
5076  skipLogCurrElem();
5077  }
5078  else if (_e.name() == "bass") {
5079  QString step;
5080  int alter = 0;
5081  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5082  if (_e.name() == "bass-step") {
5083  // attributes: print-style
5084  step = _e.readElementText();
5085  }
5086  else if (_e.name() == "bass-alter") {
5087  // attributes: print-object, print-style
5088  // location (left-right)
5089  alter = _e.readElementText().toInt();
5090  }
5091  else
5092  skipLogCurrElem();
5093  }
5094  ha->setBaseTpc(step2tpc(step, AccidentalVal(alter)));
5095  }
5096  else if (_e.name() == "degree") {
5097  int degreeValue = 0;
5098  int degreeAlter = 0;
5099  QString degreeType = "";
5100  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5101  if (_e.name() == "degree-value") {
5102  degreeValue = _e.readElementText().toInt();
5103  }
5104  else if (_e.name() == "degree-alter") {
5105  degreeAlter = _e.readElementText().toInt();
5106  }
5107  else if (_e.name() == "degree-type") {
5108  degreeType = _e.readElementText();
5109  }
5110  else
5111  skipLogCurrElem();
5112  }
5113  if (degreeValue <= 0 || degreeValue > 13
5114  || degreeAlter < -2 || degreeAlter > 2
5115  || (degreeType != "add" && degreeType != "alter" && degreeType != "subtract")) {
5116  _logger->logError(QString("incorrect degree: degreeValue=%1 degreeAlter=%2 degreeType=%3")
5117  .arg(degreeValue).arg(degreeAlter).arg(degreeType), &_e);
5118  }
5119  else {
5120  if (degreeType == "add")
5121  degreeList << HDegree(degreeValue, degreeAlter, HDegreeType::ADD);
5122  else if (degreeType == "alter")
5123  degreeList << HDegree(degreeValue, degreeAlter, HDegreeType::ALTER);
5124  else if (degreeType == "subtract")
5125  degreeList << HDegree(degreeValue, degreeAlter, HDegreeType::SUBTRACT);
5126  }
5127  }
5128  else if (_e.name() == "frame")
5129  fd = frame();
5130  else if (_e.name() == "level")
5131  skipLogCurrElem();
5132  else if (_e.name() == "offset")
5133  offset = calcTicks(_e.readElementText(), _divs, _logger, &_e);
5134  else if (_e.name() == "staff") {
5135  int nstaves = _pass1.getPart(partId)->nstaves();
5136  QString strStaff = _e.readElementText();
5137  int staff = strStaff.toInt();
5138  if (0 < staff && staff <= nstaves)
5139  track += (staff - 1) * VOICES;
5140  else
5141  _logger->logError(QString("invalid staff %1").arg(strStaff), &_e);
5142  }
5143  else
5144  skipLogCurrElem();
5145  }
5146 
5147  if (fd) {
5148  fd->setTrack(track);
5149  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, sTime + offset);
5150  s->add(fd);
5151  }
5152 
5153  const ChordDescription* d = 0;
5154  if (ha->rootTpc() != Tpc::TPC_INVALID)
5155  d = ha->fromXml(kind, kindText, symbols, parens, degreeList);
5156  if (d) {
5157  ha->setId(d->id);
5158  ha->setTextName(d->names.front());
5159  }
5160  else {
5161  ha->setId(-1);
5162  QString textName = functionText + kindText;
5163  ha->setTextName(textName);
5164  }
5165  ha->render();
5166 
5167  ha->setVisible(printObject);
5168 
5169  // TODO-LV: do this only if ha points to a valid harmony
5170  // harmony = ha;
5171  ha->setTrack(track);
5172  Segment* s = measure->getSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, sTime + offset);
5173  s->add(ha);
5174  }

5180 /**
5181  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/beam node.
5182  Sets beamMode in case of begin, continue or end beam number 1.
5183  */
5184 
5185 void MusicXMLParserPass2::beam(Beam::Mode& beamMode)
5186  {
5187  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "beam");
5188 
5189  int beamNo = _e.attributes().value("number").toInt();
5190 
5191  if (beamNo == 1) {
5192  QString s = _e.readElementText();
5193  if (s == "begin")
5194  beamMode = Beam::Mode::BEGIN;
5195  else if (s == "end")
5196  beamMode = Beam::Mode::END;
5197  else if (s == "continue")
5198  beamMode = Beam::Mode::MID;
5199  else if (s == "backward hook")
5200  ;
5201  else if (s == "forward hook")
5202  ;
5203  else
5204  _logger->logError(QString("unknown beam keyword '%1'").arg(s), &_e);
5205  }
5206  else
5207  _e.skipCurrentElement();
5208  }

5227  else if (_e.name() == "voice")

5278 
5279 //---------------------------------------------------------
5280 // parse
5281 //---------------------------------------------------------
5282 
5283 void MusicXMLParserLyric::parse()
5284  {
5285  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "lyric");
5286 
5287  std::unique_ptr<Lyrics> lyric { new Lyrics(_score) };
5288  // TODO in addlyrics: l->setTrack(trk);
5289 
5290  bool hasExtend = false;
5291  const auto lyricNumber = _e.attributes().value("number").toString();
5292  QColor lyricColor { QColor::Invalid };
5293  lyricColor.setNamedColor(_e.attributes().value("color").toString());
5294  QString extendType;
5295  QString formattedText;
5296 
5297  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5298  if (_e.name() == "elision") {
5299  // TODO verify elision handling
5300  /*
5301  QString text = _e.readElementText();
5302  if (text.isEmpty())
5303  formattedText += " ";
5304  else
5305  */
5306  formattedText += nextPartOfFormattedString(_e);
5307  }
5308  else if (_e.name() == "extend") {
5309  hasExtend = true;
5310  extendType = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
5311  _e.readNext();
5312  }
5313  else if (_e.name() == "syllabic") {
5314  auto syll = _e.readElementText();
5315  if (syll == "single")
5316  lyric->setSyllabic(Lyrics::Syllabic::SINGLE);
5317  else if (syll == "begin")
5318  lyric->setSyllabic(Lyrics::Syllabic::BEGIN);
5319  else if (syll == "end")
5320  lyric->setSyllabic(Lyrics::Syllabic::END);
5321  else if (syll == "middle")
5322  lyric->setSyllabic(Lyrics::Syllabic::MIDDLE);
5323  else
5324  qDebug("unknown syllabic %s", qPrintable(syll)); // TODO
5325  }
5326  else if (_e.name() == "text")
5327  formattedText += nextPartOfFormattedString(_e);
5328  else
5329  skipLogCurrElem();
5330  }
5331 
5332  // if no lyric read (e.g. only 'extend "type=stop"'), no further action required
5333  if (formattedText == "") {
5334  return;
5335  }
5336 
5337  const auto lyricNo = _lyricNumberHandler.getLyricNo(lyricNumber);
5338  if (lyricNo < 0) {
5339  _logger->logError("invalid lyrics number (<0)", &_e);
5340  return;
5341  }
5342  else if (lyricNo > MAX_LYRICS) {
5343  _logger->logError(QString("too much lyrics (>%1)").arg(MAX_LYRICS), &_e);
5344  return;
5345  }
5346  else if (_numberedLyrics.contains(lyricNo)) {
5347  _logger->logError(QString("duplicate lyrics number (%1)").arg(lyricNumber), &_e);
5348  return;
5349  }
5350 
5351  //qDebug("formatted lyric '%s'", qPrintable(formattedText));
5352  lyric->setXmlText(formattedText);
5353  if (lyricColor != QColor::Invalid)
5354  lyric->setColor(lyricColor);
5355 
5356  const auto l = lyric.release();
5357  _numberedLyrics[lyricNo] = l;
5358 
5359  if (hasExtend && (extendType == "" || extendType == "start"))
5360  _extendedLyrics.insert(l);
5361 
5362  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "lyric");
5363  }

5370  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/slur node.
5371  */
5372 
5373 void MusicXMLParserNotations::slur()
5374  {
5375  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "slur");
5376 
5377  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(), _e.attributes(), "notations");
5378  _notations.push_back(notation);
5379 
5380  // any grace note containing a slur stop means
5381  // last note of a grace after set has been found
5382  // -> remember slur stop
5383  if (notation.attribute("type") == "stop") {
5384  _slurStop = true;
5385  }
5386 
5387  _e.readNext();
5388 
5389  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "slur");
5390  }
5391 
5392 //---------------------------------------------------------
5393 // addSlur
5394 //---------------------------------------------------------
5395 
5396 static void addSlur(const Notation& notation, SlurStack& slurs, ChordRest* cr, const int tick,
5397  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
5398  {
5399  auto slurNo = notation.attribute("number").toInt();
5400  if (slurNo > 0) slurNo--;
5401  const auto slurType = notation.attribute("type");
5402  auto lineType = notation.attribute("line-type");
5403  if (lineType == "") lineType = "solid";
5404 
5405  const auto track = cr->track();
5406  auto score = cr->score();
5407 
5408  // PriMus Music-Notation by Columbussoft (build 10093) generates overlapping
5409  // slurs that do not have a number attribute to distinguish them.
5410  // The duplicates must be ignored, to prevent memory allocation issues,
5411  // which caused a MuseScore crash
5412  // Similar issues happen with Sibelius 7.1.3 (direct export)
5413 
5414  if (slurType == "start") {
5415  if (slurs[slurNo].isStart())
5416  // slur start when slur already started: report error
5417  logger->logError(QString("ignoring duplicate slur start"), xmlreader);
5418  else if (slurs[slurNo].isStop()) {
5419  // slur start when slur already stopped: wrap up
5420  auto newSlur = slurs[slurNo].slur();
5421  newSlur->setTick(Fraction::fromTicks(tick));
5422  newSlur->setStartElement(cr);
5423  slurs[slurNo] = SlurDesc();
5424  }
5425  else {
5426  // slur start for new slur: init
5427  auto newSlur = new Slur(score);
5428  if (cr->isGrace())
5429  newSlur->setAnchor(Spanner::Anchor::CHORD);
5430  if (lineType == "dotted")
5431  newSlur->setLineType(1);
5432  else if (lineType == "dashed")
5433  newSlur->setLineType(2);
5434  newSlur->setTick(Fraction::fromTicks(tick));
5435  newSlur->setStartElement(cr);
5436  const auto pl = notation.attribute("placement");
5437  if (pl == "above")
5438  newSlur->setSlurDirection(Direction::UP);
5439  else if (pl == "below")
5440  newSlur->setSlurDirection(Direction::DOWN);
5441  newSlur->setTrack(track);
5442  newSlur->setTrack2(track);
5443  slurs[slurNo].start(newSlur);
5444  score->addElement(newSlur);
5445  }
5446  }
5447  else if (slurType == "stop") {
5448  if (slurs[slurNo].isStart()) {
5449  // slur stop when slur already started: wrap up
5450  auto newSlur = slurs[slurNo].slur();
5451  if (!(cr->isGrace())) {
5452  newSlur->setTick2(Fraction::fromTicks(tick));
5453  newSlur->setTrack2(track);
5454  }
5455  newSlur->setEndElement(cr);
5456  slurs[slurNo] = SlurDesc();
5457  }
5458  else if (slurs[slurNo].isStop())
5459  // slur stop when slur already stopped: report error
5460  logger->logError(QString("ignoring duplicate slur stop"), xmlreader);
5461  else {
5462  // slur stop for new slur: init
5463  auto newSlur = new Slur(score);
5464  if (!(cr->isGrace())) {
5465  newSlur->setTick2(Fraction::fromTicks(tick));
5466  newSlur->setTrack2(track);
5467  }
5468  newSlur->setEndElement(cr);
5469  slurs[slurNo].stop(newSlur);
5470  }
5471  }
5472  else if (slurType == "continue")
5473  ; // ignore
5474  else
5475  logger->logError(QString("unknown slur type %1").arg(slurType), xmlreader);
5476  }
5477

5530 //---------------------------------------------------------
5531 // articulations
5532 //---------------------------------------------------------
5533 
5534 /**
5535  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/articulations node.
5536  Note that some notations attach to notes only in MuseScore,
5537  which means trying to attach them to a rest will crash,
5538  as in that case note is 0.
5539  */
5540 
5541 void MusicXMLParserNotations::articulations()
5542  {
5543  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "articulations");
5544 
5545  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5546  SymId id { SymId::noSym };
5547  if (convertArticulationToSymId(_e.name().toString(), id)) {
5548  Notation artic = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(),
5549  _e.attributes(), "articulations", id);
5550  _notations.push_back(artic);
5551  _e.readNext();
5552  continue;
5553  }
5554  else if (_e.name() == "breath-mark") {
5555  _breath = SymId::breathMarkComma;
5556  _e.readElementText();
5557  // TODO: handle value read (note: encoding unknown, only "comma" found)
5558  }
5559  else if (_e.name() == "caesura") {
5560  _breath = SymId::caesura;
5561  _e.readNext();
5562  }
5563  else if (_e.name() == "doit"
5564  || _e.name() == "falloff"
5565  || _e.name() == "plop"
5566  || _e.name() == "scoop") {
5567  Notation artic = Notation::notationWithAttributes("chord-line",
5568  _e.attributes(), "articulations");
5569  artic.setSubType(_e.name().toString());
5570  _notations.push_back(artic);
5571  _e.readNext();
5572  }
5573  else {
5574  skipLogCurrElem();
5575  }
5576  }
5577  //qDebug("::notations tokenString '%s' name '%s'", qPrintable(_e.tokenString()), qPrintable(_e.name().toString()));
5578 
5579  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "articulations");
5580  }
5581 
5582 //---------------------------------------------------------
5583 // ornaments
5584 //---------------------------------------------------------
5585 
5586 /**
5587  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/ornaments node.
5588  */
5589 
5590 void MusicXMLParserNotations::ornaments()
5591  {
5592  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "ornaments");
5593 
5594  bool trillMark = false;
5595  // <trill-mark placement="above"/>
5596  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5597  SymId id { SymId::noSym };
5598  if (convertArticulationToSymId(_e.name().toString(), id)) {
5599  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(),
5600  _e.attributes(), "articulations", id);
5601  _notations.push_back(notation);
5602  _e.readNext();
5603  continue;
5604  }
5605  else if (_e.name() == "trill-mark") {
5606  trillMark = true;
5607  _e.readNext();
5608  }
5609  else if (_e.name() == "wavy-line") {
5610  auto wavyLineTypeWasStart = (_wavyLineType == "start");
5611  _wavyLineType = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
5612  _wavyLineNo = _e.attributes().value("number").toString().toInt();
5613  if (_wavyLineNo > 0) _wavyLineNo--;
5614  // any grace note containing a wavy-line stop means
5615  // last note of a grace after set has been found
5616  // remember wavy-line stop
5617  if (_wavyLineType == "stop") {
5618  _wavyLineStop = true;
5619  }
5620  // check for start and stop on same note
5621  if (wavyLineTypeWasStart && _wavyLineType == "stop") {
5622  _wavyLineType = "startstop";
5623  }
5624  _e.readNext();
5625  }
5626  else if (_e.name() == "tremolo") {
5627  _tremoloType = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
5628  _tremoloNr = _e.readElementText().toInt();
5629  }
5630  else if (_e.name() == "inverted-mordent"
5631  || _e.name() == "mordent") {
5632  mordentNormalOrInverted();
5633  _e.readNext();
5634  }
5635  else {
5636  skipLogCurrElem();
5637  }
5638  }
5639 
5640  // note that mscore wavy line already implicitly includes a trillsym
5641  // so don't add an additional one
5642  if (trillMark && _wavyLineType != "start" && _wavyLineType != "startstop") {
5643  Notation ornament { "trill-mark", "ornaments", SymId::ornamentTrill };
5644  _notations.push_back(ornament);
5645  }
5646  }
5647 
5648 //---------------------------------------------------------
5649 // technical
5650 //---------------------------------------------------------
5651 
5652 /**
5653  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/technical node.
5654  */
5655 
5656 void MusicXMLParserNotations::technical()
5657  {
5658  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "technical");
5659 
5660  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5661  SymId id { SymId::noSym };
5662  if (convertArticulationToSymId(_e.name().toString(), id)) {
5663  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(),
5664  _e.attributes(), "technical", id);
5665  _notations.push_back(notation);
5666  _e.readNext();
5667  continue;
5668  }
5669  else if (_e.name() == "fingering" || _e.name() == "fret" || _e.name() == "pluck" || _e.name() == "string") {
5670  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(),
5671  _e.attributes(), "technical");
5672  notation.setText(_e.readElementText());
5673  _notations.push_back(notation);
5674  }
5675  else if (_e.name() == "harmonic") {
5676  harmonic();
5677  _e.readNext();
5678  }
5679  else {
5680  skipLogCurrElem();
5681  }
5682  }
5683  }
5684 
5685 
5686 //---------------------------------------------------------
5687 // harmonic
5688 //---------------------------------------------------------
5689 
5690 /**
5691  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/technical/harmonic node.
5692  */
5693 
5694 void MusicXMLParserNotations::harmonic()
5695  {
5696  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "harmonic");
5697 
5698  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(), _e.attributes(), "technical", SymId::stringsHarmonic);
5699 
5700  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
5701  QString name = _e.name().toString();
5702  if (name == "natural") {
5703  notation.setSubType(name);
5704  _e.readNext();
5705  }
5706  else { // TODO: add artificial harmonic when supported by musescore
5707  _logger->logError(QString("unsupported harmonic type/pitch '%1'").arg(name), &_e);
5708  _e.skipCurrentElement();
5709  }
5710  }
5711 
5712  if (notation.subType() != "") {
5713  _notations.push_back(notation);
5714  }
5715 
5716  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "harmonic");
5717  }
5718 
5719 //---------------------------------------------------------
5720 // addTechnical
5721 //---------------------------------------------------------
5722 
5723 void MusicXMLParserNotations::addTechnical(const Notation& notation, Note* note)
5724  {
5725  QString placement = notation.attribute("placement");
5726  QString fontWeight = notation.attribute("font-weight");
5727  qreal fontSize = notation.attribute("font-size").toDouble();
5728  QString fontStyle = notation.attribute("font-style");
5729  QString fontFamily = notation.attribute("font-family");
5730  if (notation.name() == "fingering") {
5731  // TODO: distinguish between keyboards (style Tid::FINGERING)
5732  // and (plucked) strings (style Tid::LH_GUITAR_FINGERING)
5733  addTextToNote(_e.lineNumber(), _e.columnNumber(), notation.text(), placement, fontWeight, fontSize, fontStyle, fontFamily,
5734  Tid::FINGERING, _score, note);
5735  }
5736  else if (notation.name() == "fret") {
5737  auto fret = notation.text().toInt();
5738  if (note) {
5739  if (note->staff()->isTabStaff(Fraction(0,1)))
5740  note->setFret(fret);
5741  }
5742  else
5743  _logger->logError("no note for fret", &_e);
5744  }
5745  else if (notation.name() == "pluck") {
5746  addTextToNote(_e.lineNumber(), _e.columnNumber(), notation.text(), placement, fontWeight, fontSize, fontStyle, fontFamily,
5747  Tid::RH_GUITAR_FINGERING, _score, note);
5748  }
5749  else if (notation.name() == "string") {
5750  if (note) {
5751  if (note->staff()->isTabStaff(Fraction(0,1)))
5752  note->setString(notation.text().toInt() - 1);
5753  else
5754  addTextToNote(_e.lineNumber(), _e.columnNumber(), notation.text(), placement, fontWeight, fontSize, fontStyle, fontFamily,
5755  Tid::STRING_NUMBER, _score, note);
5756  }
5757  else
5758  _logger->logError("no note for string", &_e);
5759  }
5760  }

5770

5791 void MusicXMLParserNotations::glissandoSlide()

5793  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && (_e.name() == "glissando" || _e.name() == "slide"));

5802 //---------------------------------------------------------
5803 // addGlissandoSlide
5804 //---------------------------------------------------------
5805 
5806 static void addGlissandoSlide(const Notation& notation, Note* note,
5807  Glissando* glissandi[MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL][2], MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners,
5808  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
5809  {
5810  auto glissandoNumber = notation.attribute("number").toInt();
5811  if (glissandoNumber > 0) glissandoNumber--;
5812  const auto glissandoType = notation.attribute("type");
5813  int glissandoTag = notation.name() == "slide" ? 0 : 1;
5814  // QString lineType = ee.attribute(QString("line-type"), "solid");
5815  Glissando*& gliss = glissandi[glissandoNumber][glissandoTag];
5816 
5817  const auto tick = note->tick();
5818  const auto track = note->track();
5819  auto score = note->score();
5820 
5821  if (glissandoType == "start") {
5822  const QColor glissandoColor { notation.attribute("color") };
5823  const auto glissandoText = notation.text();
5824  if (gliss) {
5825  logger->logError(QString("overlapping glissando/slide number %1").arg(glissandoNumber+1), xmlreader);
5826  }
5827  else if (!note) {
5828  logger->logError(QString("no note for glissando/slide number %1 start").arg(glissandoNumber+1), xmlreader);
5829  }
5830  else {
5831  gliss = new Glissando(score);
5832  gliss->setAnchor(Spanner::Anchor::NOTE);
5833  gliss->setStartElement(note);
5834  gliss->setTick(tick);
5835  gliss->setTrack(track);
5836  gliss->setParent(note);
5837  if (glissandoColor.isValid())
5838  gliss->setColor(glissandoColor);
5839  gliss->setText(glissandoText);
5840  gliss->setGlissandoType(glissandoTag == 0 ? GlissandoType::STRAIGHT : GlissandoType::WAVY);
5841  spanners[gliss] = QPair<int, int>(tick.ticks(), -1);
5842  // qDebug("glissando/slide=%p inserted at first tick %d", gliss, tick);
5843  }
5844  }
5845  else if (glissandoType == "stop") {
5846  if (!gliss) {
5847  logger->logError(QString("glissando/slide number %1 stop without start").arg(glissandoNumber+1), xmlreader);
5848  }
5849  else if (!note) {
5850  logger->logError(QString("no note for glissando/slide number %1 stop").arg(glissandoNumber+1), xmlreader);
5851  }
5852  else {
5853  spanners[gliss].second = tick.ticks() + note->chord()->ticks().ticks();;
5854  gliss->setEndElement(note);
5855  gliss->setTick2(tick);
5856  gliss->setTrack2(track);
5857  // qDebug("glissando/slide=%p second tick %d", gliss, tick);
5858  gliss = nullptr;
5859  }
5860  }
5861  else
5862  logger->logError(QString("unknown glissando/slide type %1").arg(glissandoType), xmlreader);
5863  }
5864 
5865 //---------------------------------------------------------
5866 // addArpeggio
5867 //---------------------------------------------------------
5868 
5869 static void addArpeggio(ChordRest* cr, const QString& arpeggioType,
5870  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
5871  {
5872  // no support for arpeggio on rest
5873  if (!arpeggioType.isEmpty() && cr->type() == ElementType::CHORD) {
5874  std::unique_ptr<Arpeggio> arpeggio { new Arpeggio(cr->score()) };
5875  arpeggio->setArpeggioType(ArpeggioType::NORMAL);
5876  if (arpeggioType == "up")
5877  arpeggio->setArpeggioType(ArpeggioType::UP);
5878  else if (arpeggioType == "down")
5879  arpeggio->setArpeggioType(ArpeggioType::DOWN);
5880  else if (arpeggioType == "non-arpeggiate")
5881  arpeggio->setArpeggioType(ArpeggioType::BRACKET);
5882  else {
5883  logger->logError(QString("unknown arpeggio type %1").arg(arpeggioType), xmlreader);
5884  }
5885  // there can be only one
5886  if (!(static_cast<Chord*>(cr))->arpeggio()) {
5887  cr->add(arpeggio.release());
5888  }
5889  }
5890  }

5892 //---------------------------------------------------------
5893 // addArticLaissezVibrer
5894 //---------------------------------------------------------
5895 
5896 static void addArticLaissezVibrer(const Note* const note)
5897  {
5898  Q_ASSERT(note);
5899  auto chord = note->chord();
5900  if (!hasLaissezVibrer(chord)) {
5901  Articulation* na = new Articulation(SymId::articLaissezVibrerBelow, chord->score());
5902  chord->add(na);
5903  }
5904 
5905  }
5906 
5907 //---------------------------------------------------------
5908 // addTie
5909 //---------------------------------------------------------
5910 
5911 static void addTie(const Notation& notation, Score* score, Note* note, const int track,
5912  Tie*& tie, MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
5913  {
5914  Q_ASSERT(note);
5915  const QString& type = notation.attribute("type");
5916  const QString& orientation = notation.attribute("orientation");
5917  const QString& lineType = notation.attribute("line-type");
5918 
5919  if (type == "") {
5920  // ignore, nothing to do
5921  }
5922  else if (type == "start") {
5923  if (tie) {
5924  logger->logError(QString("Tie already active"), xmlreader);
5925  }
5926  tie = new Tie(score);
5927  note->setTieFor(tie);
5928  tie->setStartNote(note);
5929  tie->setTrack(track);
5930 
5931  if (orientation == "over")
5932  tie->setSlurDirection(Direction::UP);
5933  else if (orientation == "under")
5934  tie->setSlurDirection(Direction::DOWN);
5935  else if (orientation == "auto")
5936  ; // ignore
5937  else if (orientation == "")
5938  ; // ignore
5939  else
5940  logger->logError(QString("unknown tied orientation: %1").arg(orientation), xmlreader);
5941 
5942  if (lineType == "dotted")
5943  tie->setLineType(1);
5944  else if (lineType == "dashed")
5945  tie->setLineType(2);
5946  tie = nullptr;
5947  }
5948  else if (type == "stop")
5949  ; // ignore
5950  else if (type == "let-ring")
5951  addArticLaissezVibrer(note);
5952  else
5953  logger->logError(QString("unknown tied type %1").arg(type), xmlreader);
5954  }
5955 
5956 //---------------------------------------------------------
5957 // addWavyLine
5958 //---------------------------------------------------------
5959 
5960 static void addWavyLine(ChordRest* cr, const Fraction& tick,
5961  const int wavyLineNo, const QString& wavyLineType,
5962  MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners, TrillStack& trills,
5963  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
5964  {
5965  if (!wavyLineType.isEmpty()) {
5966  const auto ticks = cr->ticks();
5967  const auto track = cr->track();
5968  const auto trk = (track / VOICES) * VOICES; // first track of staff
5969  Trill*& trill = trills[wavyLineNo];
5970  if (wavyLineType == "start" || wavyLineType == "startstop") {
5971  if (trill) {
5972  logger->logError(QString("overlapping wavy-line number %1").arg(wavyLineNo+1), xmlreader);
5973  }
5974  else {
5975  trill = new Trill(cr->score());
5976  trill->setTrack(trk);
5977  if (wavyLineType == "start") {
5978  spanners[trill] = QPair<int, int>(tick.ticks(), -1);
5979  // qDebug("trill=%p inserted at first tick %d", trill, tick);
5980  }
5981  if (wavyLineType == "startstop") {
5982  spanners[trill] = QPair<int, int>(tick.ticks(), tick.ticks() + ticks.ticks());
5983  trill = nullptr;
5984  // qDebug("trill=%p inserted at first tick %d second tick %d", trill, tick, tick);
5985  }
5986  }
5987  }
5988  else if (wavyLineType == "stop") {
5989  if (!trill) {
5990  logger->logError(QString("wavy-line number %1 stop without start").arg(wavyLineNo+1), xmlreader);
5991  }
5992  else {
5993  spanners[trill].second = tick.ticks() + ticks.ticks();
5994  // qDebug("trill=%p second tick %d", trill, tick);
5995  trill = nullptr;
5996  }
5997  }
5998  else
5999  logger->logError(QString("unknown wavy-line type %1").arg(wavyLineType), xmlreader);
6000  }
6001  }
6002 
6003 //---------------------------------------------------------
6004 // addBreath
6005 //---------------------------------------------------------
6006 
6007 static void addBreath(ChordRest* cr, const Fraction& tick, SymId breath)
6008  {
6009  if (breath != SymId::noSym && !cr->isGrace()) {
6010  const auto b = new Breath(cr->score());
6011  // b->setTrack(trk + voice); TODO check next line
6012  b->setTrack(cr->track());
6013  b->setSymId(breath);
6014  const Fraction& ticks = cr->ticks();
6015  const auto seg = cr->measure()->getSegment(SegmentType::Breath, tick + ticks);
6016  seg->add(b);
6017  }
6018  }

6020 //---------------------------------------------------------
6021 // addChordLine
6022 //---------------------------------------------------------
6023 
6024 static void addChordLine(const Notation& notation, Note* note,
6025  MxmlLogger* logger, const QXmlStreamReader* const xmlreader)
6026  {
6027  const QString& chordLineType = notation.subType();
6028  if (chordLineType != "") {
6029  if (note) {
6030  const auto chordline = new ChordLine(note->score());
6031  if (chordLineType == "falloff")
6032  chordline->setChordLineType(ChordLineType::FALL);
6033  if (chordLineType == "doit")
6034  chordline->setChordLineType(ChordLineType::DOIT);
6035  if (chordLineType == "plop")
6036  chordline->setChordLineType(ChordLineType::PLOP);
6037  if (chordLineType == "scoop")
6038  chordline->setChordLineType(ChordLineType::SCOOP);
6039  note->chord()->add(chordline);
6040  }
6041  else
6042  logger->logError(QString("no note for %1").arg(chordLineType), xmlreader);
6043  }
6044  }

6046 //---------------------------------------------------------
6047 // notationWithAttributes
6048 //---------------------------------------------------------
6049 
6050 /**
6051  Helper function to create Notation with initial attributes.
6052  */
6053 
6054 Notation Notation::notationWithAttributes(const QString& name, const QXmlStreamAttributes attributes,
6055  const QString& parent, const SymId& symId)
6056  {
6057  Notation notation { name, parent, symId };
6058  for (const auto& attr : attributes) {
6059  notation.addAttribute(attr.name(), attr.value());
6060  }
6061  return notation;
6062  }
6063 
6064 //---------------------------------------------------------
6065 // addAttribute
6066 //---------------------------------------------------------
6067 
6068 void Notation::addAttribute(const QStringRef name, const QStringRef value)
6069  {
6070  _attributes.insert(std::pair<QString, QString>(name.toString(), value.toString()));
6071  }
6072 
6073 //---------------------------------------------------------
6074 // attribute
6075 //---------------------------------------------------------
6076 
6077 QString Notation::attribute(const QString& name) const
6078  {
6079  const auto it = _attributes.find(name);
6080  return (it != _attributes.end()) ? it->second : "";
6081  }
6082 
6083 //---------------------------------------------------------
6084 // print
6085 //---------------------------------------------------------
6086 
6087 QString Notation::print() const
6088  {
6089  QString res { _name };
6090 
6091  for (auto const& pair : _attributes) {
6092  res += " ";
6093  res += pair.first;
6094  res += " ";
6095  res += pair.second;
6096  }
6097 
6098  if (_text != "") {
6099  res += " ";
6100  res += _text;
6101  }
6102  return res;
6103  }

6120  Skip the current element, log debug as info.
6121  */
6122 
6123 void MusicXMLParserNotations::skipLogCurrElem()

6126  _e.skipCurrentElement();

6128 
6129 //---------------------------------------------------------
6130 // parse
6131 //---------------------------------------------------------
6132 
6133 void MusicXMLParserNotations::parse()
6134  {
6135  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "notations");
6136 
6137  while (_e.readNextStartElement()) {
6138  if (_e.name() == "arpeggiate") {
6139  _arpeggioType = _e.attributes().value("direction").toString();
6140  if (_arpeggioType == "") _arpeggioType = "none";
6141  _e.readNext();
6142  }
6143  else if (_e.name() == "articulations") {
6144  articulations();
6145  }
6146  else if (_e.name() == "dynamics") {
6147  dynamics();
6148  }
6149  else if (_e.name() == "fermata") {
6150  fermata();
6151  }
6152  else if (_e.name() == "glissando") {
6153  glissandoSlide();
6154  }
6155  else if (_e.name() == "non-arpeggiate") {
6156  _arpeggioType = "non-arpeggiate";
6157  _e.readNext();
6158  }
6159  else if (_e.name() == "ornaments") {
6160  ornaments();
6161  }
6162  else if (_e.name() == "slur") {
6163  slur();
6164  }
6165  else if (_e.name() == "slide") {
6166  glissandoSlide();
6167  }
6168  else if (_e.name() == "technical") {
6169  technical();
6170  }
6171  else if (_e.name() == "tied") {
6172  tied();
6173  }
6174  else if (_e.name() == "tuplet") {
6175  tuplet();
6176  }
6177  else {
6178  skipLogCurrElem();
6179  }
6180  }
6181 
6182  /*
6183  for (const auto& notation : _notations) {
6184  qDebug("%s", qPrintable(notation.print()));
6185  }
6186  */
6187 
6188  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "notations");
6189  }
6190 
6191 //---------------------------------------------------------
6192 // addNotation
6193 //---------------------------------------------------------
6194 
6195 void MusicXMLParserNotations::addNotation(const Notation& notation, ChordRest* const cr, Note* const note)
6196  {
6197  if (notation.symId() != SymId::noSym) {
6198  QString notationType = notation.attribute("type");
6199  QString placement = notation.attribute("placement");
6200  if (notation.name() == "fermata") {
6201  if (notationType != "" && notationType != "upright" && notationType != "inverted") {
6202  notationType = (const char*) 0;
6203  _logger->logError(QString("unknown fermata type %1").arg(notationType), &_e);
6204  }
6205  addFermataToChord(notation, cr);
6206  }
6207  else {
6208  if (notation.name() == "strong-accent") {
6209  if (notationType != "" && notationType != "up" && notationType != "down") {
6210  notationType = (const char*) 0;
6211  _logger->logError(QString("unknown %1 type %2").arg(notation.name(), notationType), &_e);
6212  }
6213  }
6214  else if (notation.name() == "harmonic" || notation.name() == "delayed-turn"
6215  || notation.name() == "turn" || notation.name() == "inverted-turn") {
6216  if (notation.name() == "delayed-turn") {
6217  // TODO: actually this should be offset a bit to the right
6218  }
6219  if (placement != "above" && placement != "below") {
6220  placement = (const char*) 0;
6221  _logger->logError(QString("unknown %1 placement %2").arg(notation.name(), placement), &_e);
6222  }
6223  }
6224  else {
6225  notationType = (const char*) 0; // TODO: Check for other symbols that have type
6226  placement = (const char*) 0; // TODO: Check for other symbols that have placement
6227  }
6228  addArticulationToChord(notation, cr);
6229  }
6230  }
6231  else if (notation.parent() == "ornaments") {
6232  if (notation.name() == "mordent" || notation.name() == "inverted-mordent") {
6233  addMordentToChord(notation, cr);
6234  }
6235  }
6236  else if (notation.parent() == "articulations") {
6237  if (note && notation.name() == "chord-line") {
6238  addChordLine(notation, note, _logger, &_e);
6239  }
6240  }
6241  else {
6242  // qDebug("addNotation: notation has been skipped: %s %s", qPrintable(notation.name()), qPrintable(notation.parent()));
6243  }
6244  }
6245 
6246 //---------------------------------------------------------
6247 // addToScore
6248 //---------------------------------------------------------
6249 
6250 /**
6251  Add the notations found to the score.
6252  Note that some notations attach to notes only in MuseScore,
6253  which means trying to attach them to a rest will crash,
6254  as in that case note is a nullptr.
6255  */
6256 
6257 void MusicXMLParserNotations::addToScore(ChordRest* const cr, Note* const note, const int tick, SlurStack& slurs,
6258  Glissando* glissandi[MAX_NUMBER_LEVEL][2], MusicXmlSpannerMap& spanners,
6259  TrillStack& trills, Tie*& tie)
6260  {
6261  addArpeggio(cr, _arpeggioType, _logger, &_e);
6262  addBreath(cr, cr->tick(), _breath);
6263  addWavyLine(cr, Fraction::fromTicks(tick), _wavyLineNo, _wavyLineType, spanners, trills, _logger, &_e);
6264 
6265  for (const auto& notation : _notations) {
6266  if (notation.symId() != SymId::noSym) {
6267  addNotation(notation, cr, note);
6268  }
6269  else if (notation.name() == "slur") {
6270  addSlur(notation, slurs, cr, tick, _logger, &_e);
6271  }
6272  else if (note && (notation.name() == "glissando" || notation.name() == "slide")) {
6273  addGlissandoSlide(notation, note, glissandi, spanners, _logger, &_e);
6274  }
6275  else if (note && notation.name() == "tied") {
6276  addTie(notation, _score, note, cr->track(), tie, _logger, &_e);
6277  }
6278  else if (note && notation.parent() == "technical") {
6279  addTechnical(notation, note);
6280  }
6281  else {
6282  addNotation(notation, cr, note);
6283  }
6284  }
6285 
6286  // more than one dynamic ???
6287  // LVIFIX: check import/export of <other-dynamics>unknown_text</...>
6288  // TODO remove duplicate code (see MusicXml::direction)
6289  for (const auto& d : qAsConst(_dynamicsList)) {
6290  auto dynamic = new Dynamic(_score);
6291  dynamic->setDynamicType(d);
6292 //TODO:ws if (hasYoffset) dyn->textStyle().setYoff(yoffset);
6293  addElemOffset(dynamic, cr->track(), _dynamicsPlacement, cr->measure(), Fraction::fromTicks(tick));
6294  }
6295  }
6296 
6297 //---------------------------------------------------------
6298 // stem
6299 //---------------------------------------------------------
6300 
6301 /**
6302  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/stem node.
6303  */
6304 
6305 void MusicXMLParserPass2::stem(Direction& sd, bool& nost)
6306  {
6307  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "stem");
6308 
6309  // defaults
6310  sd = Direction::AUTO;
6311  nost = false;
6312 
6313  QString s = _e.readElementText();
6314 
6315  if (s == "up")
6316  sd = Direction::UP;
6317  else if (s == "down")
6318  sd = Direction::DOWN;
6319  else if (s == "none")
6320  nost = true;
6321  else if (s == "double")
6322  ;
6323  else
6324  _logger->logError(QString("unknown stem direction %1").arg(s), &_e);
6325  }
6326 
6327 //---------------------------------------------------------
6328 // fermata
6329 //---------------------------------------------------------
6330 
6331 /**
6332  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/fermata node.
6333  Note: MusicXML common.mod: "An empty fermata element represents a normal fermata."
6334  */
6335 
6336 void MusicXMLParserNotations::fermata()
6337  {
6338  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "fermata");
6339 
6340  Notation notation = Notation::notationWithAttributes(_e.name().toString(), _e.attributes(), "notations");
6341  const auto fermataText = _e.readElementText();
6342 
6343  if (fermataText == "normal" || fermataText == "")
6344  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataAbove);
6345  else if (fermataText == "angled")
6346  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataShortAbove);
6347  else if (fermataText == "square")
6348  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataLongAbove);
6349  else if (fermataText == "double-angled")
6350  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataVeryShortAbove);
6351  else if (fermataText == "double-square")
6352  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataVeryLongAbove);
6353  else if (fermataText == "double-dot")
6354  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataLongHenzeAbove);
6355  else if (fermataText == "half-curve")
6356  notation.setSymId(SymId::fermataShortHenzeAbove);
6357 
6358  if (notation.symId() != SymId::noSym) {
6359  notation.setText(fermataText);
6360  _notations.push_back(notation);
6361  }
6362  else
6363  _logger->logError(QString("unknown fermata '%1'").arg(fermataText), &_e);
6364 
6365  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "fermata");
6366  }
6367 
6368 //---------------------------------------------------------
6369 // tuplet
6370 //---------------------------------------------------------
6371 
6372 /**
6373  Parse the /score-partwise/part/measure/note/notations/tuplet node.
6374  */
6375 
6376 void MusicXMLParserNotations::tuplet()
6377  {
6378  Q_ASSERT(_e.isStartElement() && _e.name() == "tuplet");
6379 
6380  QString tupletType = _e.attributes().value("type").toString();
6381  // QString tupletPlacement = _e.attributes().value("placement").toString(); not used (TODO)
6382  QString tupletBracket = _e.attributes().value("bracket").toString();
6383  QString tupletShowNumber = _e.attributes().value("show-number").toString();
6384 
6385  // ignore possible children (currently not supported)
6386  _e.skipCurrentElement();
6387 
6388  if (tupletType == "start")
6389  _tupletDesc.type = MxmlStartStop::START;
6390  else if (tupletType == "stop")
6391  _tupletDesc.type = MxmlStartStop::STOP;
6392  else if (tupletType != "" && tupletType != "start" && tupletType != "stop") {
6393  _logger->logError(QString("unknown tuplet type '%1'").arg(tupletType), &_e);
6394  }
6395 
6396  // set bracket, leave at default if unspecified
6397  if (tupletBracket == "yes")
6398  _tupletDesc.bracket = TupletBracketType::SHOW_BRACKET;
6399  else if (tupletBracket == "no")
6400  _tupletDesc.bracket = TupletBracketType::SHOW_NO_BRACKET;
6401 
6402  // set number, default is "actual" (=NumberType::SHOW_NUMBER)
6403  if (tupletShowNumber == "both")
6404  _tupletDesc.shownumber = TupletNumberType::SHOW_RELATION;
6405  else if (tupletShowNumber == "none")
6406  _tupletDesc.shownumber = TupletNumberType::NO_TEXT;
6407  else
6408  _tupletDesc.shownumber = TupletNumberType::SHOW_NUMBER;
6409 
6410  Q_ASSERT(_e.isEndElement() && _e.name() == "tuplet");
6411  }
